Commentary: Kemar Roach steams in from around the wicket and serves a fuller delivery first up outside off. The ball shapes away beautifully from the left-hander and David Warner makes an assured leave.
Roach pulls the length back and tightens the line around off stump. Warner goes on the back foot and defends it out on the off side.
Goes full again and shaping away from around off, left alone by Warner.
This is very full and close to the off pole, there is a bit of shape away from the left-hander and it is left alone for the keeper to collect.
Back of a length, angling in from around off stump. David Warner hops and pushes it out on the off side.
Top opening over from Roach and he starts off with a maiden. Full length around off and once again there's a good shape on the delivery. David Warner doesn't bother playing at it.

Jayden Seales starts off with a ripper. This is served on a good length on off stump, looking to bring it back but the ball just shoots up off the deck. Usman Khawaja looks to defend but gets a blow on the gloves.
A huge cheer from the crowd as Usman Khawaja and Australia get off the mark. This is short and on leg stump, Khawaja pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Pitched up in that channel around off, trying to swing it in but the ball just holds its line as Warner makes yet another leave.
Nice tight line around off, Warner doesn't get forward or back and ends up getting an inside edge onto the pads.
A bit straighter and fuller now from Seales and the ball just nips back in a touch. David Warner solidly blocks it off.
Good length, close to the off stump and just holding its line again. Warner shoulders arms.
Shortish length, angling into the body. Khawaja stays back and tucks it away past square leg for a single.
Warner is off the mark with an unconvincing shot. Good length, angling in from around off. Warner pushes at it and gets an outside edge through gully and picks up a single.
Goes fuller now and angles it on middle stump, Khawaja makes a block off the front foot.
Good early call and they get two. Good length, around the hips and there's that extra bounce again. Khawaja fends it 'round the corner towards fine leg for a brace.
On a length and outside off, Khawaja leaves this one alone.
Full and swinging away nicely but just a bit too wide of the off pole to make the batter play at it.
Pitched up around off at 132 clicks, Warner punches it towards silly mid off.
Tight line around the off pole and on a good length, Warner watchfully lets it through to the keeper.
A bit fuller and down the leg side, left alone by Warner.
FOUR! Crunched! This is banged in short and over middle, Warner swivels and hooks it through the square leg region for the first boundary of the Test match.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Jayden Seales comes back strongly after conceding the boundary and gets the early breakthrough. This is very full and angling across the left-hander. David Warner crouches a bit and looks for the expansive cover drive but his feet don't move and Warner ends up playing away from the body. The ball just holds its line a touch and take the inside edge before crashing into the stumps. Warner's poor run of form in Test matches continues and Seales is ecstatic.
Howout: b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Back of a length on off stump, Marnus Labuschagne goes back to defend it out. End of a brilliant over from Jayden Seales, a boundary and a wicket off it.
Fullish length, skidding through onto the pads, Khawaja plays it from inside his crease and towards short mid-wicket.
Full and in that channel around off stump, Khawaja lets it through to the keeper.
Pitches it up now on off stump, Khawaja drives it straight to the man at mid off.
FOUR! Gorgeous straight drive from Usman Khawaja. Full again, looking to angle it into middle and leg, Khawaja stands tall and just punches it right back past the bowler for a boundary.

Edged but just short of the fielder! Roach just pulls back the length a touch and keeps the line around off. The ball leaves the batter after pitching and Khawaja gets an outside edge on it. Luckily for him though, the ball lands well short of the man at second slip.
FOUR BYES! No chance for the keeper there. Full and angling well down the leg side, the ball races away into the fine leg fence.
Good length outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.

FOUR! Edged away! Good length, on a righter line this time. Labuschagne looks to get behind the line of the ball but gets an outside edge that goes through the slip cordon and into the third man fence. Labuschagne is off the mark as well.
Banged in short and well outside off, Labuschagne goes chasing after it but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Two is the call from Labuschagne but they will have to settle for the single. Full and straight, just gently pushed towards the vacant mid on region for a single.
Back of a length and on off stump, Usman Khawaja hops and keeps it down on the off side.
Fullish length, this one is pushed well across the left-hander and Khawaja makes an easy leave.
Good length around off, a bit of extra bounce on that occasion. Labuschagne is able to defend it back onto the deck.

Half a shout for lbw but the finger stays down. This is fuller and outside off, the ball just nips in sharply off the deck. Labuschagne shoulders arms and gets pinged on the back leg. The Windies players appeal but nothing is given.

NO BALL! Lovely delivery from Kemar Roach and once again there's an appeal for lbw but this time it doesn't matter. On a nagging length and shaping it in from around off. Labuschagne looks to defend but misses and the ball thuds into the pads. A no ball is called for overstepping.
A bit too full and straight, Labuschagne clips it through the mid-wicket region and he will come back easily for the third.
Roach switches to around the wicket for the left-hander and bowls it a bit shorter and wider. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Good length, outside off, not tight enough to make the batter play at it.
Pitches it up now and outside off, inviting the drive but Khawaja lets it through to the keeper.
On a length and outside off, just a hint of away movement off the deck. Labuschagne watchfully leaves it alone.
Full and wide outside off stump, a bit too wide to draw a shot from the batter.
A length ball, around the fifth stump line and it is once again left alone for the keeper to collect.
A bumper now around off stump, Labuschagne sways away from the line of the ball.
This is full and wide at 134 clicks, Marnus Labuschagne makes an easy leave.
Goes full again and outside off, just nipping away off the deck. Labuschagne looks to drive at it but leaves it alone in the end. Maiden!
Nicely bowled! On a nagging length and angling it into the off stump. Usman Khawaja looks to defend but gets taken aback a bit due to the extra bounce but is able to keep it out.
Way too full and way too wide from Roach this time. The keeper, Joshua Da Silva does well to collect that one.
Just pulls back the length a touch and tries to attack the pads, Khawaja defends it out towards silly mid on.
A hint of swing this time. This is full and around off, shaping away. Usman Khawaja drives it on the up but it is well stopped by the man at silly mid off.
Back of a length, close to the off stump, Khawaja gets right behind the line and defends it out with soft hands.
Full and well outside the off pole, left alone for the keeper to collect. Another maiden.
Alzarri Joseph starts off with a spicy bumper. This is banged in short and over middle and leg at around 138 clicks. The ball just zips through and Labuschagne does well to duck under it.
Back of a length and outside off. Seaming away and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
Lands it on a length and angles it towards the pads. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for a single.
Touch shorter again and angling into the body. Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. It seams away a bit and Usman Khawaja makes an easy leave.
So, Good start from Alzarri Joseph as well! Serves it on a good length and outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone again.
Roach bowls a lovely delivery angling into off. It is on a good length and Marnus Labuschagne fends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Roach bangs it short but there is not much pace in this delivery. It sits up nicely for Marnus Labuschagne and he pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Nice good-length delivery. It is outside off and the ball nips back in sharply. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
On a length and angling into middle. Marnus Labuschagne turns it towards the leg side for a single.
Goes a tad fuller and on middle from 'round the wicket. Usman Khawaja defends it solidly towards mid on.
Another solid block from Usman Khawaja! Roach continues to hit that good length, on off. Usman Khawaja comes well forward and defends it.
Lands it on a length and angles it into middle at 140.8 kph. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards right of the bowler.
A fullish delivery angling into middle at 142 clicks. Marnus Labuschagne fends it from his crease.
Touch shorter and on off. Marnus Labuschagne is solid in his defence again.
Lands it on a length, on off. Nice pace again at 142.3 kph and Marnus Labuschagne decides to block it again.
Angles it towards the body, touch shorter and Marnus Labuschagne is in no hurry to try something different and just blocks it.
A lovely good-length delivery, outside off. Bit of shape away from the batter and Marnus Labuschagne makes a good leave.

Seales starts his new spell with a shortish delivery on middle. Usman Khawaja pulls it to deep square leg and takes three. The Aussies have looked very comfortable against the short deliveries so far.
Touch short of good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
Short and wide outside off. Marnus Labuschagne gets the width to work with and cuts it through cover-point for a couple. Seales has not looked comfortable from this end so far.
Lands it on a length and angles it into middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it from his crease.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
A bit full this time, around off. Marnus Labuschagne resists the temptation to drive and makes another leave.
Joseph comes 'round the wicket and bowls it full and angles it on the pads. Usman Khawaja flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
On a good length and outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it.
Back of a length and outside off at 138.9 kph. Usman Khawaja makes a good leave.
On the shorter side, on off. Usman Khawaja rides the bounce and works it towards the leg side for an easy single.
Nice length this! A fullish delivery, outside off. Good shape too away from the batter and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
On a good length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne watches it till the end and then leaves it alone.
Mayers starts off with a full delivery on off. Usman Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Bit of a leading edge there! This is full and on middle. Usman Khawaja tries to work it towards the leg side but closes his bat face bit early and gets a leading edge that rolls towards the bowler.
On a length, on off. Usman Khawaja defends it solidy from his crease.
Bowls it on a shorter length, on middle. Usman Khawaja pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On a good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne fends it from his crease.

Top delivery to end the over! Mayers bowls it on a good length and around off. The ball shapes away nicely and Marnus Labuschagne who first tries to push at it takes his bat away from the line of the ball at the last moment.
On a good length and around off. Usman Khawaja leaves it as the ball goes just past his pads back to the keeper.
Goes a bit full on middle. Usman Khawaja clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Bowls it vety full on off at 138 kph. Marnus Labuschagne gets his bat down in time.
On a length, on off at 140.2 kph. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards the leg side.

Oh, this short delivery has hurried Marnus Labuschagne! Joseph bowls it short and angles it towards the body. Marnus Labuschagne ends up getting in no man's land as he first sets up to pull it and then decides to defend it. The ball hits his gloves and loops up in the air towars the off side.
On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it from the middle of his blade this time.
Lovely delivery! This is what Mayers can do! Serves it on a good length and outside off. The ball shapes away just a bit and beats Usman Khawaja as he tries to defend it off the front foot.
On a length, on off. Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Serves it again on a length and Usman Khawaja fends it again right under his eyes.
Bit wider outside off. On a length again and Usman Khawaja leaves it this time.
On a good length and outside off. Usman Khawaja decides to leave it alone again.
Better length this! A fullish delivery on middle. Usman Khawaja defends it from his crease.
Alzarri Joseph angles a length delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it right of mid on and looks for a single but no run there.
Serves it on a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne fends it off the middle of his blade.
On the shorter side, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and blocks it out.
Joseph continues to hit that length hard, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it again solidly.
Game of patience this! Joseph bowls it again on a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne is not trying anything fancy and blocks it again.
Just short of good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it as he rides the bounce nicely.
Lands it on a length, on off. Usman Khawaja takes a short stride forward and defends it.
This one seams back into the batter! Mayers lands it on a good length and outside off. The ball seams away and Usman Khawaja leaves it. The ball goes just past the off pole there!
Angles it into middle from 'round the wicket. Usman Khawaja clips it to fine leg for a single.
On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it right under his eyes.

That's a good shot! A fullish delivery, around off. Marnus Labuschagne just leans forward and drives it past mid off. However, the timing is not good enough to take it towards the ropes as the fielder chasing it from mid off cuts it off. Two taken.
On a good length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it from his crease.
Holder starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Angling across the batter and Usman Khawaja leaves it.
Angles it across the Khawaja again. This time on a good length and Usman Khawaja decides to leave it again.
Half an appeal there but nothing serious! This one pitches around leg, on a length. Usman Khawaja tries to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads but it is clearly going down leg.
On a good length and angled across the batter again. Usman Khawaja leaves it.
Holder stays consistent and lands it on a length again, outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Usman Khawaja is happy to just leave it alone.
Nagging length, angling it in from outside off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it on the up but straight to the man at short extra cover.
Fullish length, outside off and shaping into the right-hander. Labuschagne watchfully leaves it alone.
Just a fraction shorter and Labuschagne punches onto the width on offer as he cuts this one past the man at point. The fielder gives chase as the batters come back for three with ease.
Switches to around the wicket now and angles it in on a fuller length from outside off. Usman Khawaja lets it through to the keeper.
Pitches it up now on middle and off, Khawaja leans forward and solidly blocks it out.
On a good length and around off, shaping away from the left-hander. Usman Khawaja shoulders arms.
Full and in the channel around off, angling it in. Marnus Labuschagne makes an assured leave.
This is pitched up on off stump, a slight bit of movement into the right-hander. Labuschagne blocks it out towards mid on.
This is floated up around the pads, Labuschagne works it towards square leg.
Pitched-up delivery, shaping in beautifully from around off. Labuschagne blocks it under his eye line.
Just brings the length back a touch and angles it into off stump. Labuschagne with another solid defensive shot off the front foot.
Fullish delivery, wide of the off pole and left alone for the keeper to collect. Back-to-back maidens for Jason Holder.
Roston Chase starts off with a shortish delivery around off. Usman Khawaja goes on the back foot and punches it towards covers.
Flatter this time and tighter around the off pole. Usman Khawaja looks to cut off the back foot but is a bit late on it.
Short again and on the stumps this time, Usman Khawaja pulls it in front of mid-wicket and comfortably gets back for the third. The 50 is now up for Australia.
Tossed up, full and around off, Labuschagne firms it towards silly mid off.
BEATEN! Just holds it back a touch and bowls it on a length around off. Labuschagne gets squared up as the ball slides on and beats the outside edge.
Tosses it up now around off, Labuschagne knocks it down to long on for a single.
Lovely delivery! Jason Holder pitches it up on the fifth stump and it is angled in. The ball pitches and shapes away beautifully, zipping past the outside edge of Labuschagne's willow.
Around the top of off, solidly kept out by Labuschagne.
Goes a bit wide of the crease and tries to angle it in from outside off. Labuschagne makes an easy leave.
Slightly pitched up on the pads, Labuschagne plays it with soft hands and in front of mid-wicket.
Full and on off stump, punched away towards mid on.
Keeps it full and outside off, Labuschagne shoulders arms at it. A hat-trick of maidens now for Jason Holder to start his day.
Just a fraction shorter and outside off, Usman Khawaja backs away to cut it towards deep point for a single.
Nicely bowled. Chase sees Labuschagne advancing and just pulls back the length and also gives it more flight. Labuschagne adjusts well and blocks it out.
Drifted onto middle and leg, flicked away towards short leg.

FOUR! Tossed up, around off, Marnus Labuschagne steps down the track and hammers it to the right of the man at mid off for a boundary. Roston Chase isn't happy and feels that the fielder could have done better there.
Around middle and leg, this is nudged away onto the leg side.
Nicely flighted, around middle, Labuschagne pushes it back to the bowler.
Holder comes from around the wicket and serves it full and well wide of the off pole. Usman Khawaja doesn't play at it.
Length ball, close to the off pole and Usman Khawaja makes an assured leave. The ball nips back in late after going past the stumps.
Good length on leg stump, Usman Khawaja tucks it off his hips through backward square leg and rotates the strike.
Pitches it up now on middle, Labuschagne pushes it out towards silly mid on.
Full and outside off, left alone for the keeper to collect.
Back of a length, outside off and Labuschagne shoulders arms at it.
Floated up, outside off, Usman Khawaja reaches forward and plays it towards cover-point.
SIX! All the way! Tossed up around off, Usman Khawaja skips down the track and lifts it high and handsome over the long off fence for a biggie. The 50 partnership is now up between these two.
Flighted, full and around off, this is wristily driven towards wide long off for a couple of more runs.
Nagging length, drifted onto middle and leg. Khawaja keeps it out.
Around middle and off this time, Usman Khawaja solidly defends it out.

Top delivery! Roston Chase just slows this one up a touch, serves it on a nagging length and pushes it a bit wider. Usman Khawaja is forced into playing the drive but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Good length, around off and this is left alone by Labuschagne.
Back of a length, closer to the off pole. Labuschagne stays back and bunts it up towards silly point.
Goes fuller now and angles it in from around off, Labuschagne presents a dead bat at it.
Fullish delivery outside off, Labuschagne drops it onto the off side and just threatens to take the single but Khawaja says no.
Very full and on the fifth stump, this is driven straight to the man at mid off.
Length ball, outside off and this one just holds its line. Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
Flighted, on a length and outside off, Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Nicely drifted in from around the off pole and this one is a bit quicker as well. Usman Khawaja pushes it out on the off side.
FOUR! The runs are now starting to flow off Khawaja's bat. This is dragged down on middle, Khawaja rocks back and pulls it well in front of the square on the leg side for a boundary.
On a length and outside off, Khawaja doesn't play at it.
This is around the pads, Usman Khawaja goes back in his crease and works it away down to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Chase fires this one into middle and leg but Usman Khawaja manages to keep it out. That will be it for the first session as Lunch is called.
Roach starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery, around off. The ball nips back in and Marnus Labuschagne blocks it onto the turf.
Good delivery again! Lands it just short of good length and outside off. The ball zips off the surface with some good bounce and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
On a length and outside off. Bit of shape away from the batter and Marnus Labuschagne lets it go again.
Oh, what a ripper this is! Lands it on a good length, around off. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside of Marnus Labuschagne's blade as he tries to defend it.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it towards square leg for a single.
A fullish delivery on off to end a very good first over after Lunch. Usman Khawaja drives it to covers.
Almost drags it onto his stumps! On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne fends it from his crease onto the turf. However, the ball rolls back and goes just past the stumps.
Short of good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
Wow! A perfect shory delivery now! Bangs it short and on off. A good pacy delivery this and Marnus Labuschagne sways away from the line of the ball.

FOUR! That has caught everyone by surprise but Marnus Labuschagne will take it! A full toss, on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets a thick outside edge as he tries to defend it and the ball goes through the point region for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it solidly from his crease.
Goes fuller and around off. Marnus Labuschagne leanes forward and drives it through covers for a couple.
Back of a length and angling into the ribs of Usman Khawaja. He clips it towards the leg side.
Just short of good length and around off. Bit of extra bounce as well on this delivery and Usman Khawaja defends it well as he takes his one hand off the blade.
On a length, on off. Usman Khawaja plays it with a straight blade towards the off side.
Hits that hard length again, on off. Usman Khawaja fends it towards the off side as he takes a decent stride forward.
On the shorter side and on middle. Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Usman Khawaja makes a good leave.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it onto the turf as he rides the bounce nicely.
Short and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne cuts it hard towards the point fielder.
Back of a length, on middle at 137.5 kph. Marnus Labuschagne fends it towards mid on and takes a quick single. Joseph needs to be a bit fuller here.
Bowls it very full on off this time. Usman Khawaja gets his bat down in time and takes a single as the ball rolls towards square off the wicket on the off side.
FOUR! Beautifully timed! Alzarri Joseph bowls it full again on middle. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it gently off the middle of his blade and the ball runs through the mid on region for a boundary.
Lands it on a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne has been very patient today and shows it yet again here as he leaves it alone.

Nicely bowled but nicely played too! Just short of good length and outside off. The ball straightens after pitching and bounces nicely as well and Marnus Labuschagne keeps his bat inside the line of the ball.
On a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne turns it towards the leg side for a single.

FOUR! Usman Khawaja picks the length quickly and pulls it quite nicely here. Roach bowls it short and on off. Usman Khawaja gets into his position quickly and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Usman Khawaja blocks it from his crease.
Fullish length, around off. Usman Khawaja drives it to covers this time.
An effort ball from Joseph! Bangs it short angling into middle. Marnus Labuschagne ducks under it.
This one seams away off the deck! Short and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne sets up initially to cut it but then leaves it alone as he ball goes further away.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne fends it from his crease.
Joseph bowls another bouncer on middle. Marnus Labuschagne is happy to just duck under it.
Shortish length again, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne just tucks it towards the leg side and takes a quick single this time.
Ends the over with another short delivery, this time to Usman Khawaja. On middle and leg and Usman Khawaja too just ducks under it without much fuss.
Tad shorter and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it through square leg for a couple.
On a length, on off at 133 kph. Marnus Labuschagne defends it calmly towards the leg side.
FOUR! Oh, there is a leg slip for that very shot but it it goes right of that fielder. A length delivery on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne clips it right of the leg slip fielder for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for a single.

Roach comes up with this superb deliveries every now and then but the wicket still eludes him. On a good length and around off. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Usman Khawaja's blade as he tries to defend it.
Goes fuller and around off/ Usman Khawaja drives it to cover-point.
Goes full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to short mid-wicket where Tagenarine Chanderpaul on debut makes a good diving stop.

14th Test match half-century for Marnus Labuschagne! This man just continues to grow from strength to strength. He has shown tremendous ability to adjust his game according to the conditions and has come out with flying colours more often than not. This is full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it through mid-wicket and takes three.
On a length and outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Holder serves it on a length again. A pretty harmless delivery as it is outside off and Usman Khawaja leaves it.
On a length, angling into middle from 'round the wicket. Usman Khawaja defends it towards mid on.
Just short of good length and on around off now. Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Touch shorter and around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it to covers as he rides the bounce nicely.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne makes a good leave.
Pulls his length back slightly, around off. Marnus Labuschagne stays in his crease and lets it go.
Shortish delivery, around off. The ball zips off the surface as Marnus Labuschagne gets an inside edge this time as he tries to punch it. The ball goes just past the stumps.
On a length and and on off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to clip it towards the leg side but ends up getting a leading edge towards covers.
FOUR! Nicely played! Serves a fullish delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it through square leg for a boundary. Very good shot!
On a length, on off. Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Fraction short and around off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Nice calm leave again! A fullish delivery, around off. Usman Khawaja just keeps his eye on the ball and lets it go.
A very harmless delivery as it is on a length and way outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Touch shorter and on off. Usman Khawaja defends it solidly from his crease.
Another maiden for Holder. He lands it on a good length and angles it across the batter as Usman Khawaja lets it go again.

A peach of a delivery to start a new spell from Seales! Lands it on a good length and around off. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Marnus Labuschagne front foot defence.
On a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it through the backward square leg region for a couple.
On the shorter side, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and blocks it out.
100-run stand comes up between these two! Seales goes fuller and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it through mid-wicket for a couple. This partnership is looking dangerous for West Indies now.
Pulls his length back slightly and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne makes a good leave.
Bowls it on a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone. Good over from Seales here.
Fullish delivery around middle and off, Usman Khawaja solidly defends it out.
Full again, angling it across the left-hander. Khawaja watchfully leaves it alone.
Length ball, pushed well outside off and angling across yet again, No shot is offered by Khawaja.
Pitched up a bit, close to the off pole and just holding its line. Usman Khawaja makes a very assured leave. A no ball has been called as Jason Holder has overstepped.
Good length, around the off pole, left alone for the keeper to collect.

In the air but lands safely! Short of a length around off and hurrying onto the batter. Usman Khawaja looks to take it on but gets it off the top edge. The ball goes up around the vacant mid-wicket region and the batters are able to pick up a single.
A gentle-paced delivery, full and angling down leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to flick but misses.
This is full and outside off, Usman Khawaja plants the front foot forward and drives it through extra cover. The fielder gives chase and the batters come back for the third with ease.
Fuller in length and wide of the off stump, left alone for the keeper to collect.

FOUR! Awkward one for Labuschagne but he gets lucky there. This is banged in short at a good height and over middle. Labuschagne is caught in two minds there and just ends up getting his bat up. The ball flies off the top edge and into the fine leg fence.

EDGY FOUR! Jayden Seales cannot believe it as Labuschagne gets a slice of luck once again. Good length, on a tight line around off stump. Labuschagne pushes at it and gets an outside edge that goes in between first and third slip for a boundary.
On a hard length and outside off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Pitches it up now around the fifth stump line and this one is let through for the keeper to collect.
Nicely drifted onto middle, Khawaja watchfully eases it out on the off side.
FOUR! Nicely done! This is quicker and very full around off. Usman Khawaja plays it late and just opens the face of the bat to get it into the third man fence.
FIFTY for Usman Khawaja, his brilliant run in 2022 continues with another solid knock. Flatter one around off, Khawaja rocks back and caresses it through cover for a single.
Tossed up around off, Labuschagne comes forward and pushes it towards mid off.
Around middle and leg, this is driven through wide mid on. Labuschagne looks for two but will only get a single.
Full and on off stump, knocked down to long off for one more.
Back of a length and around off, Usman Khawaja gets behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Just a fraction shorter and over middle and leg. Usman Khawaja hops and keeps it down on the leg side.
Around the top of off, Khawaja defends it out on the off side off the back foot.
A length ball, in the channel around off and just angling across. Usman Khawaja shoulders arms.
Seales hits the length hard and keeps it around off. There is a bit of an extra bounce but Khawaja keeps it down on the off side.
Pitched a bit further up and around off, Khawaja looks to cut but pulls out of the shot as the ball is just a bit too full to cut.
Slows it up now and bowls it on a length around the pads. This is nudged away towards backward square leg.
Around middle and leg, this is eased away through wide mid on for a single.
Nicely flighted, full and outside off. Usman Khawaja reaches out and drives it towards deep extra cover for an easy single.
A bit slower and angling it across the right-hander, Labuschagne shuffles a bit and works it 'round the corner for one more.
On the shorter side and outside off, cut away off the back foot but straight to point.
A slight fumble and the batters are able to scamper through. Shorter again and outside off, Usman Khawaja rocks back and cuts it hard towards point where the fielder misfields and allows the single.
Fullish length around off, holding its line, Khawaja leaves it alone.
Pitched a bit further up and on off stump, Usman Khawaja gets back in his crease to defend it out.
Full and around off, Khawaja shoulders arms at it.
Not off the middle of the bat but good enough to pick up three. This is full and wide, Usman Khawaja drives it on the up and through extra cover for an easy three.
Good length around off, Marnus Labuschagne defends it back onto the pitch.
Firmly struck but straight to the fielder. This is a half-volley outside off, Labuschagne drives it along the ground but finds the man at extra cover.
Just a touch quicker and fuller, drifted onto middle, Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Flighted, full and on middle and leg, Khwaja leans forward and flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Just a tad shorter and around off, this is cut away straight to the man at point.
And again! A bit closer to the off pole this time and quicker too. Usman Khawaja cuts it off the back foot towards point.
Tossed up well outside off and Khawaja lets it go.
A maiden! Nicely flighted, on off stump and Usman Khawaja prods forward to defend.
Starts the new spell with a half-volley on leg stump. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it straight into the pads of the man at short leg and picks up a single off the fumble.
An attempted short ball well down leg and left alone for the keeper to collect.
Good bouncer, over middle and at 135 clicks. Usman Khawaja does well to duck under it.
Shorter and around the hips, pulled away behind square on the leg side for a single.
A sharp bumper now, at a good height and over the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne is able to duck under it with ease.
Back of a length and outside off, left alone by Labuschagne.
Drops it a bit short and outside off, Usman Khawaja rocks back and cuts it towards deep point for a couple of runs.
A bit of turn! Nicely flighted around off stump, Khawaja looks to defend off the front foot but the ball grips and turns away, beating the outside edge.
Floated up on off stump, Usman Khawaja defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Khawaja drives it with the turn and through extra cover for a single.
Excellent running! Tossed up again, Labuschagne steps out and drives it towards mid off for a quick single.
Drifted onto the off pole from around the stumps but Khawaja stays solid in defense.

Short of a length and around off, Marnus Labuschagne gets on top of the bounce and pulls it well in front of the square on the leg side. The fielder from mid-wicket gives it a long chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Banged in short and over leg stump at around 139 clicks, Usman Khawaja ducks under it.
A good bouncer, around the off pole and shooting up nicely off the deck. Khawaja is able to duck under this one as well.
Back of a length, around leg stump and at 140 clicks. Khawaja works it away off his hips towards square leg for a single.
Good length, nipping back in a bit from outside off. Labuschagne makes an easy leave.
Full and outside off, at 142.3 KPH and this one just zips through. Marnus Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
Bowls it a touch short, on off. Usman Khawaja goes back and blocks it.
FOUR! 150 up for Australia! Shortish delivery on off. Usman Khawaja rocks back and pulls it firmly through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Pitched outside off and turns away. Usman Khawaja sets up to cut it but then decides against it.
Tossed up, around off. Usman Khawaja pushes it to covers.
An arm ball now, on off. Quicker and Usman Khawaja blocks it from his crease.
Fires a full delivery again on off. Usman Khawaja gets his bat down in time.
Josepth bowls it touch short, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and blocks it out.
On the shorter side again, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Takes his length a bit fuller this time. Around off but Marnus Labuschagne has no problem in leaving it again.
Joseph goes fuller on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it firmly off the middle of his blade but straight to mid off.

Bangs it short and around leg. Marnus Labuschagne tries to pull it but missess. However, Windies players were a bit excited there and maybe they heard some noise but Kraigg Brathwaite decides against taking a review.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce nicely to defend it solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kyle Mayers gets back into the attack and strikes straightaway! A big wicket here of Usman Khawaja and the partnership is finally broken. This man Mayers has the knack of picking up big wickets and he has done it yet again here. Serves a beautiful good-length delivery, around off. Mayers gets good shape away from the batter and the ball catches the outside edge of Usman Khawaja's blade as he tries to defend it. Joshua Da Silva takes an easy regulation catch and that is exactly what Windies needed to lift their spirits up.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kyle Mayers

Commentary: On a length and on middle. Smith defends it towards the leg side.
Pulls his length back a bit and on middle. Smith works it to mid-wicket.
On a length and there is that shape again into the batter as Smith blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on middle as the ball shapes back in again. Smith tries to push it but the ball goes off the inside half of his blade to fine leg for a single. He is off the mark!
On a length and just around off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Smith watches it till the end and lets it go.
A fullish delivery, on off. Smith drives it off the outside half of his blade this time and takes a single as the ball goes towards covers.

FOUR! Suddenly things are happening here for the Windies!  This is a fullish delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to drive it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies to the right and just over Holder at third slip as he tries to catch it. The ball runs away towards the third man fence.
Another lovely delivery! Pitches it on a good length, around off. The ball seams away after pitching and beats the outside edge of Marnus Labuschagne's blade as he tries to defend it.
Fraction short and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.

Absolute jaffa to end the over! Angles it on a good length, around off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to defend it but the ball just straightens a bit after pitching and beats Marnus Labuschagne's blade yet again. Brilliant stuff!
Back of a length and outside off. Smith leaves it.
Serves it on a good length and around off. The ball swings into Smith but he decides to let it go.
On a length, on off. Smith defends it from his crease this time.
Bowls it in that channel outside off again. Gets some swing into the batter again as Smith is happy to not touch it.
Back of a length, on middle. Smith tries to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Just short of good length again, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne shuffles across and defends it towards the leg side.
Roach with a good-length delivery, outside off. Smith leaves it.
Angles a a length-delivery on middle. Smith works it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out. Roach needs to be tad fuller here.
Bangs it short on off. The ball hurries Marnus Labuschagne a bit as he gets a top edge on his pull. The ball goes in the air and over square leg as the batters take two.
Serves it on a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne fends it from his crease.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne gets inside the line of the ball and defends it towards the mid-wicket region.
Shortish delivery on off. Smith rides the bounce and blocks it out.
A length delivery on off. Smith defends it solidly here. Need to be fuller to create more chances.
A fullish delivery, on off. Smith drives it to covers.
Nice shape into Smith this time. On a length and on off. Smith gets across and defends it towards the leg side.
Touch short and on middle. Smith works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Lands a good-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne watches it till the end and decides to leave this alone. That will be Tea on Day1! Australia are 162 for 2.
FOUR! Whacked away! Kemar Roach starts the new session with a loosener. This is short and over leg stump, Steven Smith pulls it with disdain and over the jumping man at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length around off, Smith blocks it out onto the off side.
A touch fuller now, nipping in from around the off stump. Smith looks to tuck but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Good length around middle and leg, this is nudged away towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on the fifth stump line, Steven Smith looks to punch off the back foot but mistimes it badly.
Full and outside off, Smith looks to drive at it but then makes a classic 'Steven Smith' leave.
Gentle-paced delivery, at around 117 clicks and full and wide outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it through to the keeper.
Mayers tightens the line around off stump and keeps it full. Labuschagne makes an assured leave.
Fullish delivery outside off, Labuschagne doesn't bother playing at it.
Goes a bit wider of the crease and angles it in from outside off. Labuschagne shoulders arms at it.

They run four! Full and wide, driven square of the wicket by Marnus Labuschagne and Alzarri Joseph gives it a chase from inside the ring. Joseph does eventually get there but the throw is a weak one which allows the batters to cross over for the fourth run.
Fuller and in that channel around off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Back of a length, over middle and leg, Smith keeps it down on the pitch.
Fullish delivery around off, Smith leaves it alone and the ball just nips away late before going into the keeper's mitts.
Keeps it on a fuller length and taught around the off pole. Steven Smith goes back and across before making the leave.

BEATEN! Kemar Roach angles it into the off stump from wide of the crease and the ball straightens beautifully after pitching. Steven Smith looks to punch it straight but is beaten past the outside edge.
Full and at the stumps, driven firmly towards mid on for a single.
A length ball now, a touch outside off and Labuschagne leaves it alone.
This is a bit fuller and well outside the off stump. Steven Smith leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
On a length and angling it into the off stump. Smith blocks it out from his crease.
Good running once again. This is very full and outside off, Steven Smith opens the face of the blade and punches it through the cover region for three runs.
Pitched up around off, Labuschagne punches it right back at the bowler who does well to stop it.
Fuller in length and outside off, no shot offered by Labuschagne.
Full again and angling onto the pads, Marnus Labuschagne wrists it away through backward square leg for a run.
Starts the new spell with a fuller delivery, angled in at the toes. Labuschagne blocks it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Overpitched and punished! This is outside off and Marnus Labuschagne is quick to pounce on it. Labuschagne drives it through the big gap around extra cover and picks up a boundary. He is into the 90s now.
Nagging length, angling it into middle and leg, Labuschagne hangs back and keeps it out on the leg side.
Fuller delivery outside off and this one leaves the batter after pitching. Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good delivery! A touch fuller and angling in from around off. The ball straightens after pitching as Labuschagne makes yet another assured leave.
Good length around off, Labuschagne stays back and nudges it down onto the leg side.
FOUR! Easily done! Full and on the pads, Steven Smith flicks it well in front of mid-wicket and times it well enough to pick up a boundary.
Back of a length and well outside off, Smith looks to step out and pull but changes his mind and leaves it alone.
Fullish length, curving in from outside off, Smith leans forward to make the block.
Around the off pole, Smith solidly defends it towards cover-point.
Full again but just a bit too straight, Steven Smith clips it away through mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.
Good length outside off, Smith keeps it out on the off side.
Uppish but safe! Pitched up outside off, Labuschagne leans forward and looks to punch but does so a bit uppishly. The ball though lands well in front of the man at short cover.
This is around off stump, Labuschagne lets it through to the keeper.
Around the top of off, Labuschagne makes yet another leave.
Good length over middle, Labuschagne stays in his crease and pushes it out towards mid on.
FOUR! Threading the needle! Pitched up outside off, Marnus Labuschagne drives it on the up and pierces the small gap between extra cover and mid off to collect a boundary.
Holder pulls back the length and tightens the line around off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.

Seales starts the new spell with a half-volley around off, Steven Smith drives it through extra cover and the fielder from inside the ring has to give it a long chase. The batters come back for the third with utmost ease.
Good length, angled into middle and kept out by Labuschagne.

Excellent running and the runs are flowing thickly for the Aussies here. Back of a length and outside off, Labuschagne taps it wide of the man at point for a couple of runs. They look for the third and almost run into each other before completing it.
A length ball around middle, this is just nudged away onto the leg side for a single.
Sweetly timed but finds the fielder! Full and around off, Marnus Labuschagne middles the cover drive but hits it straight to the man at short cover.
Short and at the body, a controlled pull shot by Labuschagne towards deep mid-wicket for a single. He moves on to 98 now.
Short and down the leg side, Marnus Labuschagne pulls it hard and down to fine leg for only a single.
Short again and at the body, Steven Smith pulls it away behind the man at square leg and picks up a brace. The 200 comes up for Australia as well.
Around the top of off, solidly blocked out by Smith.
It is just too easy at the moment for these two and the 50-run stand is also brought up. Overpitched and outside off, Steven Smith drives it square of the wicket and picks up an easy three.
Good length on leg stump, Labuschagne dabs it down on the leg side.
Fullish length, well outside off and left alone by Labuschagne.

FOUR! Unlucky for the bowler. Good length, angling in from around off and straightening off the deck. Steven Smith gets squared up but plays at it with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the slip cordon into the third man fence.
Full and on the pads, this is wristed away well in front of mid-wicket for a couple more.
Fraction shorter and around off, Smith just jabs it through mid-wicket for one.
Fullish length from Seales outside off, Labuschagne watchfully leaves it alone.

FOUR! Take a bow, Marnus Labuschagne! An eighth Test match century for him and he has made it look really easy so far. This is a wide half-tracker, Labuschagne reaches out and slaps it in front of the square on the off side. The ball trickles away into the fence and Labuschagne will now be eyeing a big one here.
Short of a length and around off, this is pulled through wide mid on for a single.
Holder pitches this one up on middle and off as Labuschagne gets a leading edge towards cover-point.
Full and wide, a bit too wide though to make the batter play at it.
Pitched up a bit in that channel around off and Labuschagne makes a watchful leave.
Full again but angling down the leg side as Labuschagne misses the flick.
Pitched up again, around the off stump and angling in. Marnus Labuschagne lets this one through to the keeper.
A tidy over from Holder as he bowls a maiden. This is a bit fuller and around off, the ball angles in after pitching but Labuschagne makes yet another assured leave.
FOUR! A juicy half-volley to start with. Steven Smith leans on and drives it gloriously through the small gap between short extra cover and mid off to find the fence.
Pulls back the length a touch and Smith just blocks it out.
Nicely flighted, on a fullish length and drifted in from outside off. Smith presses forward to defend.
Bowls it a touch shorter and at the stumps, Smith rocks back to keep it out.

FOUR! A second boundary in the over and Australia are piling on the misery here. Tossed-up delivery well outside off, Steven Smith drives it square of the wicket this time and gets it into the cover boundary.
On middle and leg, flicked away towards mid-wicket.
On a fuller length and around off, Labuschagne blocks it towards mid on.
Goes a bit wider of the crease and looks to angle it in from outside off. Labuschagne stays solid in defense.
A length ball, drifted onto the pads, Labuschagne works it away through backward square leg for a single.
Slightly fuller but well wide of the off stump, left alone by Steven Smith.
Back of a length and outside off, Smith goes on the back foot and punches it out towards cover-point.
Fuller one around off and just shaping away a touch. Smith defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Marnus Labuschagne shimmies down the track and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Tad short and turning into middle. Smith works it to mid-wicket and Marnus Labuschagne wants a single but is rightly sent back by Smith.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Smith turns it to deep square leg for a couple this time.
Touch shorter and quicker on middle. Smith blocks it off the back foot.
Chase goes full again on middle. Smith clips it to mid-wicket.
Shortens his length and the ball turns slowly into Smith. He waits for it and then works it to mid-wicket again. Things are going quite swiftly for Aussies now.
On a good length and around off at 126.5 kph. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
Fails to find the gap! Bowls it full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it along the ground to mid-wicket.
Nicely driven! A fullish delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it through covers as the fielder chases it. They take three easily.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off. Smith blocks it from his crease.
Serves it on a length, on off. Smith with a solid block from his crease again.
Just short of good length and outside off. Smith leaves it in his own unusual way.
WIDE! Starts off with a very short delivery. Way too high and Marnus Labuschagne makes room only to leave it alone. The keeper collects it and the umpires calls it wide.
Shortish delivery and angling into body. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it backward square leg.
Bangs it short and around leg again from 'round the wicket. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Bowls it way too short again as Smith sees it going over his head. Joshua Da Silva fails to stop it completely but gets a glove on it. The ball rolls behind him and a bye is taken.
Bangs it short and down the leg side. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.

SIX! This time all the way for a maximum! First of this Test match! Joseph continues to bowl it short, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne gets inside the line of the ball and hooks it over fine leg for a maximum.
Shortish delivery, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne pullls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
A fullish delivery down the leg side. Marnus Labuschagne tries to flick it but misses.
On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
Holder serves a fullish delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it to the cover fielder this time.
Shortish delivery and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne cuts it through covers. The ball does not travel all the way to the ropes but Marnus Labuschagne adds another three runs to his total.
Back of a length, on off. Smith blocks it from his crease.
On a length and angling into middle. Smith works it straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Bangs it short, around leg. Marnus Labuschagne tries to pull it but does not get any timing on it and ends up playing it to the leg slip fielder.
Another bouncer and this time Marnus Labuschagne is in better control of his pull shot as he plays it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
Joseph with another short delivery, around leg. Smith gets inside the line of the ball and lets it go.
This is good stuff from Joseph, they need to try something different here and Joseph is doing exactly that. He bangs it short and on middle. Steven Smith again sways away from the line of the ball.
WIDE! Bangs it halfway down the pitch again on middle. Smith ducks under it but the umpire reckons that it is too high and calls it wide. Joseph is not happy though.
FOUR! On the pads and it's a boundary for Smith! On a length and around leg. Smith just tucks it fine as the ball races away towards the fence.
Just short of good length this time angling into the body and Smith works it to mid-wicket.
Turning into leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to backward square leg.
Pushes it quicker and flatter on middle. Marnus Labuschagne goes deep in his crease and blocks it out.
FOUR! Good shot! Tossed up and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shimmies down the track and actually is beaten by the flight there but ends up still driving it through covers for a lovely boundary.
Touch shorter and quicker on off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it to covers. There is good healthy banter going on between Marnus Labuschagne and Joshua Da Silva.
Chase bowls it flatter and quicker on middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to mid-wicket.
Touch shorter and turning into middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne goes deep in his crease and works it to square leg for a single.
Back of a length and around off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and punches it through backward point for a couple.

Finds the edge but it is well short of the slip fielder! On a good length and around off. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward to defend it. He, however, gets a thick outside edge that falls well short of the widish first slip fielder.
Joseph lands it on a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne with a solid block this time.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls a fullish delivery that shapes back a bit into Smith. On middle and Smith defends it towards right of the bowler.
On a length, on off. Smith stays in his crease and calmly defends this one.
Bowls a full delivery on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for a single.
Touch shorter and quicker on middle. It allows Smith to go deep in his crease as he works it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on middle from 'round the wicket. Marnus Labuschagne drives it to mid on.
Touch shorter and on off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
This is a bit slower in the air and is pitched on the off stump line. Smith works it towards the leg side.

FIFTY FOR STEVEN SMITH! This has been a very fluent knock from the Australian number 4! Chase bowls it fuller and around off. Smith leans foward and drives it to sweeper cover for a single. Smith surely would be looking to convert this into a big one.
Bowls a full delivery on middle. Smith flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

Joseph bangs it short and angles it on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tries to pull it but is hurried by this short delivery and gets a top edge. The ball, however, falls in the vacant mid-wicket region and a single is taken.
A full delivery on off. Smith drives it well but straight to the mid off fielder.
Touch shorter and around off. Smith punches it to covers for a single.
Joseph tries a short delivery again, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it well but the fielder at mid-wicket stops it.
Touch shorter, around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it towards covers but fails to find the gap.
Chase bowls it a touch shorter and Smith easily defends it off the back foot.
Bowls it quicker and flatter on off. Smith with a solid block again.
Chase with a fullish delivery, around off. Smith seems to be just happy to defend at the moment.
Chase bowls it fuller on off. Smith with a solid front foot defence.
Tosses this one up and around off. Smith defends it off the front foot quite nicely again.
Fires it on middle and bit fuller too. Smith works it to mid-wicket. Good tight over from Chase this!

Almost picks up a wicket first ball. Kraigg Brathwaite comes from around the wicket and starts with a round-arm delivery angling across off. Marnus Labuschagne ends up chopping it over first slip for a single.
Around the pads, this is nudged away onto the leg side.
On the pads again and this is just worked away towards backward square leg.
Full and at the stumps, blocked out by Smith.
A touch shorter and around leg stump, this is played off the back foot towards square leg for a run.
On the shorter side and flatter, on off. Marnus Labuschagne goes back and punches it to long off for a single.
On middle and leg, flicked away onto the on side.
Flights it up now around off, Labuschagne punches it out towards cover.
Tossed up full and on middle, Labuschagne defends it out.
Loopy delivery around off stump, this is eased down to long on for a single.
Around the off stump, kept out by Steven Smith.
Tosses it up on middle, Steven Smith looks to drive it straight but hits it towards mid on and is a bit annoyed with himself.

Kemar Roach almost produces a wicket straight after taking the new ball. This is full and wide, zipping through. Labuschagne reaches out to drive but the ball beats the bat and there is an appeal for caught behind but the bat clearly hit the ground there.
Fullish length around off, Labuschagne defends it out.
On a length and pushed wider of the off stump, no shot offered by Labuschagne.
Roach goes very full and looks to attack the pads. Labuschagne looks to flick it away but gets a leading edge onto the off side.
Back of a length and outside off, Labuschagne leans back and taps it through covers for a single.
Pitches it up now around off, Steven Smith drives it firmly towards mid off.
Starts off with a gentle-paced delivery, full and well outside off. Labuschagne leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Much better now, pitched up around middle and Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.
Seales looks to go full and wide but just pushes it beyond the tramline outside off. The umpire lets him off the hook though.
On a hard length and well outside off, Steven Smith shoulders arms.

DROPPED! Tagenarine Chanderpaul almost pulls off a brilliant take in the deep on debut. Fraction shorter and well outside off. Marnus Labuschagne sees the width on offer and throws his hands at it. The ball is slashed away towards deep backward point and the man in the deep seems to pick it up a bit late. Chanderpaul does dive in but the ball falls short. A single is also taken.
Good length outside off, Steven Smith leaves it alone.

FOUR! Edged away! Fullish length around the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne just gets squares up a touch but plays at it with soft hands. The ball goes off the outside edge and runs through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Good length, around off and this one nips back in sharply. Labuschagne looks to block but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Short and wide, slapped away towards deep cover for a single.
Pitched a bit further up and around middle and leg, Smith punches it towards mid on.
FOUR! Short ball but just not short enough to trouble the batter. This is outside off and Steven Smith fetches it before muscling it away into the mid-wicket fence.

BEATEN! Kemar Roach with a beautiful comeback delivery that leaves Steven Smith bamboozled. This is served on a good length and angling in from around off. The ball straightens after pitching and Smith just spars at it. The ball zips past the outside edge into the keeper's gloves.
On a fullish length and outside off, Labuschagne makes an easy leave.
Full and trying to attack the pads but it is spilled well down the leg side.
Pitches it up now around off stump, Labuschagne defends it under his eye line.
A tad fuller and pulled wider of the off pole. Labuschagne looks to play at it but decides to leave it in the end.
Keeps it full and bowls it in the channel around off. There's just a hint of away shape on it but it is an easy enough leave for Labuschagne to make.
Pitches it up on the pads, Labuschagne defends it out. Maiden!
Length ball, well wide of the off stump, Steven Smith lets it through to the keeper.
Full and outside off, Smith opens the face of the blade and drives it square of the wicket for a single.
Pitched up around the fifth stump and shaping away, left alone by Labuschagne.
Just a fraction shorter and wide outside off, Labuschagne presses back and taps it through cover-point for a run.

Kemar Roach serves this on a good length and angles it in from the off stump. Steven Smith looks to press forward and block but misses and gets hit high on the pads. There is an hopeful appeal for lbw but it has been turned down. There hasn't been a single review throughout the day but desperate times call for desperate as Kraigg Brathwaite does go for it. UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved and Ball Tracking confirms that the ball is comfortably going over the leg stump.
Around the top of off, Smith defends this one onto the off side.
Full and around off stump, Marnus Labuschagne crouches a bit and caresses it through the cover region for a couple of runs. Good running on that occasion.

FOUR! A valiant effort in the deep but it goes in vain. This is on a good length but well outside off. Labuschagne uses the width on offer and slaps it away behind point. Tagenarine Chanderpaul runs to his left from deep point and puts in the dive but is unable to prevent the boundary. Labuschagne moves on to 149 now.

150 up for Marnus Labuschagne and it is the fourth time he has surpassed this score in Test matches. This is pitched up outside off, Labuschagne with another cover drive and he gets back for two with ease. This has been a sublime knock so far from him.
On a good length and around off, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Good length again but a bit wider and Labuschagne taps it through cover-point to pick up a single.
A bit fuller and tighter around the off stump. Steven Smith watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.
Kyle Mayers comes back into the attack and serves a yorker-length delivery around middle. Labuschagne jams it out towards short mid-wicket.
This is very full again but a lot wider, Labuschagne plays it late and with an angled bat past point for a single.
Good length angling down leg. Steven Smith shuffles across and shoulders arms at it.
Fuller in length but well outside off, easy leave for Smith.
Mayers goes wider of the crease and angles it in a long way from well outside off. Steven Smith stays back and keeps it out.
Around the top of off, this is defended off the back foot.

JAFFA! No idea what happened there! Jason Holder starts off with a good-length delivery that is angled into off stump. Labuschagne looks to block but the ball just seams away off the deck and goes past the shoulder of the blade. Labuschagne smiles as he knows the delivery was too good but Jason Holder is left frustrated.
Pitches it up now on off stump and this is solidly blocked off by Labuschagne.
Good length outside off, this is guided away through backward point for a single.
Angles this one into the stumps, Steven Smith blocks it out.
Good length around off, Steven Smith leaves it alone.

An inside edge to end Day 1! This is full and angled into leg stump, Steven Smith shuffle across a bit and gets an inside edge down to fine leg for a single. The umpires call for Stumps as Australia finish the Day with 293/2!
Roach starts off with a short and wide delivery outside off. Smith cuts it through covers for a couple. Good positive start for Smith.
Shorter in length again and outside off. Smith tries to punch it this time but gets an inside edge that goes just past the stumps.
Tad shorter again by Roach angling into middle. Smith works it towards the leg side.
Gets his length bit fuller this time. On a good length and outside off. Smith decides to leave it alone.
Roach has not found his length so far. He bowls it on a shortish length again and outside off. Smith lets it go again.

Finally bowls it fuller but ends up drifting on the pads. Smith is ready for it as he flicks it through mid-wicket and the batters run four. Very good running and this is a nice positive start from the Aussies.
Holder starts off with a fullish delivery on off at 124 kph. Marnus Labuschagne defends it with soft hands towards the off side and takes his first run of the day. 300 up for Australia!
He drifts it way down the leg side this time. Smith first sets up to flick it but then decides to let it go.
On a length, on off. Smith with a solid block now.
Lands it on a good length at a gentle pace again. Smith makes an easy leave. Not much swing so far for the Windies.
Touch short of good length and on off. Smith defends it right under his eyes.
Back of a length and outside off. Smith resists the temptation to go at a widish delivery and lets it go. So, just one run from Holder's first over of the day.

Now he finds that channel! Lands it on a good length, around off, angles it into the batter. Marnus Labuschagne is neither back or forward and ends up getting an inside edge onto his pads as he looks to defend it.
A fullish delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it back to the bowler.
Touch on the shorter side, around off. Marnus Labuschagne dabs it to backward point for an easy single. The partnership between these two besties is now 150!
Back of a length, on off. Good bounce for Roach as the ball hits the higher part of Smith's blade as he tries to defend it. The ball rolls towards the off side and a single is taken.
Roach bangs it short and not much pace on this delivery. On off and Marnus Labuschagne pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Serves it on a length, on off at 126 clicks and Smith defends it nicely showing a full face of his blade.
Holder with a good-length delivery, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
A fullish delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it. However, he gets the inside half of his blade to fine leg for a single.
Touch shorter and outside off. Smith rides the bounce and punches it to deep point where Tagenarine Chanderpaul does well to keep it to just a single.
That's a good one! Bowls a bouncer, around leg. Good bounce and zip on this delivery as Marnus Labuschagne fails to get any bat on his hook shot.
Holder bangs it short again on middle. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it quite well this time and takes three as the ball goes towards the deep square leg region before the fielder cuts it off.
Serves it on a good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it from his crease. Roach needs to be consistent with this line and length.
Yet again after bowling a good delivery, he drifts on the pads. A fullish delivery and Marnus Labuschagne easily flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Angling into middle on off. Roach went wider of the crease there and Smith defends it to mid on.
Serves a fullish delivery on off. Smith with a solid block here.
Overpitched delivery on off. Smith times his straight drive quite well. However, Roach is alert and stops it with his right hand.
Beautiful delivery! Lands this in that corridor of uncertainity and Smith gets beaten as he tries to defend it.
On a good length and around off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to block it off his front foot. However, the ball straightens a bit after pitching and beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne makes an easy leave this time.
Lands a good length delivery again, around off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go again.
Shortish and wider outside off. Easy leave for Marnus Labuschagne this time.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to deep square leg for an easy single.

Back of a length, on off at 124.5 kph. Smith blocks it onto the turf. Aussie batters have looked pretty comfortable so far as West Indies have neither got their lines and lengths right nor any great movement off the turf or in air.
WIDE! Bowls a fullish and widish delivery way outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.

FOUR! Oh, just past the stumps! Shortish delivery and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to pull it. However, the ball goes off the inside edge and just past the stumps towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
On the shorter side and on off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it off the inside half of his blade to deep backward square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Smith lets it go.
On a good length again and this time a bit closer to the off stump. Smith goes forward to defend it but the ball seams away a touch and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Good shape into the batter. A fullish delivery swinging into off. Smith fends it towards the leg side.
On a good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.

FOUR! In the gap and Marnus Labuschagne gets another boundary! A shortsih delivery that nips back on on off. It cramps Marnus Labuschagne for room and he just tries to guide it towards the off side. Gets a bit of outside edge that goes in the gap wide of the diving first slip fielder for a boundary.
On a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Goes fuller and on middle. Smith flicks it well in front of square and takes three runs. Good running again.
Shortish delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it to square leg. Bonner half-stops it and a single is taken.
Bangs it short and angles it into middle and leg. Smith ducks under it.
Good-length delivery, around off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
Lands it on a length again and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne stays patient and lets it go.
Mayers hits that good length again, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it solidly from his crease.
On the shorter side, around off. Marnus Labuschagne dabs it towards the off side for a single.
Back of a length and angling into leg. Smith tries to flick it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Lands it on a length and outside off. Smith watches it till the end and lets it go.

In the air...but safe! Holder bangs it short on off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to pull it off the front foot. He, however, gets a top edge this time that goes aerially but falls well short of the deep square leg fielder. Single taken.
Bangs it short and around leg. Smith leaves it alone.

That's an easy single, you don't want to give these singles away easily. On a length, on middle. Smith works it behind square on the leg side and takes a single as the fielder there is bit slow to approach that ball.
Shortish delivery and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne cuts it to deep point for a single.
On a length and around leg. Smith tries to leave it and gets hit high on the pads.
Holder angles a length delivery on off. Smith is as calm as ever and defends it right of the bowler.
On a hard length and outside off, Labuschagne just nudges it down with soft hands behind point and picks up a single.
Good length, trying to angle it in from outside off. Steven Smith puts a big stride forward and looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
WIDE! This is banged in halfway down the track and over leg stump. The ball goes well over the batter's head and a wide is called.
Another easy single. Good length, around off, eased away towards the vacant backward point region for a run.

A strong shout of 'no' from Steven Smith. Fullish delivery, around off stump and almost reversing into the batter. Labuschagne gets an inside edge towards square leg and looks for one but is sent back.
Fuller in length around off and swinging back into the batter. Labuschagne just pushes it towards mid on.
Length ball angling into middle ane leg, this is worked away onto the leg side.
Drop and run! Good length around off stump, Steven Smith just dabs it down towards silly point and races through for the single.
Goes full and keeps the line around off. Labuschagne defends it under his eye line.
Just a fraction shorter and around off, this one nips back in a touch as well. Labuschagne taps it towards cover-point for one more.
Length ball, angling it in from around the top of off stump, Smith solidly keeps it out.
This is full and outside off, trying to induce the drive but Smith leaves it alone.
Fullish length around the pads, this is flicked away 'round the corner for a single.
Good length, on the fifth stump line. The ball just straightens a bit and Steven Smith edges it down with soft hands towards second slip.

They run four and not for the first time it has happened in this innings either. Fuller and around off, Smith opens the face of the bat and drives it square through the point region. Jayden Seales chases it down and the ball just slows down before Seales picks it up but it will be four runs.
Around the top of off, Smith blocks it out.
Banged in short and over the stumps, Smith just ducks under it.
A touch fuller and angling into the pads, Smith keeps it out on the leg side.
Length ball around off, Steven Smith shuffles across the off stump and works it away through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and straight, Smith flicks it down to fine leg and turns the strike over.
Length ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to play away from the body but the ball keeps a bit low and beats the outside edge.
This is angled into middle and leg, Labuschagne just nudges it towards short mid-wicket.
Back of a length and close to the off pole. Labuschagne looks to punch off the back foot but gets an inside edge that goes past the stumps and towards short fine leg. They pick up a single.
Lovely bowling! Roach goes a bit fuller and angles it in from around off. The ball straightens after pitching and zips past the outside edge of Smith's willow.
Good length around off, just seaming away a touch but Smith is able to defend it out.
Alzarri Joseph starts a new spell with a bit of a loosener. This is short and wide, cut away to deep point for a single by Labuschagne.
Pitches it up now in that channel around off and Steven Smith lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Nicely done! Short and a bit wide again from Joseph. Steven Smith rocks back and just dabs it past the slip cordon and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Good length on off stump, Smith shuffles across and works it away through mid-wicket for a single.
On the shorter side yet again and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne opens the face of the bat and guides it to the left of the man at third man for a couple of runs.
Goes a bit fuller and just tightens the line around off stump, Labuschagne doesn't play at it.

Full and on the pads, Steven Smith uses his wrists and whips it through the vacant spaces around mid-wicket and picks up three more runs. A no ball is also called as Kemar Roach has overstepped. The 200-run stand between these two is up and neither batter is showing any signs of slowing down.
Pitches it up now around middle, Labuschagne defends it from inside his crease.
Full and straight, this is punched firmly back past the fielder but straight to the man at mid off.
Good fielding. Full again and on the pads, flicked away to the right of the man at mid-wicket who makes a good stop. They do take the single though.
Fullish length around off, Steven Smith leaves it alone.
Keeps it on a fuller length but pushes it wide of the off stump, Smith shoulders arms at it.
Good length over middle stump and blocked out towards short mid-wicket.
Chase starts off with a quicker one on middle and leg, Labuschagne backs away and pushes it towards cover for a quick single.
Floated up and turning down leg, Smith just nudges it behind square on the leg side and rotates the strike.
Tossed up around middle, Labuschagne advances but then has to adjust and keep it out.
Flatter one around middle and this one keeps low. Labuschagne backs away and forces it down to long off for a single.
Flighted delivery, Steven Smith works it towards mid-wicket.
Nicely tossed up, on middle and leg, Smith presents the full face of the bat and pushes it towards mid on.
Back of a length and around off, this is dabbed down towards backward point.
Fullish delivery outside off and shaping away, Labuschagne watches it go past him and through to the keeper.

FOUR! Short and wide, Marnus Labuschagne throws his hands at it and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies away just out of reach of the jumping man at gully and into the third man fence. Alzarri Joseph doesn't seem impressed with that effort.
Length ball around off, Labuschagne defends it out.
Joseph bowls it full and closer to the off pole at 137.4 clicks but Labuschagne makes an assured leave.
Nice shape on that one. This is very full and on off stump, shaping away as well, Labuschagne manages to keep it out.
This is floated up on the pads, Smith nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Flighted, around middle and Steven Smith just defends it out.
Tossed up full and outside off, Steven Smith drives it through covers towards the sweeper and picks up a single.
On a length and on off stump, Labuschagne backs away and plays it straight towards the cover region.
Slows it up a touch and bowls it on middle, Labuschagne just blocks it out.

Aerial but lands well short! Roston Chase gives it a nice loop and bowls it around middle. Marnus Labuschagne dances down the track and gets beaten in the flight and ends up dragging the big shot towards deep square leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul is over there but the ball lands short of him and they get a single.
This is banged in short over middle and leg and at a good height as well. Marnus Labuschagne goes after it and mistimes the hook shot towards deep square leg for one.
Short again, over middle and Smith pulls it through wide mid on for a single.
Good length around off, Labuschagne watches it closely and leaves it alone.
Good length around the top of off and at almost 141 clicks. Labuschagne gets right behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Hits the length hard does Joseph and bowls it around the hips. Labuschagne just drops it towards mid-wicket and picks up a run.
Good length and at the stumps, Smith pushes it towards wide mid on for yet another comfortable single.
Chase bowls it full and on the pads. Smith works it to mid-wicket.
Shortish length and around off. Smith punches it through backward point for a single.
On the shorter side again, around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it through covers for a single.
FOUR! Smith moves to 97 now! Chase bowls it on middle. Smith reaches the pitch of the ball and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Turning into middle and leg. Smith works it towards the leg side.
Tossed up on middle. Smith drives it off the inside half of his blade to long on for a single. Smith will retain the strike!
On a good length and outside off. Smith lets it go with ease.
