NO BALL!  Abit fullish delivery, outside off. Smith resists the temptation to drive it and lets it go. A  No Ball is called for overstepping.
On a length and around off. Smith guides it towards the gully fielder.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Smith with a solid block. The wait continues as the crowd gets excited.
Alzarri Joseph goes wide of the crease and angles it on middle and leg. A length delivery and Smith works it past square leg for a single.
Lovely delivery! Lands on a good length and outside off. The ball straightens a bit after pitching and beats the putside edge of Marnus Labuschagne's blade as he tries to defend it.
On a good length and around off. The ball nips back in and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it as the ball goes very close past the off stump.
Tossed up, on middle. Smith works it to square leg.
A solid block! Tossed up on middle. Smith blocks it off the front foot.

Here it is....29th Test century for Steven Smith! He equals Don Bradman's record of 29 centuries and raises his bat as his wife in the balcony applauds his effort along with his teammates and this crowd at the Optus stadium. This is a fuller delivery on middle. Smith drives it to long on for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it out.
Turning into leg and fuller in length too. Marnus Labuschagne tries to tuck it towards the leg side. He gets a faint part of his blade and keeper moves to his left but fails to catch it.
Touch shorter and around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it through point for a couple.
Lands a length delivery on middle. Smith works it towards the leg side.
Angles a length delivery on the pads. Smith tucks it to fine leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Joseph bowls it a tad short, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it from his crease.
A length delivery on off. That bounces sharply and hits high on Marnus Labuschagne's blade as he defends it.
On the shorter side, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to mid-wicket.
Good use of the wrists! Tossed up on middle. Smith reaches the pitch of the ball and works it past the diving fielder at widish mid on and takes two runs.
Fuller and on the leg. Smith clips it to square leg for a single.
Touch shorter on off. Marnus Labuschagne goes back and punches it to covers for a single.
Flatter and quicker on middle. Smith blocks it out.
On the shorter side, around off. Smith tries to cut it but gets an inside edge that rolls towards the leg side.
Shortish delivery again and outside off. Smith cuts it to deep point for a single.
Back of a length, on middle. Smith fends it calmly towards the leg side.
Short and wide outside off. Smith cuts it to deep cover for a couple. Nothing happening for the West Indies bowlers at the moment.
Shortish length again, around off. Smith first sets up to pull it but then checks his shot and just blocks it.
On a length, on off. Smith with a solid block again.
Seales again pulls his length back, around off. Smith punches it to deep backward point for a single.
Keeps it on the shorter side, on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it right under his eyes.
Shortish length and around off. Smith chops it to deep backward point for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Marnus Labuschagne skips down the track and pushes it to long on for a single.
Bit quicker and turning into leg. Smith just works it to the leg side.
FOUR! Poor delivery and punished! Short delivery and outside off. Smith rocks back and cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Fires it flatter and quicker on off. Smith fends it off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up delivery on off. Smith gets a good stride forward and defends it.
Takes a single and moves to 199! A fullish delivery, around off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it left of mid off for a single.
Short and outside off. Smith cuts it to deep point for a single.
Seales bowls a fullish delivery and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne resists the temptation to drive and leaves it.
Seales again bowls it full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne gets to his double century in style! What a player this man is turning out to be! The hunger for runs is just amazing and he just continues to grow in stature. Seales a bowls an overpitched delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and drives it crisply through covers for a lovely boundary. Takes off his helmet and soaks in the applause from this healthy crowd here at the Optus stadium.
On the shorter side and around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it through point for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Oh, what an anti-climax! Marnus Labuschagne departs just at the stroke of Lunch and that ends a marathon knock from a fantastic cricketer. Kraigg Brathwaite brings himself on and fires a flatter and touch shorter delivery, around off from 'round the wicket. Marnus Labuschagne goes back and tries to steer it square off the wicket on the off side. However, the ball bounces a touch more and takes an outside edge of his blade and Joshua Da Silva behind the stumps takes a sharp catch. Marnus Labuschagne is disappointed and it will be Lunch on Day 2! Marnus Labuschagne gets a standing ovation and Australia are 402 for 3 at Lunch on Day 2!
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kraigg Brathwaite

Commentary: This is full and fired in on middle. Travis Head pushes it back to the bowler.
Head is off the mark! Drops it a tad short and on the pads, Head works it away through square leg for a single.
Goes full again and angles it across Steven Smith who presses forward to defend.
Easy single on offer. Around middle, nudged away towards square leg for a quick run.
Flatter delivery around off, Travis Head backs away and eases it through cover-point for one more.
FOUR! A poor delivery to start with from Jayden Seales. Seales comes from 'round the wicket and angles it into the pads, Head just tucks it away through backward square leg and picks up a boundary.
FOUR! Seales is not happy with himself and rightly so. A tad short but way too wide and Travis Head just cuts it away past point to pick up back-to-back boundaries.
Much better this time around. Back of a length and closer to the off pole, Head goes on the back foot to defend.
Pitches it up now in that channel around off, Head shoulders arms at it.
Good length and good channel around the off stump, Head watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.
Good length around off, Travis Head presses back and punches it square of the wicket towards deep point for one.
A round-arm delivery from Kraigg Brathwaite and this is just fired into the off stump. Travis Head does well to keep it out.
Angling into middle and leg, Head eases it down to long on for a single.
A bit fuller and on off stump, Steven Smith blocks it out.
Drags back the length and angles it across the right-hander. Smith goes on the back foot and guides it away through short third man for a couple of runs.
Two more! Tossed up full and on the pads, Steven Smith whips it in front of mid-wicket and comes back for the second with ease.
Around the pads, Smith plays it out with soft hands onto the leg side.
Play and a miss! This is fuller and outside off, angling in as well. Travis Head looks for the expansive drive but misses and gets beaten on the inside edge.
Fraction shorter and outside off, Head slaps it away in front of point and picks up a single.
Seales bowls this one fuller and outside off, Steven Smith just lets it through to the keeper.
On a hard length and on off stump, Smith blocks it out without any fuss.
Back of a length and around off, Smith defends it out with a dead bat.
Back of a length and over middle stump, Steven Smith hops and works it away past square leg for a couple of runs.
On a length and around off, Head punches it out toward the cover region.
Tossed up, full and around off, this is knocked down to long off for a single.
A hint of flight this time, bowled around off. Steven Smith gets inside the line of the ball and paddles it 'round the corner for one.
Around middle and leg, kept out by Head.
A tad bit short and around the pads, this is flicked away towards mid-wicket.
Drifted into middle and leg, kept out by Travis Head.
Just short of good length and on off. Smith blocks it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side, around off. Smith pushes it to the short cover fielder.
A length delivery again, on off. Smith defends it towards the off side.
A fullish delivery that is angled into off. Smith with a solid block off the front foot.
Shortish length and around off. Smith rides the bounce and punches it to deep point for a single.
Back of a length, angling into off from 'round the wicket. Head works it towards the leg side with the angle for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Head drives it firmly to long off for a single.
Pushes it quicker on off from 'round the wicket. Smith blocks it.
Touch shorter and on off. Smith punches it to long off for a single.
Nicely tosssed up again, on off. Head drives it to long off for a single.
Floated up around the pads, Smith flicks it towards square leg.
Loopy delivery, full and around leg stump, this is eased away towards mid on.
This is pitched up around off, Travis Head stands tall and drives it firmly but straight to mid off.
An attempted yorker on off stump turns out to be a full toss. Travis Head hangs back and just opens the face of the bat to guide it past backward point for a couple of runs.
Back of a length on off stump, Head hops back and keeps it down towards cover-point for a quick single.
Good length, close to the off pole and Smith just solidly blocks it out.
Hard length from Seales, keeps it around the off stump and the ball seams back in off the deck. Steven Smith gets pushed onto the back foot but manages to push it out on the off side.
WIDE! Banged in halfway down the track, around off and the ball just flies over the batter's head. A wide is called.
Good length, around off and this is defended out in front of the man at short cover.
Floated up around middle and leg, Travis Head pushes at it gently and is able to get it past the man at silly mid off for a single.
Drops it shorter and around middle, Smith works it off the back foot towards backward square leg.
Tossed up, on a length and around off, Steven Smith presses forward to defend.
Flighted delivery, a tad fuller and angling across the batter, Smith strides forward to defend.
Slower and shorter around leg stump, Steven Smith has enough time to go deep in his crease and glance it behind square on the leg side for a brace.
Tosses it up a bit and bowls it on middle, Steven Smith defends it off the front foot.
Shorter and angled at the body, Travis Head tries to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball goes off his hips and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
A touch fuller this time and bowled around off, Steven Smith defends it back onto the deck.
Around the top of off, this one just skids through and Steven Smith does well to keep it out.
FOUR! Driven and driven well enough. This is overpitched around off stump, Steven Smith plays a high-elbow cover drive and pierces the gap to find the fence.
Length ball outside off, Smith lets this one through to the keeper.
Good length around off, just pushing the batter back a bit. Steven Smith solidly keeps it out on the off side.
A bit of a round-arm action and it is bowled very full on middle, Travis Head drives it down to long on and rotates the strike.
Flatter one, slanted across the off stump, Steven Smith punches it off the back foot and through covers for a single.
Tossed up on off stump, Head pushes it out.
Holds it back a touch and flights it around off stump, Travis Head caresses it towards extra cover.
Tossed up, full and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Shortens the length and bowls it outside off, Travis Head waits for it and cuts it through point for a run.
Starts with a back-of-a-length delivery around the hips. This is tucked away past square leg for an easy single.
Holder stays 'round the wicket to the right-hander as well. He angles it full and well across the right-hander. Steven Smith doesn't play at it.

Uppish but in the gap! This is full and wide again, this time Steven Smith does go after it and ends up playing it aerially off the toe end of the bat. The ball goes over the cover region and Smith gets two.
Excellent stop from Tagenarine Chanderpaul. This is in the slot and around off, Steven Smith drives it firmly and to the right of the man at extra cover but it is well stopped.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! This is around off, Steven Smith takes a step across the off stump and drills it straight back past the bowler and into the long off fence.
This is on a shorter length and outside off, Steven Smith guides it off the back foot and to the right of the man at third man for a couple of runs.
FOUR! A half-tracker from Kraigg Brathwaite and it is punished! Short and outside off. Head rocks back and slaps it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR BYES! Fires it down the leg side. Head tries to clip it but misses. The keeper misses it too and the ball races away towards the fine leg fence.
Flatter and quicker again on middle. Head works it to mid-wicket.
Pushes it on middle and leg. Head works it towards the leg side.
NO BALL! Kraigg Brathwaite oversteps now! Angles a flatter delivery on middle and leg. Head tries to work it towards the leg side but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
A flatter delivery on middle. Head pushes it towards mid on.
Shorter and on off. Head goes back and punches it back to the bowler.
Holder bowls it short and on off. Smith pulls it through mid-wicket and takes three as the fielder makes a good diving stop near the ropes.
FOUR! Runs are flowing pretty quickly now! Short and outside off. Head cuts it through point for a boundary. That was hit very hard.
Shortish length again and it is outside off. Head tries to cut it again but misses this time.
Holder keeps it on the shorter side, on off. Head rides the bounce and dabs it towards the off side for a single.
A length delivery on middle by Holder. Smith works it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Head is not going to shy away from playing his shots! Bangs it short and angles it on middle and leg. Head tries to pull it but gets a top edge that runs away towards the fine leg fence.
Back of a length, on off. Smith blocks it onto the tuf.
On the shorter side again, on off. Smith stays in his crease and dabs it towards the off side with soft hands.
On a good length and around off. Smith leaves it alone.
On a good length, around off. Smith tries to defend it but gets a thick outside edge. Jermaine Blackwood at first slip dives to his right and stops it off the bounce.
On the shorter side angling into middle. Smith works it to mid-wicket.
Hits that hard length again, on off. Smith is as calm as ever and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Head drives it to long off for a single.
Chase tosses it up, on off. Smith knocks it down to long on for a single.
Pushes it quicker on off. Head tries to drive it but hits it off the inside half of his blade back to the bowler.
A fuller delivery on leg. Head sweeps but straight to backward point.

NOT OUT! Tossed up on middle from 'round the wicket. Head goes for a big sweep shot but misses. The ball hits his pads and Chase makes a loud appeal. However, the umpire turns it down. It looks close to the naked eye and Kraigg Brathwaite goes for the DRS. The replays roll and the UltraEdge shows no bat there. Then, the Ball Tracking rolls and it shows that the ball is going over the middle pole. So, the original decision will stay and Head will continue.
Touch shorter and on off. Head goes back and punches it to covers for a single.
Back of a length and outside off. Angled across the batter nicely and Head lets it go.
On the shorter side and around off. Head rides the bounce and dabs it to backward point for a single.
On a length and on off. Smith defends it towards the leg side.
Bowls a full delivery on off. Smith drives it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side, on middle. Smith works it towards deep backward square leg for a couple.
Joseph keeps it a touch shorter and outside off. Smith leaves it alone.
Tossed up on middle. Head drives it to long on for a single.
Pushes quicker and on off. Smith blocks it out solidly.
Bowls another fullish delivery on off. Smith reaches the pitch of the ball and works it to long on for a single.
Loopy delivery on off. Head drives it firmly to long off for a single.
Turnning into middle and leg. Bit flatter and Smith works it towards square leg.
On the shorter side, on middle. Smith goes back and punches it to mid on.
Back of a length and angles it on middle and leg. head works it to fine leg for a single.
A good-length delivery on off. Smith tries to defend it but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and the ball rolls towards the gully region.
Touch shorter and around off. Smith punches it gently to covers for a single.
Good pacy bouncer this! Jospeh fires a bouncer on off. It zips off the surface and Head ducks under it.
A full delivery on the pads. Head clips it through mid-wicket nicely hut Holder does well to stop it inside the playing area. Three taken.
A flatter delivery on off. Smith plays it back to the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Travis Head leans forward and drives it through mid off for a single.
Nicely flighted, around off and Steven Smith just eases it towards mid on.
Looped up, full and on off stump, Smith flicks it away but the fielder at short mid-wicket makes a good stop.
Slower through the air and bowled around middle, Smith nudges it onto the leg side.
Floated up on the stumps, Smith just blocks it out.
Shortish length and outside off. Smith cuts it to deep backward point for a single.
Joseph bowls it on a fullish length, on off at 138.2 kph. Smith drives it off the inside half of his blade towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! 150 up for Steven Smith! He is back at his best now! He has looked in total control right throughout this knock and is looking good for many more. A fullish delivery on the pads this time. Smith leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Smith dabs it to point for a single.
On the shorter side, on off. Head rides the bounce and fends it towards the off side for a single.
Good bouncer by Joseph! Angles this short delivery into the body at a good height and Smith also does well to sway away from the line of the ball.
FOUR! That's a shot of a man in form! Joseph keeps it short again, bit of room this time. Smith waits for it and just guides it over the slip fielders for a boundary.

Nice turn and bounce there! Tossed up and outside off. Head goes for a big wild slog-sweep but misses as the ball turns away from him sharply. The keeper fails to collect it cleanly and the batters take three byes as the ball goes towards the third man region.
Touch shorter and on middle. Smith works it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
A flatter delivery on off. Smith blocks it out.
Fuller delivery on off. Smith works it to mid-wicket this time.
FOUR! Nice placement! A shortish delivery and outside off. Smith stays deep in his crease and slaps it through the extra-cover region for a boundary.
Chase keeps his length a bit short again, turning into middle. Smith works it to mid-wicket.
Kemar Roach comes back into the attack and starts with a length ball that is angled into the pads from around the wicket. Travis Head works it 'round the corner for a single.
Back to over the wicket now for the right-hander. This is full and trying to shape it in from well outside off, Smith leaves it alone.

A bit of aggression now from Steven Smith but he mistimes it badly. This is short and outside off, Smith advances and looks to force the big shot square on the off side but gets a top edge over the cover region for a single.
Good length, around middle and this is just blocked out by Head.
Cut away and that will be FIFTY for Travis Head and he's got there pretty quickly as well. Short of a length and outside off, Head presses back and cuts it through point for a single.
Back of a length and around off, Steven Smith stays on the back foot and just dabs it down to backward point.
Quicker and shorter, close to the off stump, Travis Head chops it in front of covers and picks up a quick run.
Nicely drifted onto middle and leg, Smith drives it straight towards mid on.
Pushed through quicker and on a nagging length around off, Steven Smith defends it off the front foot.
Flighted, well outside off and turning in a bit. Smith waits for it and plays it with an angled bat through the vacant slip cordon for a single.
On the shorter side and around off, Travis Head rocks back and punches it through extra cover for a couple of runs.
Tossed up around middle, Travis Head looks for the slog sweep but ends up heaving it through wide mid on for a brace.
This is full and well outside off, Smith leans on and drives it through covers for a run.
Roach comes from around the wicket and angles in a very full ball on off stump. Head plays it towards mid off.
On a length but angling onto the pads, this is worked away behind square on the leg side for a single.

More signs of aggression from Steven Smith. Good length around off, Smith opens up his arms and looks to smash it over wide mid on but mistimes it. The ball clears mid on but it will only be a couple of runs.
Length again around off, this is eased away through covers for a run.
FOUR! Nicely done by Travis Head. This is banged in halfway down the track and outside off, Head hops up and just ramps it over short third man for a boundary.
Short of a length and angling into off stump, this is punched down to long on for one.

Was there an edge on it? No, it is given as byes. This is quicker and flatter, close to the off stump. Travis Head looks to cut it late but gets beaten on the outside edge. The keeper fumbles as well and the batters get a bye.
Shorter and around leg stump, this is turned off the back foot through backward square leg for a run.
A low full toss now on leg stump, Head knocks it down to long on and turns the strike over.
Chase spears one into the middle stump but Steven Smith is able to jam it out.

Another good effort in the deep by Tagenarine Chanderpaul. This is full and around off, Steven Smith drives it through extra cover. Chanderpaul runs to his left from long off and dives in to make the stop. Three runs are taken.
Kraigg Brathwaite brings himself back on and starts with a flighted delivery around off. Steven Smith wrists it through mid-wicket for a single.
This is quicker and darted into the leg stump, Travis Head backs away and hits it through mid off for a run.
Slower and shorter around the leg stump, Steven Smith works it in front of the square on the leg side and looks for two but has to settle for the single.
FOUR! Immaculate placement from Travis Head. Quicker and flatter, Head rocks back and punches it in front of covers for a boundary.
Flatter again and angling into leg stump, Head forces it through mid on for one.

FOUR! Edgy boundary but Steven Smith and Australia won't mind it one bit. This is angled across the off stump quicker and on a shorter length as well. Smith looks to punch it off the back foot but gets an outside edge that runs away into the third man fence.
A full toss now around middle, Head heaves it past the diving man at wide mid on for a single.
Slows it up a touch and shortens the length as well. Smith waits for it and just drops it onto the leg side for one more.

FOUR! Poor effort in the deep from Kemar Roach. Chase tosses it up well wide of the off stump. Travis Head has to reach for it but he is able to generate good power on the cut shot. This is hit well in front of the square on the off side and Roach runs around from deep cover but fails to stop it with his boot.
A tad bit short and on middle and leg, Head works it off the back foot towards mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted delivery around off, this is just eased through covers for one.
Gives it a nice loop and bowls it well outside off. Travis Head presses forward but leaves it alone.
On a good length and angled across the off stump, Steven Smith stays deep and just punches it through mid off for a single.

FOUR! A real long hop from Kraigg Brathwaite and it is duly punished. This is slower and served around leg stump. Head pulls it off the back foot and in between the fielders at fine leg and deep square leg for a boundary. Head is now scoring at run-a-ball.
Full and straight, drilled down to long on for a single.
Floated up on the pads, Steven Smith whips it through mid-wicket and races back for the second. Excellent running.
Slightly flighted around off, Smith pushes it towards silly mid off.
Around the pads, this is nudged away towards mid-wicket for a single.
This is drifted down the leg side and Smith leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Nicely drifted from around off stump, Smith leans on and pushes it back to the bowler.
This is full and on off stump, driven down to long on for a single.
This is full and angled in at the toes, Travis Head flicks it away through square leg for one more.
A nice and juicy full toss on off stump, trying to induce a big shot from the batter. Steven Smith just knocks it along the ground and to long on for a single.
Another low full toss around off, Travis Head hits it through mid on for a run and that will be Tea on Day 2. Australia are 568/3!
FOUR! Head starts off the session with a boundary! Shorter and angling on the pads. Head tucks it fine and the ball races away towards the fence for a boundary.
On the shorter side, on off. Head punches it to long off for a single.
Flatter and quicker one on off. Smith tries to punch it but gets beaten.
A flatter delivery on middle. Smith works it towards the leg side.
Touch shorter on middle. Smith works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Head works it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Poor delivery and punished! This is a full delivery on leg. Head paddles it towards the fine leg fence for another boundary.
Tossed up on off. Head drives it to long on for a single.
Shorter and down the leg side. Smith tries to clip it away but misses.
Angles it on the pads again. Smith works it to square leg for a single.
Bowls almost a yorker, on off. Head digs it out back to the bowler.
Oh, a full toss angling into the body. Head is surprised by this delivery but manages to work it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Head knocks it down to long on for a single.
Bowls it full and on middle. Smith works it to deep square leg for a single.
On the shorter side and angling into middle. Head goes deep in his crease and knocks it in the gap towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
A fuller delivery, around off. Head drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
On the shorter side, on off. Smith just lifts it over the bowler's head with a straight blade and comes back for the second run.
Angles it on the pads and it is bit quicker. Smith works it to square leg for a single.
Touch shorter and outside off. Smith cuts it to backward point for a single.
Short and outside off. Head cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Fires it quicker and outside off. Smith cuts it to deep point for an easy single again. This is just poor bowling, Windies are making way too easy for these Australian batters.
Fires it full and down the leg side. Head clips it to short fine leg and Smith looks for a single but is sent back.
Tossed up, on off. Head drives it to long off for a single.
Smith calls for the second run straightaway and gets two! Touch shorter and around off. Smith waits for it and just works it towards wide of long on for a couple. Smith moves to 199!
Tossed up, on middle. Head shimmies down the track and knocks it to long on for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Smith works it to mid-wicket and fails to find the gap.

Gets to his double-hundred now! What a fantastic flawless knock this has been! Takes off his helmet and soaks in the applause from his teammates and this healthy crowd here at the Optus Stadium. A shortish delivery, around off. Smith chops it to backward point and takes a single that takes him to his fourth double-hundred in Test cricket.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Oh, tragedy here for Travis Head! He is gone on 99 and Australia have declared. A shortish delivery by Kraigg Brathwaite that is pushed quicker as well and around off. Head tries to late-cut it but gets an inside edge that goes onto knock over the stumps. He would be disappointed but it has been a superb knock from the South Australian. Australia declare at 598/4!
Howout: b Kraigg Brathwaite

Commentary: Starc starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. It is at 143 clicks and Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it.
Shortish length again but this time the line is straighter. On the body and Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce to block it onto the turf.

A fullish delivery shaping into off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot and the batters take a quick single as the ball rolls towards the off side where Marnus Labuschagne at covers fails to collect the ball cleanly.

FOUR! Tagenarine Chanderpaul is underway with a boundary in Test cricket! Starc squares him up here though. Lands it just short of good length and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul tries to  defend it but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and goes past the gully fielder for a boundary.
A thick outside edge again! Back of a length and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it with soft hands as the ball goes off the thick edge towards gully.
Starc goes for a yorker, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul though manages to get his bat down in time. Exciting first over from Starc!
Starts off with a fullish delivery, outside off. It swings away from the batter and Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go.
Lands it on a good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is solid in his defence this time.
Nice! A good-length delivery, around off. The ball zips off the surface as Kraigg Brathwaite decides to leave it alone.
Jermaine Blackwood is always around that off stump. He lands it on off again and the ball seams away quite sharply as Kraigg Brathwaite keeps his bat inside the line of the ball.
Hits the good length again, bit outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Angles a length delivery on middle this time. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the leg side.
Good carry and movement here! Lands it on a good length and outside off. The ball shapes away nicely as Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go.
Goes a bit closer to the off stump now. On a good length and just around off.  it shapes away again and Tagenarine Chanderpaul is aware of it as he keeps his bat inside the line of the ball.

A big appeal for an LBW but the umpire turns it down! Pat Cummins takes a late review. The replays roll in and Snicko shows no bat invloved. The Ball Tracking rolls and it shows that the it is umpire's call on wicket's hitting. So, the original decision stays. Coming to the delivery, this lands on a good length, on off. The ball seams away a bit and Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend. The ball hits his pads but in the end he is safe now.
On a good length again, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it nicely this time.
Starc goes very full on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets his bat down in time. This is good bowling and good batting as well from the youngman.
Serves a good-length delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it nicely again.
On a good length and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite is not interested in touching that and lets it go.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out solidly. This man is key here for the Windies.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite just pushes it gently down the ground for a couple.
FOUR LEG BYES! West Indies will take this! On a length and angling into pads. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to clip it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and runs towards the fine leg fence.
NO BALL! Overstepping by Josh Hazlewood! Lands it on a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is as solid as ever.

An appeal for a caught behind but nothing serious! Serves it on a good length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend it but the ball seams away just a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Serves it on a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
A fullish delivery at 146.9 kph. It is shaping away nicely again and Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out quite confidently.
Bowls it on a length again, around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it square off the wicket on the off side.
Touch short of good length and outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul watches it till the end and then lets it go calmly.
Starc goes for a full delivery and it is on the pads. Tagenarine Chanderpaul tries to flick it but misses.The ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
A fullish delivery, around off at 147 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite is patient enough to leave it.
Bowls it full again and angled across the right hander at almost 146 clicks. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go again.
Nicely bowled! Josh Hazlewood just kisses the deck on a length and angles it across the left-hander. Tagenarine Chanderpaul plays inside the line of the ball.
And again! A touch fuller and just a bit wider, Chanderpaul plays inside the line of the ball and the ball does nip back in late on its way to the keeper.
Back of a length and around the body, Chanderpaul negotiates it well and keeps it down on the off side.

FOUR! What a confidence booster that is for the young man. This is full and straight, swinging back in a touch. Tagenarine Chanderpaul plays a beautiful on drive and beats mid on to pick up a boundary.
Back of a length and over middle and leg, Chanderpaul defends it off the back foot.
Ouch, that must have hurt! Good length, around middle and just seaming in off the deck. Chanderpaul looks to block it out but misses and takes a blow to the groin region and he is down in pain.
Good length on leg stump and at over 144 clicks. The ball nips in off the deck and Kraigg Brathwaite gets hit on the thigh pad.
Lovely shape on that one but equally well played by Brathwaite. This one shapes in a touch from around the off stump, Brathwaite plays it late and with soft hands down to the gully region.

Very full at 143.5 clicks and swinging into the middle stump. Kraigg Brathwaite plays a checked straight drive and gets good timing on it. Pat Cummins hunts it down from mid on and saves a run for his side.
Fullish length outside off, at over 145 clicks and swinging away from the left-hander. Tagenarine Chanderpaul does well to leave it.
Trying to attack the pads but it is spilled down the leg side.

FOUR! Just a gentle punch and the ball runs away. A low full toss on off stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul just shows the full face of the bat and collects a boundary towards long off. The young man is dealing only in boundaries at the moment.
Lovely channel from Josh Hazlewood. On a nagging length and around the off stump, just straightening a touch off the deck. Brathwaite looks to block but the ball zips past the outside edge.
BEATEN! Josh Hazlewood just pitches it a bit further up and keeps it close to the off pole. An expansive drive is induced from Kraigg Brathwaite and he is lucky not to edge that one.
An attempted short ball, around the leg stump and just doesn't rise enough. Brathwaite ducks and Alex Carey does well to dive down to his left and grab it.
Good running. Good length around the stumps, this is just gently pushed onto the leg side for a quick single.
Hazlewood comes from around the wicket and angles in a fuller delivery from around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to drive at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Well negotiated. Nagging length, bowled from wider of the crease and angling it in. Chanderpaul looks to drive but just plays inside the line of the ball.
Cummins starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery over off, Brathwaite gets right behind the line to block.
Banged in short and over the stumps, Brathwaite ducks and another good take from Alex Carey as the ball wobbles a bit.

Oh, no! Now Kraigg Brathwaite gets hit in a similar area to Tagenarine Chanderpaul and that can be really painful. Good length around off and nipping in off the deck. Brathwaite looks to defend but misses and takes a blow to the groin region. He shrugs it off though.
Full and close to the off pole, nipping away a touch after pitching. Brathwaite fails to defend as the ball stays low and zips past the outside edge.
Leg bye! Good length again, around the pads, Brathwaite hops and looks to work it off his hips but misses. The ball goes off the thigh pads and towards short fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
Nagging length served close to the off stump. It is angling away but just holds its line and once again Tagenarine Chanderpaul plays inside the line of the delivery.
Just short! Shorter and angled at the body. Brathwaite hops and is able to keep it down in front of the man at short leg.

FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Full and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it on the up and times it sweetly right back past the bowler for a boundary. A no ball is also called as Hazlewood has overstepped.
A tad shorter and on leg stump, Brathwaite tucks it 'round the corner for a single.

That one almost knocked him over! Josh Hazlewood comes from 'round the wicket and angles in a short ball at the body. Tagenarine Chanderpaul is able to duck under it but tries to bend his back and get out of the way. Chanderpaul does well to drop the hands and takes a blow on the left shoulder.
Full and angling into the pads, this is flicked away towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length and around the hips, Brathwaite hops and keeps it down on the leg side.
Fuller in length and angled into middle and leg. The ball skids on a bit but Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
Fullish length, in that channel around off and pushed across the off stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul watchfully leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Good length, pitching around leg and angling away. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to block it off the front foot but gets squared up and the ball hits him high on the pads.

Another blow to the young man but he is hanging in there. Banged in short and over the stumps, Tagenarine Chanderpaul does well again to get the hands down as he looks to bend his back. The ball crashes into the chest region and lobs up onto the off side.

FOUR! This is a great battle between the debutant and the seasoned Aussie attack. Short and just wide enough for Tagenarine Chanderpaul to throw his hands at it. Chanderpaul slaps it away over the point region and picks up a boundary.
Good length, around the top of off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul just blocks it out onto the off side.
On a length and around middle and leg, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Lyon starts off with a regular off-break delivery, on a length and down the leg side. Kraigg Brathwaite gets deep in his crease and works it 'round the corner for a single.
Comes from 'round the wicket now and tosses it up around off stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul presses forward to defend.
Just a little bit of drift into the middle stump, Chanderpaul watches it carefully and keeps it out.
Drags back the length a fraction and bowls it slower as well. The ball bounces a bit extra but Chanderpaul manages to keep it down.
Nicely flighted on off stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul pueshe sit out on the off side.
Fraction shorter and close to the off pole, Tagenarine Chanderpaul rocks back and chops it towards point.
Good length around off, Brathwaite stays back and blocks it out on the off side.
Pitches it up now in that channel outside off and Brathwaite just shoulders arms.
Top delivery! Nagging length around the fifth stump line and Kraigg Brathwaite has a feel for it. The ball just nips away a touch and beats the outside edge.
Good, early call for the single. Fuller in length and at the stumps, this is flicked away in front of mid-wicket for a quick single.

Beaten all ends up! Pat Cummins comes from around the wicket and serves it on a length at around off stump and at 138 clicks. The ball shapes away beautifully but Tagenarine Chanderpaul manages to play inside the line of the ball.
This is a bit fuller and a bit wider of the off stump. Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Nagging length, turning it in from around off, Brathwaite defends it out.
Slightly shorter and outside off, turning into the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it off the back foot and gets it through point for a couple of runs.

Shouts of 'catch it,' but there's no bat on that one. On a length around middle and leg, this one grips and bounces a bit extra as well. Brathwaite pads it away and the ball loops up off the thigh pad around leg gully.
Full and straight, pushed back to the bowler.
Nathan Lyon is getting some real purchase at the moment. This is tossed up outside off and the ball turns in, beating the outside edge.
Close! Flighted once again by Lyon, on a length and this one turns in sharply from around off. Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms but the ball almost clips the top of off stump.
Pitched-up delivery, angling it into middle stump, well blocked by Tagenarine Chanderpaul.

SIX! All the way! Cummins goes for the bumper over leg stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul shows some intent and gets inside the line of the ball before hooking it a long way over the fine leg fence. A bright start this from the young man.
Full and angling into middle and leg, Tagenarine Chanderpaul gently pushes it back past the bowler and past mid off as well for a couple of runs.
This is full and straight, Chanderpaul stays solid in defense.
A sharp bouncer now angling down leg, Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to take it on yet again but is well beaten this time around.
Edged away! A touch fuller and closer to the off stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul pushes at the ball with soft hands and gets an outside edge down towards gully.
Lyon bowls it quicker and touch shorter on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite turns it towards the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite takes a big stride forward and blocks it out.
Pushes it quicker on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to short leg.
Bowls it much slower through the air, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is solid in his defence again.
Bowls it on the straighter line and flatter. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out again.
Pitches it around off and it turns back in slightly. Kraigg Brathwaite fends it off the front foot.
Back of a length and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul dabs it towards the gully region.
Cummins goes fuller on middle from 'round the wicket. Tagenarine Chanderpaul shows the full face of his blade as he pushes it past the bowler for a single. 50 up for West Indies! Good start this.
On a good length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite watches it till the end and lets it go.

An appeal for a caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. However, after discussion with his teammates, Cummins takes the DRS! The replays roll in and there is nothing on the Hotspot and Snicko as well. So, the original decision stays and Kraigg Brathwaite will continue. The keeper and the slip fielders were not that confident but Head at short leg was. Anyways still no wicket for Australia!
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite with a solid block back to the bowler.
A good-length delivery and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend it but the ball zips past the outside edge of his blade.
Tossed up, outside off. The ball turns away after pitching and Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go.
Nice loopy delivery on off. However, Tagenarine Chanderpaul is equal to the task and blocks it out.
Flighted delivery again, on off. Nice front foot defence by Tagenarine Chanderpaul.
Pulls his length back slightly but the line is again, around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it towards the off side.
Shortish delivery and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul goes deep in his crease and punches it through covers and the batters run three before the fielder cuts it off.
A flatter and quicker delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it off the back foot.

Cummins comes 'round the wicket and bowls a bouncer angling into middle. The young man, Tagenarine Chanderpaul goes for a hook shot but misses it. There are fielders at fine leg and deep square leg, so he needs to be careful.
Back of a length and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul steers it through backward point for a single.
On a good length and outside off. The ball seams away off the pitch and Kraigg Brathwaite does well to keep his bat inside the line of the ball.
Bangs it short and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite calmly ducks under it.
Back of a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and works it towards the leg side.
Cummins bowls it on a good length but it is outside off. So, Kraigg Brathwaite just decides to have some fun by leaving it.
A full delivery angling into middle from 'round the wicket. Tagenarine Chanderpaul drives it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it off the inside half of his blade to short fine leg.
FOUR! Wow! That's a confident shot! Short and outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul cuts it hard through point for a boundary. This young man is looking like a pretty good player.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it off the inside half of his blade.

Shortish delivery and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul cuts it with some good flourish again. However, this time the timing is not that good and the ball fails to reach the ropes. The batters do take three tough.
A fullish delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to mid on. The fight is on!
Back of a length, on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it towards the leg side.
On a length, on middle and leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it off the inside half of his blade to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off at 141 clicks. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and blocks it out.

Oh, nasty from Starc! He bowls it on the shorter side, on middle. The ball zips off the surface and bounces sharply. However, Kraigg Brathwaite does quite well there to ride the bounce and keeps it down on the turf without much fuss.
A fullish delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to mid off now.
Full and way down the leg side. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to flick it but misses.
Short and fast angling down the leg side from 'round the wicket. Tagenarine Chanderpaul tries to pull it but misses.
Back of a length, around leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul tries to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Josh bowls it full and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
On a length, on off at 136.5 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it solidly from his crease.
Pulls his length back and it is around off. Kraigg Brathwaite watches it carefully and then leaves it.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it calmly towards the leg side. Three overs left in the day now!
Starc bowls it full and on leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pushes it wide of mid on for a single.
On a good length, on middle at 142.3 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and defends it left of short fine leg.
A fullish delivery and angled across the right hander at 144.4 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite makes a good leave again.
Bowls another fullish delivery, around off at 144 clicks again. Kraigg Brathwaite resists the temptation to drive and lets it go.
Pulls his length back this time, on off at 142.3 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and blocks it onto the turf.
Nice calm and patient approach again! Starc serves a fullish delivery, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Shortish delivery and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul rides the bounce and steers it through the gully region for a couple.

FOUR! Outside edge but it is in the gap and Tagenarine Chanderpaul moves onto 45 now! On a good length and around off. The ball seams away a bit and squares Tagenarine Chanderpaul as he tries to defend it. The ball goes between the slip fielder and a gully fielder for a boundary.
Lands it on a good length again and outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go.

In the air...but well short of the deep square leg fielder. Josh Hazlewood bangs it short and on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul takes up the challenge and hooks it uppishly but well short of the deep square leg fielder for a single.
Touch short of good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it solidly from his crease.
Goes a bit fuller and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it to mid on. Final over of the day coming up...
A very full delivery on off at 145 kph. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it solidly.
Bangs it short and it is angled around leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets inside the line of the ball and lets it go.
Starc is firing this short deliveries at the young man now. It is angled on middle and leg again at 141 kph and Tagenarine Chanderpaul does well to duck under it.
Bowls a fullish delivery on the pads. Tagenarine Chanderpaul clips it to fine leg for a single.

A ripper from Starc! He comes 'round the wicket and angles a good-length delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite is stuck on his crease as he tries to defend it. However, the ball goes just past the outside edge of his blade back to the keeper.

Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out! This has been a great effort from this Windies opening pair. Starc comes 'round the wicket and lands a length delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps his focus on and blocks it solidly. West Indies are 74/0 at the end of Day 2!

On the mark straightaway! Lands it on a good length, around off. The ball seams just away from Tagenarine Chanderpaul as it is angled across him and just beats the outside edge of his blade as he tries to defend.

Another ripper from Josh Hazlewood! Lands it on a good length again, on off this time. It seams away a fair bit and with good bounce as Tagenarine Chanderpaul ends up defending inside the line of the ball.
Serves another good-length delivery, outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go easily this time.
Shortish delivery and around leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets inside the line of the ball and lets it go.

FIFTY on debut for Tagenarine Chanderpaul! Brilliant knock from the young man and he would be looking to make most of this start. Just short of good length and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it with soft hands and the ball rolls away off the outside half of his blade through the gully region for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Gone this time and Josh Hazlewood strikes early on Day 3! End of a very good knock on debut by Tagenarine Chanderpaul. Josh Hazlewood lands a perfect delivery again, in that channel around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul again tries to defend this good-length delivery which is angled across him. However, this time the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and  goes straight to first slip where David Warner takes an easy catch. Now then, a wicket early in the day and let's see how the Windies respond now.
Howout: c David Warner b Josh Hazlewood

Commentary: A fullish delivery on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to fine leg for a single.
A good-length delivery, around off. The ball shapes away a bit and beats the outside edge of Bonner's blade as he tries to defend.
Oh, beaten again! A fullish delivery, around off. It is shaping away and Bonner tries to drive it away. The ball beats the outside edge of his blade again.
On a length, on off. Bonner with a solid block off the front foot.
A fullish delivery on middle. Bonner tries to flick it but gets the inside edge on his pads. The ball rolls towards the leg side and Bonner takes a single to get off the mark.
On a good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it off the front foot.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Bonner watches it carefully and lets it go.
Serves it on a length, on off. Bonner blocks it solidly from his crease.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Bonner defends it towards mid on.
Serves another good-length delivery on off. Bonner blocks it right under his eyes.
Bowls a fullish delivery and outside off. The ball swings away a bit and beats the outside edge of Bonner's blade as he tries to defend it.
Continues to hit that good length, outside off. Bonner makes a watchful leave.
Cummins hits that good length and keeps it around off. Kraigg Brathwaite plays it very late as he allows it to shape away and defends it towards the off side.
Lands it on a good length again and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
The ball seams away sharply here! It probably hits that crack outside off. This one is just short of good length. The ball goes away from Kraigg Brathwaite as he leaves it.
Bowls a short one and angles it around leg. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks under it.
Gets back to his good length stuff, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend it but the ball straightens after coming in with the angles and beats the outside edge of Kraigg Brathwaite's blade.
Shortish length and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite plays it with the angled blade and soft hands. The ball goes through the backward point region for a couple.
This is just short of good length and outside off. Bonner leaves it alone.
Lovely delivery! Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Bonner presses forward to defend it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Pulls his length back this time, on off. Bonner rides the bounce and blocks it out.
A fullish delivery on middle and shaping into the batter. Bonner flicks it to mid-wicket now.
Touch fuller again and around off. Bonner drives it to covers for a single.
FOUR! Poor delivery and punished! Goes fuller and on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite just flicks it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. Much-needed for the Windies.
On a good length again and outside off. The ball seams away and Bonner does well to not commit to that ball.
Good running this! On a length, on off. Bonner fends it towards the off side with soft hands and takes a quick single.
Back of a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to clip it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.

Oh, what a peach of a delivery! Cummins angles it on off. Lands it on a length and Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend on that angle but the ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of his blade.
And again! Continues to hit good length and serves it around off. The ball straightens again after pitching and beats Kraigg Brathwaite as he tries to defend it.
A fullish delivery and it shapes away nicley from Kraigg Brathwaite as he gets beaten again. Good thing is that he is managing to keep himself inside the line of the ball.
On a good length, on off. Bonner defends it solidly from his crease.
Lands on a length, on off. Bonner blocks it towards the off side and takes a quick single.
Serves a good-length delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Good leave! Lands it on a good length and around off. The ball seams into him a bit but Kraigg Brathwaite covers his off stump and lets it go.
Banged in short and it is outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks under it.
Just short of good length this time and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Cummins hits that hard length again, on off. Bonner tries to defend it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Bangs it short and it is angled around leg. Bonner ducks under it.
Now gets back to his good length! Serves it around off. Bonner tries to defend it off the front foot but the ball just seems to be missing the outside edges of these blades right now.
Cummins with a length delivery on off. Bonner blocks it solidly.

FOUR! Lovely shot! This is good batting, you need to score runs when you get an opportunity. Overpitched delivery, around off. Bonner takes a good stride forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Beaten! Very close to the outside edge of Bonner's blade this time. Serves a good-length delivery, around the off pole. Bonner tries to defend it but the ball straightens and beats him.
Starts off with a length delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to square leg for a single.
Hits the good length and outside off. The ball shapes away and Bonner makes a good leave.

Oh, that has hit him on the helmet! Sharp bouncer by Green angles it on middle. Bonner takes his eyes off the ball and tries to duck under it but the ball goes onto hit his helmet. He will need some treatment here!
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone.
Bouncer again but this time Bonner does well to duck under it. On middle and at  a good pace but negotiated well by Bonner.
Back of a length, on off. Bonner waits for it and plays it with soft hands towards the off side.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out with ease.

A fullish delivery, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite sees an opportuntiy to score runs and tries to drive it. However, the ball coms into Kraigg Brathwaite a bit and finds the inside edge of his blade. It goes onto hit his pads.
Bowls a half-volley, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives but finds the mid off fielder.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite fends it out from his crease.
On the shorter side, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite though plays it quite well as he rides the bounce and dabs it towards the off side.

Beaten! A frustrated look on the face of Cummins. He has bowled well but has not been able to find that edge. Just short of good length and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to punch it away from his body but misses it.
This is bowled fuller and in that channel around off, Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms.
Full and angling onto the pads, Bonner flicks it down to fine leg for a single.
A good bumper now, over the stumps and jumping off the surface. Kraigg Brathwaite gets taken aback a bit but manages to get out of the way.
Pitches it up now on off stump, Brathwaite pushes it out towards silly mid off.
Length ball, around middle and leg, Brathwaite has a slight shuffle across off stump and blocks it out.
Back of a length and over middle, this one gets up pretty high but it is solidly kept down by Brathwaite.
Serves it on a length and around off stump, Bonner defends it off the front foot.
Good length, angling it in from around off, Nkrumah Bonner presses forward to make the block.
Goes fuller now and keeps it outside off, Bonner punches it on the up but straight toward short cover.
Cummins bowls this one on a hard length, around middle and leg, Bonner hops and looks to tuck it away but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
BEATEN! Pitches it up now in that channel around off and angles it in. The ball shapes away beautifully after pitching and completely squares up Bonner who is beaten past the outside edge.
Good length around leg stump, Bonner nudges it onto the leg side. Maiden!
Green goes full and straight, Brathwaite pushes it back past the bowler and to the left of the man at mid on to pick up an easy single.
A touch fuller around the fourth stump and zipping off the deck, Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms at it.
On a length and this is angled into middle and leg. The ball skids through but Bonner is able to keep it out.

FOUR! Width on offer. Fuller in length but well outside off, Nkrumah Bonner goes for the drive but gets it off the outer half of the bat and well past the slip cordon into the fence. The 100 is now up for West Indies.
This is dug in short and over the stumps, Bonner ducks under it.
Pitches it up now and looks to attack the stumps, Bonner is able to get a bat on it.
Starc starts from over the wicket and serves a full ball outside off. Brathwaite frees his arms a bit and drives it past mid off for a couple of runs.

Risky single but good running. Nagging length, shaping it in from around middle. Brathwaite looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket. They go for the single and the direct hit is missed at the batter's end but it seems Bonner would have been home anyways.
A bit of a fumble and the batters take two with ease. Very full and wide, Nkrumah Bonner caresses it through extra cover for a couple of runs.
Fullish length around off, Bonner watchfully leaves it alone.
Full and around off, Bonner shoulders arms.
A half-volley around off and at around 141 clicks. Nkrumah Bonner just bunts it onto the off side and scampers across for a single.
NO BALL! This is full and straight, Jermaine Blackwood negotiates his first ball well as he blocks it towards mid on. A no ball is called for overstepping.
On a fullish length and attacking middle and leg, Blackwood punches it towards mid on.
Leg bye! Good length around the pads, Blackwood looks to flick but gets it off his pads past square leg. They get a leg bye.
A touch fuller and at the stumps, Brathwaite defends it out on the leg side.
A length ball at the stumps, Brathwaite keeps it out.
This is around middle and leg, Brathwaite pushes it towards mid on.
Excellent running! Back of a length and around off, Brathwaite hops and keeps it down in front of covers and scampers through for one.
Around the top of off and angling across the right-hander, Brathwaite looks to defend but is beaten past the outside edge.
On a hard length and around off, Brathwaite gets right behind the line of the ball to keep it down on the deck.
A length ball on off stump, Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Overpitched from Starc and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it uppishly through the cover region and picks up a couple of runs.
Full again around off, Brathwaite drives again but is unable to beat the man at mid off to his left.
Shorter this time and angled across the off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite stays on the back foot and just eases it through extra cover for a couple of more runs.
Starts off with a shortish delivery on off stump. This one turns in and Blackwood keeps it down towards short leg.
Tosses it up on a length and outside off, there is a good bit of turn into the right-hander. Jermaine Blackwood just works it away through mid-wicket for a single.

A bit of aggression from the Windies skipper. Lyon switches to 'round the wicket and floats it up on leg stump. Brathwaite advances and drags the slog in front of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Lyon pulls the length back a shade and bowls it around the pads, Brathwaite goes on the back foot and nudges it past the diving fielder at leg slip for a run.
On a length and around leg stump, Jermaine Blackwood looks to play it off the back foot but ends up blocking it onto the deck.
Fuller this time around and on leg stump, Blackwood pushes it towards mid on.
Fullish length, close to the off pole and angling across. Kraigg Brathwaite plays at it with soft hands and gets an outside edge down to third man for a single.
Starc hits the length hard and bowls it on off stump, Blackwood defends it off the back foot.
Good length around middle stump, Blackwood keeps it out without any fuss.
On a hard length and on off stump, Blackwood gets right behind the line to make another solid block.
Short of a length and around off, Jermaine Blackwood hops and defends it down on the deck.
Lovely delivery! Fuller length, close to the off pole and at around 144 clicks. The ball just zips off the deck as Blackwood looks to drive but gets beaten past the outside edge.
On a length and turning in sharply from off stump, Brathwaite just shoulders arms and the ball hits him on the body.
FOUR! Well played! This is tossed up around off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite gets inside the line of the ball and sweeps it away behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Flighted, around middle and leg, this is nudged away onto the leg side.
Shorter in length and turning into the pads, Brathwaite looks to work it past the fielder at short leg but fails to beat him.
This is down the leg side, Brathwaite leaves it alone but the ball hits the pads and goes towards leg slip.
Around middle and leg, Brathwaite keeps it down in front of short leg.
A bouncer now, over leg stump and a bit too high for Jermaine Blackwood to play at it.
On a hard length and over leg stump, Blackwood hops and dabs it down on the leg side.
Nicely done. Starc goes a bit fuller and bowls it around off stump at over 141 clicks. Jermaine Blackwood looks to block but the ball just straightens a touch and whizzes past the outside edge.
A length ball around middle and leg, this is easily blocked out by Jermaine Blackwood.
Short ball now, at 141.3 clicks and looking to attack the body but it is down the leg side. Blackwood does well to read the line of the ball and move out of the way of the delivery.
Good length around off, Blackwood watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.
Pitches it on middle and turns into Kraigg Brathwaite. He goes back and defends it towards the leg side.
SIX! Good positive intent from Kraigg Brathwaite! Tossed up, on mddle. Kraigg Brathwaite dances down the track and tonks it down the ground for a maximum.
This time quicker and flatter, around leg. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to sweep but misses.
Pushes it quicker again and tad shorter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Tossed up and fuller on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to mid off.

FIFTY For Kraigg Brathwaite! This has been a superb knock from the skipper, great grit and determination all through. This one is fuller and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Oh, wide of second slip! On a length and angled across the batter. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it away from hos body. The ball though goes off the outside edge of his blade and wide of Smith who dives to his right but fails to reach it. The ball races away towards the third man fence.
Back of a length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and blocks it out.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it wide of mid off for a single.
On the shorter side, on off. Jermaine Blackwood hops and defends it out.
Angles a shortish delivery on off from 'round the wicket and Jermaine Blackwood does well to block it again.
In the gap! On the shorter side and around off. Jermaine Blackwood rides the bounce nicely and opens the face of his blade just a bit. The ball runs through the point region for a couple.
Flatter and quicker on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Another good shot from Kraigg Brathwaite! Great placement! This is fuller and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite sweeps and sweeps it wll through square leg for a boundary.
Pushes it quicker on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Around off and turning into the batter. Kraigg Brathwaite plays it late and fends it towards the off side.
Touch short and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it from his crease.
Tossed up, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite sweeps it to deep square leg for a single this time.
On a good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it solidly from his crease.
A fullish delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite dabs it towards point. Again plays it late and with soft hands. Good batting this!
Back of a length and angling into the body. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad towards the leg side and a leg bye is taken.
On the shorter side again, around off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it through covers for a couple.
Hits the hard length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it right under his eyes.
Tossed up and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite opens the face of his blade as he presses forward to defend and takes a single towards the backward point region.
Lovely flighted delivery again, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the front foot.

FOUR! Jermaine Blackwood is getting more and more confident with each delivery! This is tossed up and wider outside off. Jermaine Blackwood strides forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Touch shorter and on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the back foot.
On the shorter side again, on off. Jermaine Blackwood goes back and tries to work it towards the leg side but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Tossed up, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the front foot.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the off side.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite covers the line of the ball and fends it onto the turf.
Goes a bit fuller and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is as solid as ever.
Shortens his length now on off. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and blocks it out.
A length delivery on off. Bit of shape into the batter and Kraigg Brathwaite defends it with the inside half of his blade towards the leg side. Single taken. 150 up for West Indies!
Serves a length delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out solidly as he covers the line of the ball nicely here. That's Lunch on Day 3!
Starc begins the session from around the stumps and angles in a very full ball from outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite jams it out on the off side.
Just brings the length back a touch and brings it a bit closer to the off pole as well. Brathwaite looks to block but the ball holds its line and passes the outside edge.
This is full and at the stumps, Brathwaite punches it back towards the bowler.
Full again, at 142 clicks and attacking middle and leg stump. Brathwaite keeps it out on the leg side.
This one's pitched up on off stump, Brathwaite drives it tentatively and towards mid on.

Just staying a touch low. Nagging length around off and angling in. Brathwaite looks to defend it with a straight bat but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge. Starc starts off the session with a maiden.
Cummins digs it in a bit short and around the body. Jermaine Blackwood hops and keeps it down on the leg side.
Goes fuller now and around the fifth stump line, Blackwood lets it through to the keeper.
This is pitched up around off, Blackwood pushes it back to the bowler.
Very full and on off stump, just shaping away a touch as well. Jermaine Blackwood punches it back out on the deck.
On a good length and around off stump, Blackwood watchfully leaves it alone.
Back-to-back maidens! This is a touch fuller and around off, Jermaine Blackwood presses forward and solidly keeps it out on the off side.
FOUR LEG BYES! A bit too straight from Starc. Good length around the pads, Brathwaite looks to tickle it fine but misses. The ball goes off the thigh pads and runs away into the fine leg fence.
Fullish length around off, Brathwaite plays it square of the wicket towards cover-point for an easy single.
Starc switches to over the wicket and angles across a full ball at 141 clicks. Jermaine Blackwood gets pushed onto the back foot and has a feel for it but the ball beats the outside edge.
Back of a length and around off, Blackwood goes on the back foot and dabs it down with gentle hands towards backward point for one. The 50-run stand between these two is up.
TWO LEG BYES! Shorter and around the hips, Brathwaite plays it off the thigh pad again and down to fine leg. The batters pick up a couple of leg byes.
Tentative drive! Full and pushed well outside off, Brathwaite goes after it but ends up just pushing at it. The ball goes to the left of the man at cover and they get a run as well.
Full and straight from Cummins, Brathwaite blocks it back to the bowler.

OUT! TIMBER! Skipper to skipper and at last, Pat Cummins does have his 200th Test wicket and he has certainly deserved it. This is a dream delivery from Cummins as he serves it on a length and angles it into middle and off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to block and plays down the correct line but the ball just straightens a touch off the deck and beats the outside edge going on to hit the top of off stump. Brathwaite departs after a solid knock but Australia now have a chance to go hard at the Windies middle order.
Howout: b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Absolute ripper! Pat Cummins switches to around the wicket and welcomes Kyle Mayers to the crease with a sharp bouncer. This is around off and angling in at a good height. Mayers looks to sway away from the line of the ball but the ball hits the left shoulder and Alex Carey leaps up brilliantly to grab it.

Was there any bat on it? No, just past the outside edge. Fuller in length and angling in from around off. The ball seams away a touch and zips past the outside edge as Kyle Mayers looks to block it off the front foot. There is an appeal from behind but Cummins isn't interested and rightly so.
Around the top of off, Mayers just about keeps it out on the off side.
A length ball on off stump, Mayers flicks it away towards mid-wicket. Top over from Pat Cummins, a wicket-maiden.
Mitchell Starc comes from over the wicket and angles across a full and wide one, Jermaine Blackwood strokes it away towards extra cover.

Edged and FOUR! This is full and wide again at 143.3 clicks. Jermaine Blackwood goes for the flashy cover drive but the ball takes the outside edge and goes in between the slip cordon and gully for a boundary. An extra slip there and Blackwood was a goner.

Poor running, that should have been an easy three. Starc keeps it full and wide, Blackwood plays a lovely cover drive and it is a long chase for the fielder who runs behind it from covers. They, however, take only two and are content with it.
Starc shortens the length and bowls it over leg stump, Blackwood hops and nudges it down on the leg side.
Good length, angling across the right-hander, Blackwood lets it through to the keeper.
Full and trying to attack the pads but it is spilled down the leg side by Starc.
On a hard length and around off, Mayers stays on the back foot and pushes it out on the off side.
Nagging length, on the fifth stump line and just staying a bit low. Kyle Mayers doesn't move his feet as he looks to play the cover drive. The ball goes past the outside edge.
Goes full now and angles one into the middle stump. Mayers looks to drive at it but gets an inside edge towards fine leg and gets off the mark with a single.
Pat Cummins seems to have found his rhythm here. A short ball now over middle stump and this one just climbs on the batter. Jermaine Blackwood does well to hop and keep it down on the deck.
Fullish length at the stumps, nudged away in front of mid-wicket.
Pitches it up now and angles it into the off pole, Blackwood looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the leg side.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Kyle Mayers' stay at the crease is a short one. Mitchell Starc steams in from over the wicket and angles in a full ball into the off pole. This is bowled at over 144 clicks and catches Mayers out. Once again Mayers' feet don't go anywhere and he is late in his attempted drive as well. The ball takes a faint inside edge and goes on to castle into the stumps. These are dangerous times for the Windies batters as they look to fend off the Aussie quicks.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: This is on a good length outside off, trying to bring it back into the right-hander. Jason Holder leaves it alone.
Fullish length and slanted across Holder who makes yet another leave.
This is very full and at 144 clicks around off stump, Holder watchfully leaves it alone.
Starc is just probing away around the off stump. This is full again, trying to induce the drive but Holder resists the temptation and leaves it alone.
Pitched up on off stump, Jason Holder pushes at it with soft hands and edges it down through backward point. The batters hurry back for the second and that is excellent running.
Good length around middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood tucks it away through square leg for a single.
On a good length again and angling into the pads, Holder looks to flick but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
This is pitched up on middle stump, Holder blocks it out towards mid on.
A good bumper now over off stump, Holder is able to duck under it though.
Well left! A touch fuller now, close to the off pole and jagging back in a touch. Jason Holder trusts the bounce and shoulders arms at it.
This is very full and angling into the leg stump, Holder manages to get some bat on it and flicks it through backward square leg for a run.
Full and in that channel around off stump, Holder leaves it alone.
On a length around off and seaming away, Jason Holder lets it through to the keeper.
Switches to 'round the wicket now and tries to attack the base of middle stump, Holder jams it out towards extra cover.
Keeps it full but this time tries to angle it in from outside off. Holder makes an easy leave.
Starc tries to attack the pads but just snatches at it a bit and pulls the trigger down the leg side. Alex Carey does well to collect that one.
Fullish length, well outside off and it is once again left alone by Holder. Maiden!
Cummins with a back-of-a-length delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood calmly blocks it out.
Serves it on a length, on off at 132 kph. Jermaine Blackwood fends it from his crease towards mid on.
Goes fuller and on middle. Jermaine Blackwood clips it to square leg for a single.
Shortish delivery and angling into the body at 135 kph. Holder rides the bounce and works it behind square to the leg side for a single.
On a length and angling into middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it right of mid on and looks for a single but is sent back by his partner.
Short and outside off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it through covers for a couple. Jermaine Blackwood is looking quite comfortable in the middle.
Josh Hazlewood starts off with a fullish delivery on off. Holder leans forward and drives it crisply to mid off.
Hits that good length area on off. Holder though leaves it on height as the ball goes over the off pole back to the keeper.
Touch shorter and angling into middle. Holder clips it to deep square leg for a couple.
Back of a length and outside off. Holder leaves it alone.
Better line! On a good length again but this time close to the off pole. However, Holder is aware enough of his off stump and leaves it alone.

A fullish delivery on middle. Holder tries to drive it but seems to have missed it as the ball hits his back leg. Josh Hazlewood appeals and the umpire raises his finger. It did look out to the naked eye but Holder takes the DRS straightaway and looks pretty confident as well. The replays roll in and the Hotspot shows no bat invloved. However, there is a spike as the ball passes the blade on the Snicko. The on-field umpire himself seems to be confused and first gives it out and then realises that he has made a mistake and gives it not out. There is lot of confusion on the field and Australian players are not happy. However, the offical decision is not out and that is what matters. Holder will continue!
Tossed up delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it to covers.
Slower through the air, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the front foot.
Another flighted delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood pushes it to covers.

FOUR! Streaky but a boundary for Jermaine Blackwood! A shortish delivery and just outside off. Jermaine Blackwood goes back and tries to punch it. However, he gets a thick outside edge that runs away through the gap towards the third man fence.
Slower through the air and on middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it towards the leg side.
Pushes it bit quicker on middle. Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the back foot and the ball loops up a bit in air and falls just away from the short leg fielder.
Touch shorter and outside off. Holder lets it go with ease.
Just short of good length, on off. Holder stays deep in his crease and blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on off. Holder with a solid defence again.
