Angles a fullish delivery on middle. Holder clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and outside off. Jermaine Blackwood goes deep in his crease and plays it quite late as he dabs it towards the off side.

Oh, that's a nasty delivery! Josh Hazlewood bowls this bouncer at a perfect awkward height angling into the body. Jermaine Blackwood tries to sway away from the line of the ball but the ball goes onto his his handle and gloves.
Tossed up, on off. Holder with a solid block.
Slower through the air and around off. Holder fends it with soft hands and opens the face of his blade a bit. The ball runs through the third man region and couple of runs are taken.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tossed up and outside off. It is a half-volley and Holder takes a big stride forward and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on off. Holder drives it to mid off.
Lovely tossed up delivery. It induces Holder to press for a forward defence. However, the ball goes straight off the deck and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Flatter and quicker on off. Holder blocks it solidly.
A length delivery and angling into middle. Jermaine Blackwood clips it to mid-wicket.
Targets the middle stump again. On  length and Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the leg side.

Oh, that's a ripper from Josh Hazlewood! A perfect short delivery on off as Jermaine Blackwood is caught off-guard. He hops and looks to keep it out. However, the ball goes off the shoulder of his blade and loops up in the in front of gully. Green there runs forward and dives to take it but fails to reach it in the end.
Back of a length, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood clips it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Jermaine Blackwood is definitely rattled a bit by this short-pitch stuff. Josh Hazlewood angles a shortish delivery on the body and Jermaine Blackwood just about manages to keep it out.
Back of a length and outside off. Jermaine Blackwood lets it go. Good battle going on here between Josh Hazlewood and Jermaine Blackwood.
Tossed up, on off. Holder blocks it out.
Fullish delivery on middle. Holder knocks it down to long on for a single.
Tad shorter and turning into off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the back foot.
Fuller delivery and slower through the air, on off. Jermaine Blackwood keeps it out off the front foot.
On middle and fuller again. Jermaine Blackwood pushes it towards left of short mid-wicket where the fielder makes a good stop diving to his left.
Quicker delivery again and flatter. Jermaine Blackwood with a solid block.
Bangs it short and on middle. Holder ducks under it.
Touch shorter and on off. Holder stays deep in his crease and defends it towards the off side.
Keeps it on the shorter side but it is a harmless delivery as it is way outside off. Holder leaves it alone.

Lands it on a length angling into middle and leg. Holder tries to work it towards the leg side but misses and gets rapped up on the pads. A half an appeal by the bowler and the fielders but it is going down leg.
Serves it on a length again, on off. Holder blocks it out solidly.
Hazlewood with a shortish delivery on off. Holder drops his wrists as the ball hits his biceps and goes back to the keeper.
Pitches it on and turns this ball into middle at a good pace. Jermaine Blackwood lets it spin and blocks it out.
Bowls it on middle and flatter. Jermaine Blackwood works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Natural variation of an off-spinner beats him this time. Tossed up, around off. Holder presses forward to defend but the ball beats the outside edge as it does not turn and goes back to the keeper.
Tossed up on off. Holder reverse-paddles it and hits in the gap as the ball is stopped just inside the ropes near the third man fence. Three taken.
Tossed up delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket this time.
Loopy delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood though gets well forward and blocks it out.
Starts off with a fullish delivery on middle. Holder works it straight to mid on.
Short delivery at 132 kph, angling into off. Holder sways away from the line of the ball.
FOUR! Classy shot! Green overpitches on off. Holder leans forward and shows the full face of his blade as he drives it down the ground for a boundary.
Lands it on a length, on off. Holder with a solid block from his crease.
Green goes a bit fuller again and around off. Holder drives it crisply again but finds the mid off fielder.

FOUR LEG BYES! Australians are firing short-pitch bullets and the Windies batters keep taking blows on the way. Green bowls a short delivery now angling into the body. Holder tries to duck under it but does not keep his eyes on the ball. The ball brushes his helmet and runs away towards the fine leg fence. Time for the mandatory Concussion Test now. The physio is out and Holder looks all fine to continue.
Drops it a bit short and on leg stump, Jermaine Blackwood goes on the back foot and whips it away towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Switches to over the wicket now and tosses it up full and outside off, Holder leans on and eases it towards cover-point.
SIX! Right in the slot and dispatched! Tossed up on off stump and turning in. Jason Holder frees his arms and slogs it all the way over the wide long on fence for a biggie.
Around middle stump, Holder keeps it out.
On a nagging length and pushed through quicker on off stump, Holder goes on the back foot and makes the block.

OUT! TAKEN! The change of line has worked immediately for Nathan Lyon. Lyon switches to around the wicket and just floats it up on the pads with the ball turning in. Jason Holder looks to lean forward and clip it through the leg side but ends up closing the face of the bat early and flicking it behind. David Warner at leg slip is quick to react and gets down low to his left to take a sharp catch. Holder was looking dangerous but Lyon gets the better of him on this occasion.
Howout: c David Warner b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: NO BALL! This is full and at the stumps, Jermaine Blackwood drives it towards mid on. Green has overstepped and a no ball is called.
This is banged in short and around off, Blackwood ducks under it well.
'Catch,' is the call but it lands well short. This is full and angling into middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood looks to drive but ends up pushing it uppishly towards mid on.
Back of a length and around leg stump, this is flicked away towards mid-wicket.
Oh, almost pops up! Short ball at the body, Blackwood hops as he tries to block but gets it off the glove. Luckily for him, the ball doesn't lob up towards short leg.

This is excellent bowling from Cameron Green. Another short ball at the body and this is bowled right around the shoulder. Blackwood awkwardly fens it away and the ball goes through short fine leg. They get one.
A jaffa to end the over! Lands it on a hard length and keeps it tight around off stump. The ball straightens off the deck and zips past the outside edge of Shamarh Brooks' bat.
Loops it up around leg stump, Blackwood blocks it out on the leg side.
Just drags back the length a touch and keeps it around the pads, Jermaine Blackwood plays at it with soft hands and keeps it down on the leg side.
Nicely flighted on the pads, Blackwood tickles it towards short fine leg for a quick single.
Switches to over the wicket to the new man and tosses it up on off stump. Brooks gets forward well to defend.
Shorter and around middle and leg, Brooks rocks back and dabs it down on the leg side.
Around off stump, Shamarh Brooks drags the sweep shot through square leg and the concussion substitute is off the mark with a single.
FOUR! A teaser but it does go into the fence. A length ball on the pads, Shamarh Brooks clips it away through the square leg region and picks up a boundary.
NO BALL! A bouncer now from Green around the off stump and Brooks ducks under it. Green oversteps once again and a no ball is called.
Good length, around the top of off and this is pushed away towards covers.
On a length and angling into middle and leg, Brooks keeps it out on the leg side.

FOUR! Just erring in line here Cameron Green and that's just easy pickings for Shamarh Brooks. Back of a length and angling down leg, Brooks whips it away well wide of the man at fine leg for a boundary, the second one of the over.
A bit of hostility here from Cameron Green. This is short and angled at the body. Brooks tries to fend it off the back foot but gets hurried on and takes a blow on the gloves.
Just short! Short again and around the body, Brooks hops and does well to play at it with soft hands and keeps it down in front of short leg.
NO BALL AND FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne oversteps and starts off with a real loosener as well. This is short and down the leg side, Jermaine Blackwood tucks it 'round the corner for a boundary.
Much better on the second attempt. Tosses it up around off, Blackwood defends it out.
This is floated up around off, Blackwood blocks it out on the off side.
On the shorter side and over middle, Blackwood plays it off the back foot and onto the leg side.
This is a friendly full toss around middle but the ball just dips on the batter. Jermaine Blackwood ends up pushing it back to the bowler.
On a length and around middle, Blackwood watchfully defends it out.
Tossed up at the stumps, Blackwood defends it out with soft hands.
Lyon switches ends and starts off with a quicker one. This is angled in from around off but goes straight on after pitching. Shamarh Brooks does well to keep it out.
Tossed up, full and around off, pushed away onto the off side.
Flights it up a touch and bowls it around middle, Brooks defends it in front of the man at short leg.
Floated up around off, Brooks opens the face of the bat and eases it toward cover-point.
On a length around off and this one just skids on a bit quicker. Brooks rocks back and blocks it onto the on side.
Shorter and around middle, worked away off the back foot towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
A tad shorter and outside off, turning away, Brooks cuts it off the back foot but straight to point.

Floated up on the pads, Shamarh Brooks gets a fine tickle on it and the ball races away towards the fine leg fence. David Warner from leg slip chases it down and manages to pull it back in. Three runs are taken.
Around off, this is eased away towards cover for a single.
Shorter and on middle, Shamarh Brooks turns it through mid-wicket and is quick to get back for the second.
Around the off stump, Brooks plays it late and well behind point for yet another brace.
Tossed up, full and around off, Brooks drives it down to long off for a single. That will be Tea on Day 3!
Starts off with a tossed up delivery on off. Brooks drives it straight to mid off.
Another loopy delivery on middle. Brooks drives it down the ground for a single.
This is a fuller delivery, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood drives it to covers now.
On the shorter side, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.
Oh, much quicker this one at 99 kph. It is tad short in length and around off. Jermaine Blackwood gets the inside edge onto his pads as he tries to defend it.
Slower through the air, on off. Jermaine Blackwood takes a good stride forward and blocks it.
Bowls from 'round the wicket and on off. Brooks defends it off the back foot.
Pushes it quicker on off. Brooks keeps it out off the back foot.
Bowls it fuller and around leg. Brooks tries to sweep it but misses.
Flatter and quicker again on off. Brooks blocks it out nicely again.

FOUR! Oh, just away from Head! Fuller delivery on off. Brooks drives it uppishly left of the bowler and Head dives to his left. However, he fails to get any hand on it as the ball races down the ground for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Brooks fends it off the front foot.
Fuller and on middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket.
Quicker and around off. Touch shorter as well Jermaine Blackwood keeps it out.
On middle and turning in. Jermaine Blackwood goes deep in his crease and works it off the bounce to short leg. Marnus Labuschagne fails to collect it and gets hit just near the box.
Drifting on the pads and quicker again. Jermaine Blackwood works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Shorter in length and on middle. Brooks works it to square leg for a single.
Nicely tossed up, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the front foot.
Starts off with a fuller delivery that shapes into middle. Brooks works it towards mid-wicket.
Starc bowls another full delivery on off at 140.2 kph. Brooks drives it back to the bowler.
Pulls his length back slightly, on off. Brooks though is solid in his defence.
Just short of good length and angled across the right-hander. Brooks is aware of the angle and lets it go.
Lands it on a length, on off. Brooks defends it off the middle of his blade.
Touch shorter and angled across the right hander again. Brooks watches it carefully and leaves it. Not much swing for Starc there.
Just short of good length, around off.The ball bounces sharply and Jermaine Blackwood somehow manages to keep it out onto the turf.
Now gets a good swing! Bowls a fullish length and outside off. Jermaine Blackwood goes for a big booming drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Lands it in that channel around off. Jermaine Blackwood presses forward a bit to defend it. The ball though straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Goes back to the fuller length to find some swing, on off. Jermaine Blackwood connects his drive this time but hits it along the ground straight to mid off.
Shortish delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood rides the bounce nicely and blocks it out.
A good-length delivery, outside off. It shapes away nicely as Jermaine Blackwood leaves it.
Wayward delivery from Starc! Bowls a shortish delivery down the leg side and Brooks lets it go.
Down the leg side again and touch on the shorter side. Brooks tries to clip it but misses.
Finds the right line and length finally! On a good length, on off and shaping into the batter. Brooks tries to defend it but gets the inside edge towards fine leg for a single.

OUT! LBW! Starc strikes with the new ball and Jermaine Blackwood gritty knock comes to an end. This is why Starc is so dangerous, if he gets it right, there are few bowlers in the world that can match him. He bowls a fullish delivery that shapes in nicely into Blackwood again. He tries to flick it but is late on his shot and gets hit on the pads. Starc makes a loud appeal and the umpire gives it out straightaway. Blackwood though takes the DRS. The replays roll in and according to Hotspot and Snicko there is no bat there. The Ball Tracking rolls and it shows umpire's call on wicket's hitting. So, the original decision stays and Jermaine Blackwood has to walk off.
Howout: lbw b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Bowls it full and down the leg side. Joshua Da Silva tries to flick it but misses.
Goes fuller and on off. Joshua Da Silva drives it to mid off this time.
Josh Hazlewood lands it on a length and outside off. Brooks leaves it alone.
Lands it on a good length again, on off. Brooks covers the line of the ball and keeps it out nicely.
A fullish delivery and outside off. The ball shapes away a bit as Brooks lets it go.
Touch on the shorter side and on off again. Brooks with a solid block off the back foot.
Oh, that's a brave leave! On a good length and again close to the off pole. This time it very close but Brooks leaves it on height.
Shortish delivery on off. Nasty delivery and Brooks hops and keeps it out onto the turf.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Right through the gate. It's a Mitchell Starc special! Fast and fuller swinging into middle at 145 kph. Joshua Da Silva tries to flick it but ends up playing all around that delivery as the ball sneaks between his bat and pad. Quite a poor shot this from Joshua Da Silva, he is a better batter than this but he is gone now. Aussies are right on top now.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Bowls it fuller and around off. Chase with a positive start as he leans forward and drives it through covers for a couple.
Again that delivery that shapes into the batter. Fuller in length and on off. Chase blocks it out.
Tries a variation ball as he bangs it short and around off. Chase ducks under it.
A fuller delivery on middle. Shapes into him but Chase flicks it nicely past square leg for a couple.
Pulls his length back slightly and around off. Chase dabs it towards the point region.
FOUR! Poor delivery and Brooks gets a boundary! A rare bad delivery from Josh Hazlewood as he drifts on the pads. Brooks just tucks it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Lands it on a length, on off. Brooks with a solid block from his crease.
A fullish delivery on off and Brooks defends it back to the bowler. Looking very solid here, Brooks!
A bouncer that is angled around leg. Brooks watches it till the end and then lets it go.
Serves a fullish delivery and outside off. Good shape away from the batter as Brooks leaves it alone.

FOUR BYES! Josh Hazlewood goes fuller again but drifts down the leg side. Brooks tries to clip it but misses. Carey behind the stumps fails to collect it as the ball bounces just in front of him and goes past his gloves. It races away towards the fence.
On a length and angled across the right hander, Chase leaves it alone.
A fullish delivery on off. Chase fends it off the outside half of his blade to point.
Much fuller on off. Chase defends it calmly back to the bowler.
No run.
Tries to go full and angle it across the right hander but ends up bowling way too wide outside off. Easy leave for Chase.
On a length, on off. Chase defends it right under his eyes. Chase played this over quite well but he needs to keep his concentration levels up right throughout this session.
Back of a length, on off. Brooks keeps it out carefully.
Lovely delivery! Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. The ball seams away after pitching and Brooks also does well to keep his bat inside the line of the ball.
Bowls a full delivery on middle. Brooks flicks it through mid-wicket and the batters run three. Nice shot!
Back of a length and outside off. Chase waits for it and leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and on middle. Chase drives and drives it well but finds the mid on fielder.
Ends the over with a delivery that is just short of good length and around off. Chase makes a careful leave.
A fullish delivery on middle. Brooks flicks it right of mid on for a single.
Lovely delivery! A scrambled seam delivery that pitches around off and is angled across the right-hander. Chase tries to defend it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length and around off. Chase dabs it towards point where Lyon does well to stop it with a dive.
FOUR LEG BYES! Handy runs for the Windies! Back of a length and around leg. Chase tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad and away from the diving leg slip for a boundary.
Goes for a yorker but ends up bowling a low full toss on off. Chase drives it off the bottom of his blade to right of mid off for a single.
Back of a length and around off. It is angled across the right hander and Brooks gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend it.
Lands it on a length, on off. Chase with a solid block from his crease.
Serves a good-length delivery, around off. Chase leaves it alone this time. Good leave!.
Goes a bit straighter and fullish in length as Chase defends it yet again.
Back of a length and drifts down the leg side. Chase lets it go as he watches it till the end.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Chase defends it to mid on.
Cummins with a good-length delivery on off. Chase with a solid block again. Good batting and good bowling as well.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Cameron Green comes back into the attack and picks up his first wicket of the game right away. Green serves this one full and outside off, Shamarh Brooks' eyes lit up as he looks to pounce on it and drive it through covers. The ball just nips away a touch and there's not much feet movement by Brooks. The outside edge is found and Alex Carey takes a simple catch behind the stumps. Australia will now look to clean up the West Indian tail.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Cameron Green

Commentary: Goes full and straight this time, Alzarri Joseph does well to jam it out.

In the air but lands safely. This is dug in short and at the body, Alzarri Joseph looks to take it on but gets a top edge that goes up around square leg. The fielders from short leg and short mid-wicket try to get to it but it falls out of their reach. A single is taken.
Fullish delivery around off, Roston Chase eases it towards mid off.
Pitched up around the off stump, Chase blocks it off the front foot.
Keeps it full but this is sprayed down the leg side. Left alone by Chase.
Tosses it up on a length and turning in from middle and leg, Joseph blocks it off the inside edge towards short leg.
Looped up on the pads and turning down the leg side, Joseph leaves it alone.
Nicely tossed up on off stump, Joseph defends it out.
Flighted delivery around the off stump, this is pushed out towards cover.
Tosses it up a bit wide of the off stump and Alzarri Joseph just lets it through to the keeper.
On a good length and turning in from around middle, Joseph tries to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Fullish length angling on the pads, Roston Chase flicks it away through square leg and picks up a single.
NO BALL! Full and well outside the off stump, Alzarri Joseph leaves it alone for the keeper to collect. Green oversteps and a no ball is called.
Good length over middle and leg, kept out on the leg side.
A bumper over middle stump with not much pace on it. Joseph ducks under it well.
Very full and around off, Joseph forces the drive through covers and picks up a couple of runs.
On a good length around off and nipping away a touch, Joseph watchfully leaves it alone.
Good length again from Green, over off stump and Joseph stays solid in defense.
Turning it in off a good length and into the pads. Chase plays it off the back foot and towards mid-wicket.
This is floated up full and on leg stump, Chase drives it down to long on for a single.
A tad shorter and turning into middle, Alzarri Joseph manages to keep it out.

FOUR LEG BYES! Through everyone! Lovely overspin on that delivery from Lyon as he lands it on a nagging length and around off stump. The ball turns in sharply and goes through the defense of Joseph. the ball clips the flap of the pad and beats Alex Carey behind the stumps before running away into the fence.
Tosses it up on the stumps, Joseph defends it out.
Flighted, around off and Alzarri Joseph leaves it alone.
On a fullish length and on the pads, Roston Chase clips it away in front of mid-wicket and comfortably gets back for the second.
A length ball around middle, Chase blocks it out.
Pitches it up now and bowls it outside off, Chase lets it through to the keeper.
Good length around off, this is defended out on the off side.
Full and straight, Chase punches it straight back at the bowler.
FOUR! A real gift and Roston Chase duly obliges. This is full and angling down the leg side, Chase just tickles it fine and finds the fine leg fence.
A tad bit quicker and around middle, Joseph blocks it out.
Gives it a bit more flight and bowls it around the pads, Alzarri Joseph plays it with soft hands and towards short leg.
Nicely tossed up on leg stump and turning in, Joseph prods forward to defend.
Similar delivery to the previous one, full and turning into the pads, Joseph nudges down behind short leg.
This is tossed up around leg stump and turning further down the leg side, Alzarri Joseph leaves it alone.
On a length and around the pads, Joseph defends it out. Maiden!
Starts off with a pitched-up delivery around the off stump. Roston Chase gets on the front foot and defends it out.
Around the top of off and just nipping back in a touch. Chase covers the line well and makes the block.
This is full and on off, Chase drives it straight towards mid off.
On a good length, close to the off stump and holding its line. Roston Chase makes an assured leave.
Cummins keeps it full and tries to attack the pads but spills it down the leg side. Chase misses the flick as well.

OUT! LBW! The skipper with yet another masterful stroke and West Indies lose their eight wicket. Pat Cummins serves this one a touch fuller on off stump and angles it in. The ball nips back in sharply off the deck and keeps a shade low as well. Roston Chase gets completely caught on the crease and ends up getting pinged right in front. There is a huge appeal and the finger is raised almost instanteanously. No review from Chase and rightly so as ball Tracking shows it was crashing into middle stump. West Indies still need 117 runs to avoid the follow on.
Howout: lbw b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Sharp turn there. This is tossed up on middle and the ball spins into the right-hander. Joseph gets an inside edge on it that goes just past the diving man at short leg. they do get a single.
Tossed up around off stump, Roach pushes it out on the off side.
Flighted, around off stump, Kemar Roach blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! A brilliant reflex catch at first slip by Steven Smith and Kemar Roach has to walk back for a duck. Lovely flight on this one from Nathan Lyon and he pushes this outside the off stump as well. Roach goes for the expansive drive against the turn and ends up getting a thick outside edge. Smith has almost no time react but does well to push back and grab it with both hands to his left. Australia are now just one wicket away from bundling out West Indies.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Tossed up around middle and leg, Jayden Seales blocks it off the front foot.
Nicely flighted around the off pole, Seales leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery around middle. This one nips in a touch and Joseph nudges it onto the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's it, West Indies have been bowled out here! Pat Cummins bangs this one in short over middle and at a good height as well. Alzarri Joseph looks to take it on but mistimes it badly. The ball pops up around the mid-wicket region and David Warner over there takes a simple catch and sprints back to the dressing room which is an indication that Australia will bat again. West Indies are bundled out for 283 and Australia have a mammoth first-innings lead of 315 runs.
Howout: c David Warner b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery on off. Usman Khawaja rides the bounce and blocks it out.
FOUR! David Warner and Australia are underway in style! Short and wide outside off. Warner throws his bat at it and the ball goes towards the backward point fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Gets a thick outside edge but it is still a boundary! Short and outside off again. Warner tries to cut. He gets a thick outside edge that goes over slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Warner punches it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side, around off. Warner rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a couple.
Back of a length and around off. It seams away a bit and Warner dabs it towards the off side.
Serves it on a good length, around off.The ball shapes into the batter a bit and Usman Khawaja makes a watchful leave.
On a good length and wider outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on leg. Usman Khawaja clips it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Just short of good length and on off. Warner blocks it towards the off side.
A fullish delivery on middle. Warner flicks it towards mid-wicket. The fielder there runs to his left and slides to stop it. However, the ball goes through him and couple of runs are taken.
bangs it short and on middle at 141.3 kph. Warner tries to pull it but is hurried by this delivery and just manages to keep it down to the leg side.
Roach lands it on a length, on off. Usman Khawaja defends it towards the off side.
Touch shorter and wider outside off. Usman Khawaja punches it through the backward point region and comes back for the second run.
On the shorter side again, around off. Usman Khawaja pushes it square off the wicket on the off side for a single.
Angles a back-of-a-length delivery on middle. Warner works it to deep square leg and there is a bit of misunderstanding between the batters but an easy single in the end.
On a good length and outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
Keeps it just short of good length with not much movement in the air or off the deck and Usman Khawaja leaves it easily.
Back of a length, on off. Warner dabs it onto the turf.
On the shorter side and around leg. Warner rides the bounce and tries to clip it towards the leg side. However, the ball goes off his body to fine leg and a leg bye is taken.
Just short of good length and on middle. Usman Khawaja defends it towards the leg side.
On a length, on off. Usman Khawaja fends it towards the off side.

Oh, a risky single this! Back of a length, on off. Usman Khawaja defends it towards the off side and sets off for a single. Chase runs froward and tries to fire an under-arm throw at the batter's end but misses and Warner completes the single.
What a delivery! A good-length delivery around off. The ball shapes in nicely at 145.7 kph and Warner gets beaten on the inside edge as he tries to defend it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! An early breakthrough for the Windies and Usman Khawaja departs early. This is a short and widish delivery that seams away a bit. Usman Khawaja is in two minds here whether to play at it or no and gets too late in taking his bat away from the line of the ball. The ball catches the outside edge of his blade and Joshua Da Silva behind the stumps nearly makes a mess of a regulation catch but holds onto it in the end.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary: On a good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne dabs it towards point this time.
On the shorter side and around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it nicely through cover-point for a single.
Shorter and outside off. Warner cuts it to the point fielder. Fails to find the gap there!
Back of a length again, around off. Warner is ready for it as he rides the bounce and dabs it towards the off side.
A length delivery that drifts down the leg side. Marnus Labuschagne lets it go.
Back of a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it away towards the off side.
On the shorter side and around off at 141.1 kph. Marnus Labuschagne defends it with soft hands and guides it behind square on the off side.

That's a good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne is neither forward nor back and just hangs his bat in the air. The ball catches the outside edge of his blade and goes off the bounce to the gully fielder.
On the shorter side, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards the leg side.
Lands it on a length and outside off at 141 clicks as Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
Just short of good length, on off. Warner blocks it solidly right under his eyes.
Back of a length, around leg. Warner tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad towards the leg side. A single taken.
A fullish delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne with a solid block.
Lands a length delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it onto the turf.
Bowls it touch shorter and angles it on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tries to pull it but gets the inside edge onto his body.
Roach with a shortish delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it without much timing towards the off side.
Back of a length and around leg. Warner tries to work it towards the leg side but misses as it is way down the leg side.
A shortish delivery on middle. Warner hops and manages to keep it out towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and on middle at 139.4 kph. Warner flicks it through mid-wicket and the batters take three. Good running.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Nice delivery, on a good length and outside off. The ball shapes away a bit and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
On a good length and angles it on middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards the leg side.
WIDE! Starts off with a wide length delivery, outside off. Warner leaves it alone.
Back of a length and around off. Warner dabs it through point for a single.
On the shorter side, on off. Marnus Labuschagne gets right behind the line of the ball and blocks it out.
On a length and around off. Marnus Labuschagne defends it again towards the off side.
Touch short of good length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce again nicely and blocks it.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to square leg for a single.
A fullish delivery and outside off. Warner knows there is no point in going after such a wide delivery and lets it go.
A fullish delivery on leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to square leg for a single.
Warner will feel he missed out there! A low full toss, outside off. Warner drives it straight to mid off.
Tossed up and outside off. Warner leaves it alone.
Keeps bowling it wider outside off and Warner just decides to let it go again.
Slower through the air and around off. Warner gets forward and blocks it out.
This is poor bowling! He is not even trying to make the batter play. He tosses this up, outside off and Warner leaves it alone.
Fullish delivery, a bit outside the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone.
On a good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne leaves it alone watchfully.
Bowls it a bit fuller and outside off at 120.7 kph. It shapes away a bit and Marnus Labuschagne makes another easy leave.
Goes fuller and on off. Marnus Labuschagne doesn't want to try anything fancy and just blocks it out.
A good-length delivery on off. Not much swing or seam and Marnus Labuschagne just blocks it out.
Holder ends the day with a harmless fullish delivery, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne watches it till the end and is very happy to just leave it alone. It's Stumps on Day 3!
Alzarri Joseph starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery around leg stump. David Warner hops and works it off his hips through square leg for a single.
Good running. This is short and over middle, Marnus Labuschagne pulls it straight towards mid-wicket but the batters scamper through for a quick single.
Goes full now and delivers it outside off, Warner lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length and over off stump, Warner plays it off the back foot and with soft hands onto the off side.
Short of a length and over the stumps, Warner pushes back to defend.
Easy single. This is pitched up around off, David Warner caresses it towards wide mid off for a run.
Holder starts off with a shortish ball well outside off, Warner reaches out and taps it through the point region for a single.
Shorter and angling down leg, Labuschagne pulls it off his hips down to fine leg for one more.
Holder pitches it up in that channel around off stump and David Warner makes an assured leave.
Nicely bowled! Nagging length around the off stump and just seaming away from the left-hander. David Warner stays back and has a little dab at it but gets beaten past the outside edge.
On a good length and around off again, Warner shoulders arms.
Good length again, on off stump and Warner blocks it back onto the deck.
Good placement from Labuschagne. This is overpitched on middle, Labuschagne just clips it away through wide mid on and picks up three runs.
Just a tad shorter and around leg stump, Warner gets caught on the crease as he looks to tuck it away. The ball lobs up after hitting the thigh pads and it is grabbed by the fielder at gully.
On a good length, around middle and leg, Warner stays back and defends it out.
Excellent running! Back of a length and close to the off stump, David Warner stays on the back foot and just bunts it out towards point for a quick single.
Goes full now, at 144.6 clicks and angling it into middle and leg. Labuschagne stays solid in defense.
Around the top of off and at over 142 clicks,  Labuschagnedefends it out from inside his crease.
Back of a length and around off, Warner waits on the back foot and cuts kit late down to third man for a single.
FOUR! Nicely helped around. This is short and angling down leg, Labuschagne is able to get inside the line and plays a controlled pull shot to get it into the fine leg fence.
Good length around off, the ball nips back in off the deck and Labuschagne gets squared off. He gets hit in the groin region but seems to be fine.
A touch fuller and at the stumps, Labuschagne pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter and at the body, Labuschagne jabs it through backward square leg for a single.
Pitches it up now in that channel around off, David Warner lets it through to the keeper.
Around the top of off and pushing the batter onto the back foot. Labuschagne keeps it out.

SIX! This one has flown off the edge! Alzarri Joseph bangs it in short and outside off. The ball climbs up at a good height as Labuschagne looks to pull. Labuschagne gets hurried on and the ball goes off the top edge and flies over the third man fence for a maximum.

NO BALL! Alzarri Joseph is distraught with himself as he picks up a wicket but he has just overstepped and boy, it is very close as well. This is a really good short ball over off stump and just hurrying onto the batter. Marnus Labuschagne looks to awkwardly fend it away and ends up getting it off the top edge and the ball also takes a bit of a helmet on its way. Shamarh Brooks takes a simple catch at gully but it won't count.
Another short ball outside off and Labuschagne is able to just duck under it.
Changes it up now and goes full and outside off, at almost 145 clicks as well. Labuschagne is waiting for the short ball but does manage to leave this one alone.
Just short of a length and outside off, at 144.5 clicks. Labuschagne bends his back to get out of the way of the delivery.
End of an eventful over from Alzarri Joseph. This is pitched up in that channel around off, Labuschagne shoulders arms.
Fullish delivery around off stump and angling away from the left-hander. David Warner watchfully lets it through to the keeper.
Keeps it full and closer to the off pole, Warner yet again leaves it on line.
On a nagging length and around middle, just shaping in a bit. Warner works it away towards mid-wicket and picks up a single.

FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne slashes and slashes hard. This is on a good length and well outside off, Labuschagne throws his hands at it and gets a thick outside edge that flies over the slip cordon and races away into the third man fence.
On a length around off stump, Labuschagne leaves it alone.
Banged in short and over leg stump, Labuschagne plays a controlled pull shot down to fine leg for a run.

Wonderful bit of backing up. This is full and around off, shaping away a touch, Labuschagne gets it off the inner half of the bat and through backward square leg. The batters push hard for two but the throw at the batter's end is a wayward one. Jayden Seales makes a brilliant stop backing up at point and almost forces a run out.
Banged in short and around off at 143.3 clicks, left alone by Labuschagne.
Lovely delivery! Good length, in that channel around off and just holding its line. Labuschagne looks to punch it on the up but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Edged but well short! Keeps it on a good length and around off, Labuschagne looks to block off the back foot but gets an outside edge that falls short of the fielder at gully.

FOUR! Edgy boundary and Labuschagne is looking very tentative out there. Around the top of off, Labuschagne gets pegged back and ends up pushing at it with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the gap between second slip and gully for a boundary.
Fullish length, pushed a bit wider and it is left alone for the keeper to collect.
Roach starts off from around the wicket and angles in a full ball at the stumps. Warner gets forward and punches it towards mid off.
BEATEN! Fullish length, angling it in from around off. The ball just nips away after pitching and goes past the outside edge as Warner looks to cover drive.
Pitched up around off, David Warner drives it sweetly but straight to the man at extra cover.
Keeps it full and at the stumps, Warner keeps it out on the off side.
Full again and angled into middle and leg, Warner pushes it out towards mid on.
Very full and around off stump, David Warner leans on and drives it towards mid off. Kemar Roach starts the day with a maiden.
This is short of length and angled around the hips, Labuschagne hops and looks to tuck it away but gets hit on the thigh pad.

Another excellent bumper from Alzarri Joseph and Marnus Labuschagne ends up on the deck. This is over 140 clicks and over middle stump, Labuschagne tries to bend his back and get out of the way but falls over.
FOUR! Not a good follow-up delivery from Joseph and Labuschagne takes full advantage. This is a half-volley angling down leg, Labuschagne just deflects it away into the fine leg fence.
Length ball on the pads, this is nudged away onto the leg side.
Good length over off stump, Labuschagne hops back and blocks it back on the deck.
On a good length and over off stump, this is pushed away towards silly mid on.
Serves a full delivery angling into off from 'round the wicket at 132 kph. Warner drives it straight to mid off.
Angles a length delivery on middle at 133 kph. Warner works it to mid-wicket this time.
Drifts on the pads and Warner just clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.

Bit of indecision from Warner! Back of a length and around off. Warner makes a late decision to leave and gets a bat on it in the end. The ball goes through the gap between gully and the slip fielder and a single is taken.

FOUR! Roach finds the edge but it does not carry! On a good length and on off. Marnus Labuschagne tries to defend it from his crease and gets a thick outside edge. The ball bounces just in front of th second slip fielder and he fails to collect it cleanly as the ball deflects off his hand towards the third man fence. Marnus Labuschagne is living a charmed life here!
Lands it on a length, on off. Marnus Labuschagne with a solid block from his crease.

Good running! They have run four! Shortish delivery and outside off. Warner cuts it through cover-point. However, the ball is not timed perfectly and the fielder chases it. Warner and Marnus Labuschagne run the first one with intensity and continue the same as they convert three into four runs before the fielder throws it back in towards the batter's end.

FOUR! This time a better timing and it races away towards the boundary! On the shorter side and outside off. Warner plays it late and opens the face of his blade as he guides it through the backward point region for a boundary.
A fullish delivery on middle. Warner clips it to mid-wicket.
Quick single and this will frustrate Joseph and Windies further! Back of a length, on off. Warner dabs it towards the off side for a single.
A shortish delivery down the leg side and Marnus Labuschagne leaves it.
Touch shorter and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it through covers for a couple.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Warner with a solid block from his crease.
Excellent running again! Back of a length, on leg. Warner clips it to deep backward square leg and charges back for the second run.
FOUR! Warner is getting into his groove now! Roach bowls a half-volley, outside off. Warner leans forward and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Pulls his length back slightly, outside off. Warner makes a watchful leave this time.
Back of a length and around off. Warner rides the bounce and pushes it to deep point for a single.
Back-of-a-length delivery angling into middle. Marnus Labuschagne defends it towards the leg side with the angle.
Shortish delivery and outside off. Warner cuts it to deep point for a single.
Back of a length angling into off. Marnus Labuschagne blocks it onto the turf.
On the shorter side and angling into middle. Marnus Labuschagne turns it towards mid-wicket with the angle for a single.
Bowls it short and wide outside off. Warner cuts it to deep point for a single.
A fullish delivery, around off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it left of mid off for a single.
On a length, on off. Nothing much off the deck or in the air and Warner calmly blocks it out.
Starts off with a flatter delivery, around off from 'round the wicket angle. Marnus Labuschagne just goes back and defends it towards the off side for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Warner reverse-sweeps it but does not get much bat on it as he ends up hitting it along the ground to the slip fielder.
Tossed up, on off. Warner drives it to covers.
FOUR! Just past the mid on fielder! A fuller delivery on middle. Warner drives and drives it past the diving fielder at mid on for a boundary.
A shortish delivery, outside off. Warner cuts it towards the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Roston Chase strikes and Warner departs! He is very disappointed and rightly so, he was setting up for a big score here. Chase bowls it slower through the air and on middle from 'round the wicket.  Warner takes a big stride forward and defends it with hard hands. However, the ball goes off the inside half of his blade and loops up in the air right of short leg where Brooks takes a sharp catch. So, West Indies finally have a breakthrough.
Howout: c Shamarh Brooks b Roston Chase

Commentary: FOUR! Beautifully played! Overpitched delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and drives it crisply through mid off for a boundary.
A fullish delivery on off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it gently to the mid off fielder now.
Back of a length and around off. Marnus Labuschagne is cramped for room and he just guides it over the gully fielder for a couple.

FOUR! Fifty for Marnus Labuschagne! His good form continues and the hunger for runs is just amazing. He gets to his fifty with another lovely shot. A full delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne plays a delightful straight drive as the ball goes down the ground for a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to the leg side.
Shortish length again, on off. Marnus Labuschagne rides the bounce and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Smith drives it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Runs are flowing now! Short and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it through covers for a boundary.
Slower through the air and around off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it towards the off side for a single.
Fuller and quicker on off. Smith drives it to long on for a single.
Touch shorter and turning into middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Smith defends it off the front foot.
Goes fuller and on off. Marnus Labuschagne drives it firmly to mid off.
On a length and angling into middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Back of a length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne chops it towards the gully fielder.
A shortish delivery and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne cuts it to deep point for just a single.
Oh, that's an interesting sign! Smith dances down the track to this length delivery, outside off and slaps it to deep point for a single.
Back of a length and around off. Marnus Labuschagne swings across the line but misses.
Tossed up, on off. Smith skips down the track and works it wide of long on for a single.
Shortish delivery and around off. Marnus Labuschagne punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Pushes it quicker and around off. Smith tries to cut it but misses.
Shortish delivery again and outside off. Smith cuts it to backward point this time.
And again! Chase bowls it short and outside off. Smith ends up chopping it to the backward point fielder again.
Pushes it quicker and outside off. Smith fails to connect his cut shot this time.
FOUR! Brilliant placement! Short delivery angling into middle and leg. Nice comfortable height for Marnus Labuschagne and he pulls it towards the backward square leg fence for a boundary.
Bowls another short delivery on middle. Marnus Labuschagne pulls it to deep square leg for a single this time.
Goes fuller and on middle. Smith whips it off his pads to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Holder bowls it short and around leg. Marnus Labuschagne tries to pull it but misses.
Full and on middle. Marnus Labuschagne works it to square leg for a single.
Another bumper from Holder. On middle at a awkward height for Smith this time. He tries to sway away from the line of the ball and tries to play a ramp shot but misses. The lead is 447 now!

SIX! Lovely use of the feet by Marnus Labuschagne. Tossed up around middle, Labuschagne skips down the track and lofts it straight back over the bowler's head for a maximum. The lead goes past 450 now.
Turning into the pads off a length, Labuschagne nudges it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Tossed up, full and straight, Steven Smith advances and hits it down the ground for a couple of runs.
On the shorter side and around the pads, Smith works it off the back foot towards square leg for one.
Labuschagne looks to step out again and Chase just fires it in. Labuschagne mistimes the slog badly and gets it nowhere.
Flatter one around off, Labuschagne edges it down towards point and picks up a single.
Full and angling down leg, Labuschagne flicks it towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
A bit of T20 cricket going on. Jason Holder goes for a cutter and serves it on a length around off stump. Steven Smith looks to get inside the line and scoop it over short fine leg but misses.
Short and outside off, Smith reaches out and cuts it uppishly to the right of the man at third man for a single.
Banged in short and over off stump, Labuschagne pulls it through mid-wicket for one more.
Goes full and angles it into middle and off, Steven Smith jams it out towards mid on.
Slower one, at just 97.6 clicks and on a good length outside off, this is caressed away square of the wicket to deep point for a single.
Kraigg Brathwaite brings himself back into the attack and starts with a round-arm delivery from around the wicket. This is flatter and quicker on middle, Smith hits it down the ground for a single.
Full and angled across the off stump, Labuschagne reverses it towards point.
Floated up on off stump, Labuschagne pushes it through mid off for a single.
Slightly shorter and around off, Steven Smith rocks back and punches it through covers for one more.
On the shorter side and on leg stump, Labuschagne waits for it and works it away through mid-wicket for yet another single.

Well in but good work in the deep as well. Tossed up on leg stump, Steven Smith clips it away through mid-wicket and looks for two straight away. The fielder in the deep runs around and scores a direct hit at the bowler's end. It is checked by the third umpire and the replays show that Labuschagne was well in.
FOUR! Thumped! Pitched up on leg stump, Marnus Labuschagne backs away a bit and just muscles it over wide mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back! Slower one, a full toss and around leg stump, Labuschagne shuffles past the leg stump and drags it with power in front of mid-wicket for yet another boundary.
This is short and over the stumps, pulled away through square leg for a single.
Short again and over off stump, Steven Smith gets inside the line of the ball and pulls it towards fine leg for one.
This is banged in halfway down the pitch and over the stumps, Labuschagne plays a tennis-like pull shot and mistimes it around square leg. They get a single.
A length ball angled well down the leg side. This is left alone for gthe keeper to collect.

Labuschagne gets a bit lucky there. This is fired in around leg stump, staying a bit low. Labuschagne looks to back away and pull but gets an inside edge onto the pads and the ball just goes past the leg stump.
Quicker and shorter around off, this is played off the back foot through covers for a single.
Around middle and leg, Steven Smith works it away through square leg for one more.
Dragged down, quicker and angled across the off stump. Labuschagne looks to stay put and just reverse it fine but misses.
Short again and around leg stump, Labuschagne tucks it away past square leg for a single..
A tad shorter and outside off, Steven Smith rocks back and eases it through the cover region for yet another single.
Quicker one, slanted across the off stump, Smith walks across and wrists it away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Chase goes full and wide and angles kit a long way across the batter. Labuschagne looks to drag this one leg side but toe-ends it towards the bowler.
Full and wide again, this time Labuschagne is able to broom it away towards deep mid-wicket for a single. Just one shot away now Labuschagne from yet another century.
A full toss now outside off, Steven Smith just shows the full face of the bat and eases it towards wide long off for a single.
Nicely held back by Roston Chase. This is full and wide, angling across but a low slower through the air, Labuschagne looks for the sweep but is well beaten.
Very full and outside off, Labuschagne reaches out and maneuvers it through extra cover for a run.

FOUR! Cheeky but skillful as well from Marnus Labuschagne. Quicker one, fired in full and around off, Labuschagne plays the reverse paddle and the ball just runs away into the third man fence. He moves on to 99 now.

FOUR! Take a bow, Marnus Labuschagne! Follows up the double-hundred in the first innings with a sensational century here, only the eighth man in Test history to achieve this feat. This is quicker and on the pads, Labuschagne just deflects it fine and the ball races away into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Flatter one around off, Labuschagne punches it off the back foot through covers for a single.
shorter and around off, Steven Smith looks to punch it through covers but doesn't find the gap.
And again! Quicker one around off, Smith pushes it out on the off side.
This is on middle, Steven Smith waits for it and works it in front of square on the leg side for a single. The lead moves on to 497 runs and that will be Lunch on Day 4!

Starts off with a full delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite leans forward and pushes it through covers nicely. The fielder manages to keep it inside the ropes but the batters take three. West Indies and Kraigg Brathwaite are underway!
Bowls a back-of-a-length delivery and down the leg side. Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul dabs it towards cover-point.
A fullish delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it solidly towards the off side.
Seves a good-length delivery, around off. The ball seams away a bit after pitching and Tagenarine Chanderpaul does well to keep his bat inside the line of the ball.
Good delivery again but well left! Starc with a good-length delivery, around off. The ball shapes away a bit as Tagenarine Chanderpaul keeps his bat again inside the line of the ball.
Lands it on a length, on off. The ball seams back in and catches the inside edge of Kraigg Brathwaite's blade and it goes onto hit his pads.
Back of a length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go.
Back of a length angling into middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to fine leg for a single.
Nicely angled across the batter! Lands it just short of good length and on off. The ball goes across Tagenarine Chanderpaul and he does well to not commit to the shot.
On a length and way too wider outside off this time. Easy leave for Tagenarine Chanderpaul.
Bangs it short and around leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul is alert and just ducks under it.
Back of a length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Keeps it on the shorter side again and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite watches it carefully and lets it go.
A fullish delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it with soft hand towards cover-point and comes back for the second run.
On a good length and angled across the right hander. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone. Starc needs to make him play here.
On a length and around leg. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
A fullish delivery on leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
On a good length and around off angling across the young batter. Tagenarine Chanderpaul though is aware of the fact and does not take his bat out to chase it.
Touch on the shorter side and outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go again.
Back of a length, on leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul works it to square leg.
This is again bowled on good length and angled across the left-hander. However, it is too wide and is an easy leave for Tagenarine Chanderpaul.
Bowls a short delivery on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pulls it but does not time it perfectly. The ball goes in the air and falls way short of the fine leg fielder. A single is taken.

Back of a length and this one nips back into middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite gets beaten as he tries to clip it and the ball hits high on his pads and loops up to point. Catch is taken and there is excitement in the crowd but the players know there is no bat there.
On a length, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out.
A fullish delivery, around off at 142.3 kph. Tagenarine Chanderpaul with a solid block off the front foot.
Lovely delivery! Starc serves it on a good length and around off. The ball shapes away nicely and Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend it.
Short and way outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Back of a length and comes closer to the off pole. Tagenarine Chanderpaul is ready and blocks it out.
Serves a good-length delivery on off at 142.6 kph. Tagenarine Chanderpaul though is not really worried about it and just makes a solid block.
A fullish delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it straight to mid off this time.
Pulls his length back a touch, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back to the bowler.
A fullish delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it past the bowler to mid off.
A good-length delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite with a solid block from his crease.
Shortish delivery and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and dabs it towards the off side.
On a good length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite plays it very late and with soft hands towards the off side.
Serves it on a length, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out solidly.
A fullish delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul is as solid as ever.
Nice bouncer but equally well played! Starc fires a bouncer on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul watches it till the end and sways away from the line of the ball.
Goes fuller and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul drives it to mid off this time.
On a length and angling into leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul tries to clip it but misses. The ball brushes his thigh pads and goes back to Alex Carey behind the stumps.
Goes fuller and on off at 142.3 kph. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it with a solid stride forward.
Tossed up, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets well forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Slower through the air and Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Touch on the shorter side and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Touch on the shorter side and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite opens the face of his blade a bit and guides it towards backward point for a couple.
On the shorter side and turning into middle. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it left of mid off for a single.
On a good length and angling in from 'round the wicket. He pitches it around off and Kraigg Brathwaite pokes at it but gets beaten on the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length angling into off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
A fullish delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it square off the wicket on the off side.
Beats Kraigg Brathwaite again! On a good length and angles it around off. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend it from his crease but gets beaten as the ball straightens a bit after pitching.
A fullish delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to cover-point for a single.
Serves a fullish delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it off the front foot.
Bowls a full delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on off. It turns into the right hander and he defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Turning into middle again. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it with soft hands towards the leg side.
Bowls it a touch shorter and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it past short leg for a single.
A fuller delivery on off at 94.6 kph. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets a good stride forward and defends it towards the off side.
Bit slower through the air, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it off the front foot again.
Starc comes from around the wicket and angles in a short one at the body, Brathwaite plays it off the back foot and onto the leg side.
This is full, it is the cross-seamer and bowled around middle, Brathwaite clips it away 'round the corner and picks up a single.
Switches to over the wicket for the left-hander and bowls it full and on the pads. Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it down to fine leg and rotates the strike.
On a good length and angling it in from outside off. The ball stays low and goes under the bat of Brathwaite.
Good length again, angling in and closer to the off pole. Brathwaite gets pushed on the back foot and ends up playing inside the line of the ball.
Full and straight, at 140.2 clicks, Brathwaite blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up delivery on off stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul presses forward to defend.
Tosses it up again around the off stump, Chanderpaul defends it towards silly point.
Flights it up a bit now and keeps it around off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul solidly keeps it out off the front foot.
Floated up, on off stump and this is pushed out gently towards the off side.
Drifts it on to middle stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul prods and keeps it out.
Short and turning away from off stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul rocks back to cut but finds the man at cover-point.
Josh Hazlewood comes back into the attack and starts off with a fullish delivery outside off stump. This one seams away and Brathwaite leaves it alone.
A length ball, angling it into middle, Brathwaite watchfully keeps it out.
Excellent running. This is a bit fuller and around middle, Brathwaite pushes it gently towards mid on and sets off for the single right away.
FOUR! A lovely controlled shot from Tagenarine Chanderpaul. This is short and over leg stump, Chanderpaul gets on top of the bounce and pulls it behind backward square leg for a boundary.

Banged in short again and over leg stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul hooks it away with sweet timing but Travis Head at deepish backward square leg dives down well to his left and makes the stop. A single is taken.
Pitches it up now on middle, Brathwaite punches it out to mid off.
Nicely drifted into middle and leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul watches it carefully and keeps it out.

BEATEN! Lovely delivery from Nathan Lyon. This is flighted, on a nagging length and close to the off pole. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to block behind the line but the ball just grips and goes past the outside edge.
Tosses it up now around middle and leg, Chanderpaul keeps it out.
Fuller and on middle, this is driven through mid on for an easy single.
On a length and at the stumps, Brathwaite blocks it out.
Tossed up around off and turning it in, Brathwaite presses forward and defends it out.
Hazlewood comes from around the wicket and angles in a fullish delivery onto the off stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out on the off side.
Nicely bowled! Keeps it full and just bowls it a touch wider, the ball is angled in but leaves the batter who ends up playing inside the line of the ball.
On a length and angling in from around off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul watches it closely and makes a good leave.

NO BALL AND FOUR! Good length around off and the ball just seams away off the deck. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pushes at it and gets an outside edge that goes to the right of the diving fielder at a widish third slip. That one did carry but it runs away into the fence. Hazlewood did overstep so even if it was caught, it wouldn't have mattered.
Good length around the top of off stump, Chanderpaul stays solid in defense.
Banged in short and angling it around the body, Tagenarine Chanderpaul hooks it down to fine leg and picks up a single.
Good length, hitting the top of middle, Brathwaite blocks it off the front foot.
Tosses it up now on a shorter length and on off stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul waits for it and eases it onto the off side.
Floats it up now on off stump, Chanderpaul defends it off the front foot.
A tad bit shorter and turning away from off stump, Chanderpaul rocks back and cuts it towards point.
Nicely drifted onto middle and leg, Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it with a straight bat.
And again! Floated around middle and leg, Chanderpaul defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Tentative from Tagenarine Chanderpaul but he does play it well in the end. Lyon holds it back a bit and tosses it up outside off stump. Chanderpaul prods forward to defend but pushes onto the back foot and cuts it at the last moment past the slip fielder and into the fence.
Back of a length over middle stump, Brathwaite hops and dabs it down towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length, close to the off pole and Tagenarine Chanderpaul just plays inside the line of this one.
Goes full now and keeps it around the fourth stump line, Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Back of a length and around off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul stylishly punches it off the back foot and through the cover region for a couple of runs.
On a good length and around the off stump, left alone for the keeper to collect.
Full and outside off, shaping away a touch. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets on the front foot and squeezes it through backward point for a couple of runs more.
This is tossed up on a shorter length and turning into the off stump. Brathwaite defends it off the back foot.
Flighted, a bit wide of the off stump, Brathwaite caresses it behind point but the fielder makes a good stop.
FOUR! Tossed up full and on off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite just stands tall and hoicks it away through wide mid on and collects a boundary.
Floated up on leg stump, this is eased down to long on for a single.
A bit quicker and flatter, turning away sharply from around off stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul looks to pad it away but is beaten.
Lovely delivery! Nicely drifted in from around off, drawing the batter forward, the ball turns away and beats the outside edge.
Cameron Green comes into the attack for the first time in this innings and serves a full ball at the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it away in front of mid-wicket and picks up a single.
This is banged in short and around the body, Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets on top of it and pulls it behind square leg for a run.
Pretty easy going for the Windies openers at the moment. This is floated up on the pads, Brathwaite flicks it away through backward square leg and comes back for the second with ease.
Back of a length and angling into the body. Brathwaite hops and manages to nudge it towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
A touch fuller now and at the stumps, Tagenarine Chanderpaul pushes it out towards mid on.
Good length angling down leg, Tagenarine Chanderpaul flicks it down to fine leg for an easy single.
This is pushed through a bit quicker and outside off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul presses forward but leaves it alone.
Flighted up on off stump, Chanderpaul blocks it off the front foot.
This is around off and a bit flatter, Tagenarine Chanderpaul taps it past the man at silly point.
Tossed up on off stump, Chanderpaul plays at it with soft hands and in front of silly point.
A bit of an extra bounce but Tagenarine Chanderpaul deals with it well. Tosses it up on a length and the ball turns away sharply from off stump. Chanderpaul keeps it down in front of silly point.
Flighted delivery around off, this is blocked off the front foot.
On the shorter side, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite tucks it towards fine leg as he rides the bounce and takes a single. 50 partnership is up!
Tad short and on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul punches it through covers for a couple.
Short and tad wide too outside off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul cuts it hard but straight to the point fielder.
Angles a length delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it from his crease.
Serves a fullish delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul drives it to covers for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is as solid as ever.
Tossed up, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it towards cover-point this time.
Nice flighted delivery on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul with a good stride forward again and blocks it out.
Pushes it quicker on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Slower through the air and around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it with soft hand towards the off side.
Nice delivery again, around that off pole but Tagenarine Chanderpaul is looking very solid as he defends it comfortably again.
FOUR LEG BYES! Green drifts down the leg side and Kraigg Brathwaite tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad and runs away towards the fine leg fence.
On a length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Serves another good-length delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend it but the ball goes off the thick outside edge off the bounce to Smith at second slip.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to mid on for a single.
Short and down the leg side. Tagenarine Chanderpaul tries to pull it away but misses.
Green with another shortish delivery, around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul lets it go. Nothing much happening for the Aussies at the moment.
Tossed up on off. Kraigg Brathwaite heaves it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air and around off. The ball turns away and Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.

This young man is showing some good skills. This is around off and touch slower again. Tagenarine Chanderpaul takes his front foot forward and very cleverly defends it with the angled blade and with soft hands as well.
On off and quicker. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out.
Pushes it quicker and flatter on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it solidly again.
On the shorter side, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and blocks it out.
Shorter and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it to the point fielder.
Serves a length delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is solid again with his front foot block.
Bangs it short and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks under it.
Back of a length and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Good shot! Short and wide outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite throws his bat at it and the ball flies over the point region for a boundary.
Tossed up and around off. The ball turns away and Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it alone.
Loopy delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul with a solid block off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it off the front foot again.
Slower through the air and on middle at 89.7 kph. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it again this time towards short fine leg.
Changes his pace again and bowls it quicker and on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out.
Slower through the air and around off. Good turn and loop on this delivery as Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it.
Back of a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne clips it to backward square leg for a single.
NO BALL! Marnus Labuschagne oversteps and bowls it on a length, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it.
Touch on the shorter side, around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul tries to punch it but does not get much timing on it.
On the shorter side again on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul with a solid block.
Good delivery! Lands it on a good length and angled across the left hander. Tagenarine Chanderpaul keeps his bat inside the line of the ball and lets it go.
On a length, on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul defends it off the back foot.
A fullish delivery, around off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul drives it without much timing to the off side.
Pitches on middle and it turns in. Kraigg Brathwaite goes back and defends it towards the leg side.
Tossed up on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite fends it off the front foot now.

FOUR! Nice shot but Lyon will not mind it. Tossed up, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite sweeps and sweeps it well through the backward square leg region for a boundary. It also provides an opportunity to Lyon to bring those players on the leg side into play.
Tossed up, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite fends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Flighted delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite reaches the pitch of the ball and drives it firmly down the ground for a boundary.
Pushes it quicker and flatter on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite with a solid block.
Bangs it short and on middle. Tagenarine Chanderpaul is surprised and ducks under it as he nearly falls onto the ground.
On a good length and on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it back to the bowler.
NO BALL! Serves a good-length delivery outside off. It seams away and Tagenarine Chanderpaul leaves it. Marnus Labuschagne oversteps again.
On the shorter side, on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it out solidly.
Bangs it short and around leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pulls it to fine leg for a single.
NO BALL! A full delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it wide of mid on for a single. Marnus Labuschagne has overstepped again.
Fullish delivery and on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it back to the bowler.
Shortish delivery and around leg. Tagenarine Chanderpaul pulls it through the mid-wicket region. Three taken.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tossed up around middle and leg, Tagenarine Chanderpaul plays a beautiful on drive, against the turn and gets it through wide mid on for a boundary.
Flights it up on off stump, Tagenarine Chanderpaul blocks it towards silly point.
Tossed up on off stump, Chanderpaul keeps it out.
Floated up around the off stump, Chanderpaul presses forward and blocks it in front of silly point.
A tossed up delivery on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul drives it to mid off this time.
Lyon tosses this up nicely on off. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets a good stride forward and blocks it solidly. West Indies are 84/0 at Tea on Day 41

Bump catch! Mitchell Starc starts from around the wicket and serves a yorker-length delivery around off. Kraigg Brathwaite stays deep in his crease and seems to have bunted it into the hands of the man at gully. The Aussies are interested and the umpires do go upstairs. The soft signal is not out and the replays show that the ball clearly came off the bat and hit the turf before popping up.
A cross-seamer now, full and angled into off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out.
A touch fuller and around off stump, Brathwaite solidly keeps it out.
Pitches it up now and angles it in from outside off, Brathwaite pushes it out towards cover.
Goes for the yorker now and nails it on off stump, Brathwaite is equal to it and digs it out on the off side.
On a length and trying to angle it into the pads but spills it down leg. This is left alone and Starc starts the session off with a maiden.
Green starts from around the wicket and bangs in a short ball over off stump. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets his hands out in front and hooks it behind square leg for a single.
Switches to over the wicket now and serves it on a good length around off, Brathwaite hops but keeps it down on the off side.

FOUR! Nicely driven and Kraigg Brathwaite brings up 5,000 Test runs, what a stellar achievement from the skipper! This is full and straight, Brathwaite punches it on the up and to the left of mid on. The fielder over there tries to chase it down but the ball wins the race.
Back of a length, close to the off stump, Brathwaite hangs back and dabs it down behind point.
Excellent fielding. Full and straight again, this is driven straight to the man at mid on as they look for the run. Josh Hazlewood picks it up quickly and almost catches the batter out.
A bumper now over the stumps, Brathwaite ducks under it.
This is on a length and well, outside the off stump, left alone by the batter.
That one took off! A cross-seamer from Starc, at over 142 clicks and on a good length around off. The ball just shoots off the deck and Alex Carey takes it around chest height.
Length ball around off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul pushes it towards cover.
Served on a good length and angled into middle, Chanderpaul gets across and blocks it back onto the deck.
A short ball at around 141 clicks and attacking the body. Tagenarine Chanderpaul fends it away towards backward square leg and picks up a single.
Starc comes in from around the wicket and angles in a good-length ball around off stump. Brathwaite gets cramped a bit but manages to keep it down around gully.
This is full and around off, Tagenarine Chanderpaul drives it on the up towards mid off.
Banged in short and at a good height, Tagenarine Chanderpaul does well to keep the hook shot down and plays it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
FOUR! Exquisitely driven by Kraigg Brathwaite. This is pitched up around off stump, Brathwaite just leans on and plays a checked-drive through extra cover and finds the fence.
NO BALL! Good length, close to the off pole and it is kept out by Brathwaite. A no ball is called as Cameron Green has overstepped.

Nicely driven once again and the skipper brings up yet another classy half-century! This is fuller and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it square of the wicket through covers and comes back for the third with ease.
Back of a length and around off stump, Chanderpaul bloks it out.

A good bumper this from Green, angling in around the helmet of the batter. Tagenarine Chanderpaul is able to get inside the line of the ball and hooks it towards fine leg for a single. The 100 is also up for West Indies.
Full and straight, Tagenarine Chanderpaul forces the on drive back past the bowler. Marnus Labuschagne from mid off chases it down and is able to keep it in play. They get three.
Good length, angling into the body, Brathwaite tucks it away off his hips and behind square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! The runs are now flowing for West Indies. This is short and well outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite throws his hands at it and gets a thick outside edge up and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off stump, Brathwaite keeps it down on the off side.
A tad shorter and angling in from around off, Brathwaite gets a bit cramped up but manages to keep it out.
Full and straight, this is punched back towards the bowler.

'Catch it,' is the call but Mitchell Starc fails to hang on to a very difficult chance. A lovely bumper from Cameron Green around the helmet of the batter. Tagenarine Chanderpaul takes the hook shot once again and this time gets a top edge on it. The ball flies down wide of the man at third man. Starc runs around and dives to his right but the ball hits his palms hard and pops out. A single is taken and Green is absolutely livid.
A quick bumper now over the stumps, Brathwaite ducks under it.

Lovely delivery! Cameron Green looks a bit fired up at the moment. Serves this one on a good length and around off stump. The ball just zips through off the deck and hizzes past the outside edge of Brathwaite's willow.
