Back of a length and around middle, Brathwaite tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Fullish length around off, Brathwaite punches it out on the off side.
A tad shorter and at the body, Brathwaite hops and nudges it onto the leg side for one.

Sweetly timed but it will be cut off. This is pitched up around off, Brathwaite stands tall and punches it through extra cover. Marnus Labuschagne from covers races after it and saves a run for his side.

Rides the bounce does Tagenarine Chanderpaul. Starc stays 'round the wicket to the left-hander as well and angles across a short ball. Chanderpaul throws his hands at it and is able to hit it over the gully region for a couple of runs.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! The change of angle has worked for Mitchell Starc! This is short of a length and around off, cramping the batter up. Tagenarine Chanderpaul gets pegged on the back foot and looks to cut from close to the body. In the end, there's not much room and Chanderpaul gets an inside edge as the ball goes on to disturb the stumps. The third umpire checks it just to confirm if Starc's back leg wasn't outside the tramline when he delivered the ball and everything seems fine. Australia finally have the breakthrough and it will be interesting now as to how the Windies react.
Howout: b Mitchell Starc

Commentary: Back to over the wicket now and serves a full ball around off stump, Shamarh Brooks eases it out towards cover.
Fullish length on off stump, Brooks pushes it out back past the bowler and gets off the mark with a quick single.
A bit of an extra bounce! Good length, angling into the body from around the stumps. Brathwaite looks to defend but the ball pops up a bit more. Brathwaite is able to keep it down though.
A length ball now on the pads, Brooks eases it towards mid on.
Good shot and equally well stopped. This is full and on off stump, Shamarh Brooks drives it straight back but Cameron Green does well on the follow-through to make the stop.
Banged in short and over off stump, Brooks ducks under it.
Pitches it up now around off stump, Brooks stays solid in defense.
A length ball around middle and leg, Shamarh Brooks works it away through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On a good length and angling in from around off, Brooks plays inside the line of the ball.
FOUR! Lovely touch from Brathwaite. This is on a good length and outside off, Brathwaite waits for it and taps it past backward point for a boundary.
Goes a bit fuller now and attacks the stumps, Brathwaite does well to keep it out as the ball stayed a bit low.
Around the top of off, Brathwaite opens the face of the blade and eases it towards point for a single.
A fullish delivery on off. Brooks blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Lovely classical shot! Overpitched delivery on off. Brooks leans forward and creams it past mid off for a boundary.
On a good length and outside off. Brooks watches it till the end and lets it go.
Tosses it up, around off and Brathwaite pushes it out towards covers for a single.
Nicely driven but straight to the man. This is floated up around off stump, Shamarh Brooks nails the extra cover drive but finds the fielder.
Quicker one, on a nagging length and around off, Brooks edges it down to the right of the man at first slip.
FOUR! That is a glorious shot! Tossed up, full and outside off, Shamarh Brooks just leans on, opens the face of the blade and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Around off and turning in, Brooks blocks it out.
Nicely flighted around off stump and Brooks is able to defend it out.
Serves it on a good length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite has a poke at it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Touch short of good length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it from his crease.
Serves a length delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Goes fuller and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it straight to the short mid on fielder.
Shortish delivery on off. However, Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce nicely and keeps it out towards the off side.

Has that brushed the top of the bail? Serves it on a good length, on off. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Kraigg Brathwaite's blade as he tries to defend. The ball brushes the bail along the way placed between the off pole and the middle one and goes back to the keeper. Unfortunately, for the Aussies the bail does not move!
A  flatter delivery on off. Brooks blocks it out.
On the shorter side and around off. Brooks goes back and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Brooks presses forward and defends it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Great catch by Smith and Australia have got their second wicket! This is classy bowling from Lyon. He tosses this one and pitches it just short of full length. The key here is that he bowls it wider outside off. Brooks pushes forward to defend it and gets an outside edge. The ball goes towards right of first slip and Smith dives to his right to pull off a superb catch.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Tossed up and around off again. Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the front foot.

A big appeal for a caught behind! However, the umpire is not interested. After a discussion with his players, Cummins take the review. The replays roll in and the after the results shown by Hotspot and Snicko, the third umpire has made a decision that it is NOT OUT! Coming to the ball, it is flatter and quicker around off. Touch short as well and Jermaine Blackwood who hangs on the back foot gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend it.
FOUR! Good soft hands! Back of a length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite waits for it and plays it very late as he guides it through backward point for a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it to fine leg for a single.

Jermaine Blackwood has been given out LBW but he has taken the DRS straightaway. Height looks an issue here. The replays roll in and the Snicko shows no bat here. The Ball Tracking rolls and it shows that the ball is going over the stumps. So, the decision will be reversed and it is NOT OUT! Coming to the ball, it is a back-of-a-length delivery angling into middle and leg. Jermaine Blackwood tries to clip it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Shortish delivery and outside off. Jermaine Blackwood lets it go.
Another one that is rapped up on the pads! Touch shorter and angling into middle and leg again. Blackwood tries to work it towards the leg side and misses to get hit on the pads again.
Some chin music here! Good accurate short delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood gets it at an awkward height and Blackwood somehow manages to defend it onto the turf.
Tossed up and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Loopy delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Good shot! A fuller delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite sweeps and sweeps it well through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up and pitched around off. It turns in and Kraigg Brathwaite fends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite with a block off the front foot.
Pitches it on off and the ball turns into middle. Kraigg Brathwaite waits for it and plays it with soft hands towards short leg.
A good-length delivery and around off. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood punches it left of the bowler.

Shortish delivery angling into the body. Jermaine Blackwood gets into an awkward position and takes his eyes off the ball. In the end somehow manages to get a bat on that ball and the ball goes off the top half of his blade behind square on the leg side. A runs is taken.
On the shorter side again and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite steers it towards third man for a single.
A fullish delivery on middle. Jermaine Blackwood goes for a big drive but gets no timing on it as the ball loops up in the air a bit and falls short of mid on.
Short of good length and on off. Jermaine Blackwood rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Tossed up, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot nicely.
FOUR! Kraigg Brathwaite has really played this sweep shot well today. Tossed up on off. Kraigg Brathwaite kneels and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Slower through the air and wider outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it wiht soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball runs through the third man region and three runs are taken.
Tossed up, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood tries to drive it but misses.
Flighted delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood gets well forward and blocks it.
Pitches it on off and Jermaine Blackwood goes back and turns it to the leg side.
Serves a good-length delivery that nips back on from middle. Kraigg Brathwaite is completely beaten by it as the ball brushes his pads on its way to the keeper. Just over the stumps.
On a good length and around off. The ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Kraigg Brathwaite's blade as he tries to defend it.
On a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the leg side.
Bangs it short and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks under it.
Serves it full and angles it on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to mid-wicket this time.
Lands it on a length, on off. It nips back in and Kraigg Brathwaite fends it off the inside half of his blade.
A flatter delivery, around off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the front foot.
Shorter length and on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it by going deep in his crease.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short and outside off. Jermaine Blackwood goes back and cuts it through point for a much-needed boundary. This will increase his confidence.
Turning into middle at a fullish delivery at a fullish length. Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the leg side off the front foot.

Nicely tossed up and around off. Jermaine Blackwood tries to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball turns in and bounce to hit it on the pads. There is a small appeal for an LBW but the impact is clearly outside off.
Outside off and touch shorter as Jermaine Blackwood goes back and blocks it out.
Back of a length and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to backward point for a single.
Angles a shortish delivery on leg. Blackwood clips it to fine leg where the fielder in the deep does well to dive to his right and keep it to just two.
Shortish length, on off. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it off the back foot.
Angles a length delivery on the hips. Jermaine Blackwood tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his thigh pad towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken.
Keeps this delivery on the shorter side and around off. Kraigg Brathwaite calmly opens the face of his blade to steer it to point for a single.

Oh, this one keeps low! Starc angles a length delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood hopes in hope that it will bounce but the ball keeps low and in the end, Blackwood just manages to block it off the bottom of his blade.
Touch shorter and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it towards the off side.
Tossed up, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery, outside off. Incites the batter to drive it and Blackwood goes for a big drive. However, the ball just beats the outside edge of his blade.
Beaten again! This is a tossed up delivery again, wider outside off. Jermaine Blackwood tries to defend it but this one goes straight again with the arm and ends up beating Blackwood again.
Shortish length on middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it toward the leg side off the back foot.

Nicely bowled again! Gives it a good flight again. Pitches it just short of full length and Jermaine Blackwood presses forward to defend. However, the ball goes straight again and beats the outside edge of Blackwood's blade.
On a fullish length and angling it into off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Good length, around the off stump, Brathwaite hangs back and steers it down to third man for a single.
A length ball angled into middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Beaten! This is on a nagging length and angled in from outside off. Then ball straightens a bit and keeps low, beating the inside edge of Blackwood's bat.
Good length around middle, punched away towards mid on for Blackwood.
A bit shorter and around leg stump, Jermaine Blackwood works it off his hips towards fine leg and picks up a single.
Tossed up well outside off, Jermaine Blackwood gets well forward and keeps it out on the off side.
Flighted delivery around middle, Blackwood eases it towards mid-wicket.
On a length and around middle, Jermaine Blackwood knocks it down to long on for a single.
Flatter one around middle, Brathwaite punches it through mid on and picks up one more.
Nicely drifted, full and outside off, this one goes straight on and Blackwood leaves it alone.
Nicely tossed up outside off, Jermaine Blackwood drives it along the ground and towards wide mid off.
Fuller one angling into middle stump, Brathwaite keeps it out without any fuss.
Short and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite reaches out and taps it through backward point for a single and moves into the 90s as well.
FOUR! A shot of real authority from Jermaine Blackwood. Starc looks to go full and straight but he gets pummeled down the ground for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off stump, Blackwood hops and keeps it down.
An attempted short ball, dragged down the leg side and the keeper does well to collect it low to his left.
A good bumper now, around off stump and going through at a good height. Jermaine Blackwood sways away from the line of the ball.
Tosses it up full and outside off, Brathwaite prods forward to defend on the off side.
Beaten! Gives it a nice rip and serves it on a nagging length outside off. Brathwaite looks to block but the ball turns in and bats the outside edge.
Quicker one, turning in sharply from the off stump, Brathwaite just about keeps it out.
Tossed up around off, Brathwaite pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated up full and around off, this is played towards mid off.

Top delivery from Travis Head. This is flighted on a length and around off stump. The ball grips and bounces a bit extra as well. Brathwaite looks to block but is taken aback and the ball comes off the gloves but also goes behind short leg.
This is banged in short and over the stumps, Jermaine Blackwood ducks under it.

Just short! A hostile short ball from Cameron Green and is angled at the body. Jermaine Blackwood awkwardly tries to fend it away but gets it off the toe end. The ball lands in front of a diving David Warner at leg gully.

Good length, just angling down leg. Jermaine Blackwood looks to flick but misses and the ball seems to have flicked the pads on its way to the keeper. There is a huge appeal for caught behind but the umpire remains unmoved. Cameron Green seems certain about it and Pat Cummins does take the review. Both hotspot and UltraEdge show that there's no bat involved and the ball did come off the pads. Australia lose a review as well.
Good length around leg stump, nudged away towards mid-wicket for one.
Shorter and outside off, this is guided away behind point for one more.
Banged in short and over middle, Jermaine Blackwood jumps onto the back foot to keep it down.
Tossed up on middle, this is driven through mid on for a single.
Flighted, outside off, Jermaine Blackwood presses forward and caresses it square of the wicket towards sweeper cover and races back for the second.
And again! Floated up outside off, Blackwood drives it along the ground and to the left of the sweeper in the deep for yet another brace.
Quicker one, outside off, Blackwood edges it down with soft hands towards gully.
Outside off, Blackwood drives it through extra cover for a single.
Tossed up around off, Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
FOUR! Banged in short and at the body, just angling down leg a bit. Jermaine Blackwood looks to hook but ends up playing it really fine. The ball runs away into the fine leg fence.
On a good length and over middle and leg, Blackwood keeps it out.
Shorter and around the hips, worked away 'round the corner for a single. The 50-run stand is also up between these two.
A bumper now over middle stump, Brathwaite ducks under it well.
Around the top of off, Brathwaite eases it off the front foot and towards extra cover for a quick single.
Green comes from around the stumps and tries to attack the ribs of the batter. Jermaine Blackwood is able to keep it down towards short leg.
Nathan Lyon comes back into the attack and starts off with a full toss outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite brooms it away well in front of mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker and flatter around off stump, Blackwood plays it late and down towards backward point.
Tosses it up on off stump, turning in. Blackwood makes an easy block.
Around off, Blackwood nudges it down towards short third man.
A bit quicker and flatter around off, this is punched away towards cover.
Full and around off, this is pushed back to the bowler.

Josh Hazlewood starts off the new spell with a length ball on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it away through square leg for a couple of runs and moves on to 96, his highest score against Australia in Test matches.
Lovely delivery! On a good length and around off, this one nips back in a long way off the deck and almost cuts the batter in half.
Good length again and shaping into middle, this time Brathwaite is able to block it away.
Hazlewood just keeps on probing away on a good length and angles it in from around off. Brathwaite defends it out.

Great awareness to pinch the single there. Back of a length and around middle, Brathwaite hops and pushes it out towards silly mid on. The fielder is a bit back and they are able to scamper through for one.
Back of a length and around off, hurrying onto the batter, Jermaine Blackwood just about keeps it out off the back foot.

Well swept away but equally well fielded in the deep. Tossed up around off, Kraigg Brathwaite gets down on one knee and sweeps it behind square on the leg side. Mitchell Starc from deep square leg runs around to his right and slides in to make the stop. Two runs are taken and Brathwaite is just one away from a century.
Flighted, full and around off, this is eased back to the bowler.
Straight into the fielder! tossed up on off stump, Brathwaite sweeps it hard but straight into Marnus Labuschagne at short leg and that must have hurt a bit.

There it is, Kraigg Brathwaite gets to a terrific hundred and it has been a true captain's knock from him. This is tossed up well outside off and turning in. Brathwaite brooms it away with the turn and towards deep square leg for a single. He will now look to carry this form well into Day 5.
On a nagging length and around off, Jermaine Blackwood keeps it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sharp reflexes from Marnus Labuschagne and Jermaine Blackwood's resistance comes to an end. Nathan Lyon tosses it up on a nagging length and on off stump. The ball grips and turns as Blackwood gets pushed onto the back foot. Blackwood looks to block but gets an inside edge off the pads and to the right of short leg. Labuschagne just sticks out a right hand and grabs it out of thin air. Australia are ecstatic.
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Fullish length, outside off and angling in. Brathwaite looks to block but the ball stays low and beats the outside edge.
On a length and at the stumps, Brathwaite blocks it out on the leg side.
Good length around off, Brathwaite plays it late and behind point for a single.

Top delivery from Josh Hazlewood! Comes from around the wicket to the left-hander and angles in a fullish delivery into off stump. Kyle Mayers looks to play for the line but the ball straightens after pitching and zips past the outside edge.
Keeps it full and angles it into middle, Mayers tentatively pushes it away onto the on side.
Back of a length and angled into the body, Kyle Mayers gets on the back foot to defend but takes a blow on the fingers. The physio is out to have a look as well.
Tosses it up, full and outside off, Brathwaite pushes it gently back to the bowler.
Tossed up again and around off, Brathwaite keeps it out off the front foot.
Switches to around the wicket now and serves a flatter one across the right-hander. Brathwaite stays back and dabs it onto the off side.
Fuller in length and angling across off, Brathwaite blocks it out.
This is around the pads, Brathwaite plays at it with soft hands and keeps it down on the leg side.
Nicely flighted, around middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out and after a bit of teasing, the umpires dislodge the bails. That will be Stumps on Day 4!
Starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery on leg. Mayers tries to clip it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Touch on the shorter side, on off. Mayers fends it onto the turf nicely.

FOUR! In the gap and we have the first boundary of the morning! A fullish delivery, outside off. Mayers drives and opens the face of his blade a bit as he slices it through backward point for a boundary.
Lands it on a length, on off. Mayers dabs it towards covers and takes a quick single.
Switches to 'round the wicket and lands a length delivery angling into off. It bounces a bit extra but Kraigg Brathwaite defends it quite well as he rides the bounce cleverly.
Angles a shortish delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out. Good positive start from the Windies.
Tossed up on middle and sliding on leg. Mayers tries to defend it but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a big appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Going down leg!
Touch shorter and angling into middle. Mayers goes back and defends it towards left of the bowler.
Quicker and flatter on off. Mayers defends it towards the off side this time.
Slower through the air, on middle. Mayers blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery again, on off. Mayers leans forward and defends it again.
An LBW appeal but clearly an inside edge there! He slides this delivery into middle again. Mayers tries to defend it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
A fullish delivery, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to covers for a single.
FOUR! Good confident shot from Mayers! Overpitched delivery, on off. Mayers leans forward and creams it through covers for a lovely boundary. 200 up for West Indies!
Touch shorter and outside off. Mayers leaves it alone carefully.
A fullish delivery, around off. Mayers drives it to covers this time.
Back of a length and around off. Mayers stays deep in his crease and punches it to point. Mayers is looking pretty solid so far.
A fullish delivery from Starc angling into middle. Mayers flicks it nicely again but straight to mid-wicket.
Pitches it on middle and turns it into leg. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it with soft hands towards the leg side.

FOUR! An outside edge but between the slip fielder and the keeper. This is natural variation of an off-spinner again. Shortish length on off. Kraigg Brathwaite goes back and tries to defend it expecting that it will turn. However, it doesn't and the ball catches the outside edge of his blade that runs away from the fielder at first slip towards the third man fence.
Pushes it quicker on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Fires a quicker delivery at 100 kph. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite works it towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the leg side.
Back of a length and around off. Mayers goes for a big pull shot but misses it.
Serves a length delivery on off and Mayers just punches it on the up to the cover fielder.
Goes fuller and on middle. Mayers drives it off the inside half of his blade towards mid-wicket for a single.
Short delivery and angling into off from 'round the wicket. Kraigg Brathwaite rides the bounce and blocks it out.
A fullish delivery around off. Kraigg Brathwaite leans forward and drives it to covers.
Loose shot! Angles a length delivery, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes at it away from his body and gets beaten.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nathan Lyon strikes and Australia have an early wicket! He should have got Mayers off his first delivery of the day but Aussies didn't opt for a review at that time but luckily for them, it has not cost much. Lovely loopy delivery that pitches just short of full length angling from 'round the wicket. Mayers pushes forward to defend it. However, the ball turns and catches the outside edge of his blade. The ball goes right of Smith at first slip and he takes a fine catch here. West Indies need to tighten up!
Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Tossed up, on off. Holder fends it off the front foot.
Shortish delivery on off and turning in. Holder blocks it off the back foot.
Pitches it on off and it turns in again. Holder defends it with soft hands again.
Bowls it quicker and flatter delivery on off. Holder blocks it from his crease.
Tosses this one up on off. Holder leans forward and works it to long on for a single. He is off the mark!
Back of a length, on off. Holder works it to mid-wicket.
Serves a fullish delivery on off. Bit of shape into the batter and Holder drives it to mid off.
Lands it on a good length and outside off. Holder lets it go carefully.
Bowls a fullish delivery, outside off. Holder drives it off the outside half of his blade to point.
On a good length and around off at 137.8 kph. Holder leaves it alone.
Another watchful leave. This is good they just need to be patient here! Josh Hazlewood serves a good-length delivery and outside off. Holder lets it go again.
Turning into middle from off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the leg side.
Touch shorter and it turns again into middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it just uppishly but well short of short leg.
Tossed up delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Pushes it quicker and flatter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Flighted delivery again, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to covers this time.
FOUR! Over the top! This is tossed up, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite reaches the pitch of the ball and slams it down the ground for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off. Holder dabs it towards the point region.
Fullish delivery and on middle. Holder blocks it out solidly.
Bangs it short and it is around leg. Holder ducks under it.
On a good length, on middle. Holder defends it towards the leg side.
A length delivery on off at 129.1 kph. Holder fends it with soft hands towards the off side.
On the shorter side and outside off. Holder leaves it alone. Maiden from Josh Hazlewood.
Tossed up delivery on off. It is turning in and Kraigg Brathwaite gets an inside edge as he tries to defend it.
A fuller delivery on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite sweeps it behind square on the leg side.
A flatter delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.

OUT! BOWLED! That's a killer blow from Nathan Lyon! This might well open the floodgates for Australia! Big, big wicket and Kraigg Brathwaite's stellar knock comes to an end. Lyon has beautifully changed his pace this morning. Bowls it touch short this time and around off. It is at good pace at 98 kph and turns in sharply. Kraigg Brathwaite is neither forwrad nor back and ends up getting an inside edge as he tries to push it towards the off side. The ball knocks over the stumps and West Indies now need something special to save this match.
Howout: b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: On the shorter side and turning into middle. Joshua Da Silva gets an inside edge onto his pads as he tries to defend it.
Lovely loopy delivery, outside off. Joshua Da Silva takes a stride forward and leaves it alone. Brilliant over from Lyon.
Fullish length, around off stump, Jason Holder shoulders arms.
Good length around off, nipping back in off the deck. Jason Holder looks to block it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Close but not close enough! On a good length, close to the off pole and just holding its line. Holder edges it down towards the point region and sets off for the single. Marnus Labuschagne runs around to his left and scores a direct hit at the bowler's end. Holder seemed to be struggling a bit but the replays show that his long reach saved him.
Pitches it up now on off stump, Joshua Da Silva pushes it out on the off side.
On a hard length and outside off, Da Silva chops it in front of point.
This is shorter and at the body, Joshua Da Silva pulls it down towards mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Tossed up on a nagging length and outside off, Joshua Da Silva presses forward well and blocks it out.
A tad quicker and closer to the off pole, Da Silva nudges it in front of the man at silly point.
Floats it up a bit now and on off stump, Joshua Da Silva tentatively defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on off stump, it is well blocked.
Quicker and flatter around off, Joshua Da Silva goes on the back foot to keep this one out.
Tossed up, on a length and around middle, kept out. Maiden!
On a good length and around middle, Holder tucks it straight to mid-wicket and calls for 'no.'
This is fuller and straighter from Green, Holder drives it towards mid on.
A length ball, just angling down leg and Holder looks to tickle it fine but misses.
Almost gets chopped on! Back of a length and over off stump, Jason Holder gets pushed onto the back foot and gets an inside edge that goes past the stumps.
Good length around off stump, Holder makes a leave.
Fraction shorter and well outside off, this is left alone for the keeper to collect.
Nicely drifted onto middle and off, Joshua Da Silva strides out to make the block.
Flighted delivery, full and around off, Da Silva plays it with soft hands and past the man at silly point.
This is tossed up full and around off, Joshua Da Silva smears it away towards extra cover and picks up a single.
Floated up, on middle and leg, Jason Holder leans on and eases it down to long on for one more.
Drags back the length now and slows it up a touch. This one turns in from around off and Joshua Da Silva does well to defend it off the back foot.
Nagging length, turning into middle, Da Silva keeps it out.

Length ball around the top of off stump, Jason Holder solidly blocks it out. The umpire just having a chat with Cameron Green regarding his follow-through as he went into the danger area and has also received an official warning.
Goes wide of the crease now and angles it in from outside off, Holder leaves it alone.
Good length on off, this is punched out towards cover.
Green goes for the bumper and bangs it in over the stumps, Jason Holder ducks under it well.
Fullish length around off, Holder makes an assured leave.
Top of the off stump line and angling in, Jason Holder stays solid in defense.

What happened here? The Aussies appeal for a catch but they are just playing a bit that's all. Lovely delivery from Lyon though. Nagging length close to the off stump and this one goes straight on. Joshua Da Silva looks to play it off the back foot but gets beaten past the outside edge. The ball pops up off Carey's glove and it is grabbed on by the man at leg slip.
on a length and turning into off stump, Da Silva blocks it out.
A tad shorter, Da Silva nudges it down on the leg side.
Tossed up on middle, Joshua Da Silva defends it back to the bowler.
Quicker one on off stump, Da Silva does well to keep it out.
On the shorter side and turning into middle. Joshua Da Silva goes back and works it with soft hands towards short fine leg.
Play and a miss! Travis Head tosses it up first up, full and well outside off, the expansive drive is induced but Jason Holder gets beaten past the outside edge.

OUT! TAKEN! Oh, what a ripper of a catch from Steven Smith! Travis Head gives it a nice loop and bowls it full and wide. Jason Holder reaches out and throws his hands at it, looking to go over covers. Holder is unable to reach the pitch of the ball and gets an outside edge. Alex Carey moves to his right but the ball beats him. Smith though who is almost unsighted at first slip, just puts a reflex dive down to his left and grabs it with both hands. West Indies are going down in a hurry here.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Travis Head

Commentary: Very full and outside off yet again, Chase doesn't play at it.
Tosses it up now around off, Roston Chase makes yet another leave.
This is fuller and outside off, Chase puts a stride forward and lets it through to the keeper.
Floated up, full and outside off, this is driven through covers for a couple of runs.
Turning it onto middle, Joshua Da Silva pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortens the length a bit and turns it into middle and leg, this is played off the back foot and towards mid-wicket.
This is short and wide, Joshua Da Silva has enough time to rock back and cut it past point. Mitchell Starc from backward point gives chase as the batters come back for an easy third run.
Flighted, around off, Roston Chase defends it off the front foot.
Nagging length, close to the off stump and turning in. Chase gets on the back foot and nudges it onto the leg side.
Shorter and around middle, this is forced off the back foot and through mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely tossed up, a bit fuller and on off, Chase leans forward to defend.
Full and straight, Chase flicks it in front of the man at mid-wicket who makes a good diving stop.
Beaten! Head serves this one a bit fuller and looks to turn it into the off pole. Roston Chase strides out to defend but the ball just holds its line and goes past the outside edge.
Half an appeal for lbw but nothing is given. On a length and outside off, turning in. Chase just pads it away.
Tossed up around off, this is eased away towards cover for a single.
Shortens the length now and Joshua Da Silva punches it off the back foot through the cover region and picks up a couple of runs.
The new ball does shape back a bit. Starc starts off with a fuller one on middle and this one swings back in late. Roston Chase works it away through mid-wicket for one.
A bit too straight from Starc, full and down leg, flicked down to fine leg for a single. The ball came off the pads of Da Silva and a leg bye is signalled.
Full and angling into leg stump, this is clipped away behind square on the leg side for one more.
Full again and attacking middle stump, Joshua Da Silva hits it firmly towards mid on.
Goes full and wide now, very wide and at 142.3 clicks. Joshua Da Silva looks to reach out and drive it square but is well beaten.
Well left! Length ball, close to the off pole and at 141.3 clicks. Joshua Da Silva watches it closely and leaves it on line.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Chase makes a good leave.
Back of a length, on off. Chase gets right behind it and blocks it out.
Bowls a fullish delivery on off. Chase defends it solidly again back to the bowler.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. The ball shapes away a bit and Chase leaves it.
Oh, lovely delivery! Bowls another good-length delivery, around off. The ball seams away and Chase gets beaten as he tries to defend it.
On a length, on off. Chase with a solid block from his crease.
Lovely inswinging full delivery, on middle. Joshua Da Silva just about manages to drive it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nice shot! Overpitched delivery, shaping into off. Joshua Da Silva though shows the full face of his blade and drives it past mid off for a boundary.
Pulls his length back slightly and it is around off. Joshua Da Silva makes a good leave.
Drives this full delivery on off again firmly but this time to mid off. Joshua Da Silva is looking much more assured in this innings than he was in the first one.
Starc bowls it on the shortish length, around off. Joshua Da Silva tries to pull it but misses.
Inswinger again, on middle and Joshua Da Silva flicks it to fine leg for a single.
A good-length delivery and outside off. Joshua Da Silva leaves it alone. Not much bounce there.

OUT! CAUGHT! Josh Hazlewood strikes and Joshua Da Silva after playing some good shots has to make his way back to the pavilion. Australia now are just three wickets away from sealing this game. Just short of good length and around off. Joshua Da Silva tries to punch it away from his body as the ball nips away a bit. It catches the outside edge and goes straight into the hands of Usman Khawaja at third slip. Much-deserved wicket for Josh Hazlewood and he looks a relieved man.
Howout: c Usman Khawaja b Josh Hazlewood

Commentary: In that channel around off again. The ball shapes away and beats the outside edge of Alzarri Joseph's blade as he tries to defend it.
Back of a length, on off. Joseph blocks it solidly from his crease.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Joseph leaves it alone.
Bangs it short and on middle. Alzarri Joseph ducks under it. A maiden-wicket from Josh Hazlewood!
On a length, on off at 139 clicks. Chase defends it to mid off for a single.

Oh, what a ripper! Starc bowls a pacy good-length delivery on off. The ball shapes into him and Jospeh is very late to react as the ball zips between his bat and pad as the ball goes just over the stumps.
Bowls a very full delivery on middle. Alzarri Joseph blocks it out.
Bangs it short and on middle. Alzarri Joseph ducks under it.
TWO BYES! Serves a fullish delivery that shapes down the leg side. Carey behind the stumps fails to collect it cleanly as he ball deflects off his gloves towards the fine leg region. Two byes taken.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Starc with an overpitched delivery, around off. Joseph leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
On a good length, on middle. Chase works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Serves a fullish delivery that shapes away a tad. Chase drives it to covers.
On a good length and around off. Chase with a good leave this time.
Bowls it short and angling on middle and leg. Chase ducks under it comfortably.
On a good length, on off. Chase blocks it off the front foot.
Shortish delivery on off. Chase rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side for a single.
Shorter in length and quicker on middle. Chase works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Oh, Joseph goes for a big hit here! Tossed up, around off. Joseph decides to go for a big slog-sweep but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Touch shorter and quicker on off. Alzarri Joseph blocks it out.
Turning into middle at a quicker pace again. Alzarri Joseph defends it off the front foot.
Pitches it on middle and it turns into leg. Alzarri Joseph works it to deep backward square leg and takes three.
Flatter and around off. Chase punches it to covers for a single.
A fullish delivery on off. Chase blocks it off the front foot.
Lands on a length, on off. Chase fends it solidly again.
Back of a length and around off. Chase hops and tries to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Chase works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Green bangs it short and on middle and leg. Joseph easily ducks under it.

NO BALL! Short delivery again on middle and too high this time as Alzarri Joseph ducks under it again. The umpire calls it wide first for height but then it was found out that Green has overstepped so, it is a No Ball.
On the shorter side, on off. Alzarri Joseph punches it to covers for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Joseph blocks it out.
Touch shorter and on off. Joseph defends it nicely.
SIX! SHOT! Hits it long way into the stands! Tossed up, on off. Joseph slog-sweeps and connects it quite well this time as he hits it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
Quicker and flatter around off. Joseph defends it towards the off side with soft hands.
Turning into middle and leg. Touch shorter and Joseph gets hit on the thigh pad as he tries to work it towards the leg side.
Flatter and quicker on middle. Alzarri Joseph works it to square leg and takes a single. That shall be Lunch on Day 5!
Lovely start from Mitchell Starc. A cross-seamer this, full and slanted across the right-hander. The ball just zips off the deck and zips past the outside edge of Joseph's bat.
A touch fuller and wider of the off stump, Alzarri Joseph has a feel for it but leaves it alone. The ball stays a bit low on its way to the keeper.
Full and wide at 141.6 clicks, this is squeezed out towards point.
A length ball now, pushed well across the batter and Jospeh lets it through to the keeper.
Starc switches to around the wicket now and angles in a fullish delivery into off stump. Alzarri Joseph solidly blocks it off the front foot.

Beaten! Half an appeal for caught behind and they have a chat about it but decide against reviewing it. On a length and angling into off stump, Joseph looks to block but the ball straightens and beats the outside edge.
Toses it up first up, on a shorter length and spinning into middle. Roston Chase hops on the back foot to keep this one out.
Flatter delivery around off, this is pushed off the back foot in front of silly point for a run.
Pushed a bit wider of off stump, Joseph keeps it out on the off side.
Nagging length, drifted onto middle and leg, Joseph watchfully blocks it out.

Nicely bowled and somewhat nicely played as well. Flighted delivery, on a length and outside off. This one grips a bit and Alzarri Joseph does well to ride the bounce and nudge it past first slip for a couple of runs.
Tossed up outside off, left alone for the keeper to collect.
Starc comes from around the wicket and angles it on a good length from outside off. Roston Chase stays back and dabs it down through backward point for a run.
Good length, around the top of off and caressed away towards cover.
A bumper now around off stump and delivered at a good height as well. Alzarri Joseph ducks under it.
Fuller and angling into the stumps, Joseph stays solid in defense.
Just a bit of noise but not off the bat. This is full again, on the fifth stump line and angling in. Alzarri Joseph looks for the booming cover drive but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Goes for the bouncer now, over off stump and Joseph ducks under it well.
Nagging length, turning in sharply from around off. Roston Chase gets right behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Loops it up a bit and serves it full on middle, Chase drives it right back at the bowler.
Tossed up around middle, this is worked away well in front of mid-wicket for a single.
Floated up around off stump, Joseph just blocks it out.
Fullish delivery around middle, Joseph blocks it out on the leg side.
Pushed through quicker and fuller outside off, Alzarri Joseph lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Too full and too straight from Starc, Roston Chase just clips it off his legs and through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length in that channel around off, left alone by Chase.
Full and angling into middle, this is flicked away towards mid-wicket.
An attempted short ball at the body but just angles down the leg side. Roston Chase moves away from the line of the ball.
Short of a length and at the body, Chase hops to defend but misses and gets hit around the thigh pad.
Good length on off stump, Chase defends it out on the on side.
Shorter and slower through the air, turning into middle, Jospeh solidly blocks it out.
Tossed up full and around off, Alzarri Joseph strides out to defend.
Drags back the length and bowls it around off, Joseph pushes back and keeps it out.
Tossed up a bit wide of the off stump and Joseph doesn't play at it.
On a length and turning into off stump, Alzarri Joseph makes another easy block.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished. This is tossed up outside off, Alzarri Joseph leans into it and drives it firmly through extra cover for a boundary.
Shorter and just angling down leg, this one shoots up off the deck as Alex Carey makes a good take flying to his left.
Fuller and angled into middle stump, Roston Chase gets an inside edge through square leg and rotates the strike.
Around the top of off and at 141.3 clicks, Joseph taps it out towards point.
Good length around middle and leg, this is dabbed down towards mid-wicket by Joseph.
A solid bumper now over the stumps but Alzarri Joseph is able to duck under it with ease.
This is pitched up on middle and leg, Alzarri Joseph punches it back to the bowler.
SIX! All the way! Tossed up around middle, Roston Chase just frees his arms and swings through the line of the ball smoking it over the long on fence for a maximum.
Flatter one around off, this is pushed away towards cover for a single.
Nicely done. This is a tad shorter and around off, turning in, Alzarri Joseph plays it late and edges it down towards third man for a couple of runs.
SIX! BANG! These two batters having a bit of fun out there in the middle now. Lyon tosses it up from around the wicket and on middle, Alzarri Joseph slogs it over the wide long on fence for a biggie.
On a length and turning down leg, left alone by Joseph.
Shorter and around off, Alzarri Joseph keeps it out on the off side.
Good length on middle and leg, Roston Chase works it off his legs and through square leg. The fielder from fine leg runs around to his left but the batters are able to pick up three runs.
Around the top of off, Joseph pushes it out on the off side.
Length again, around off stump, Alzarri Joseph just dabs it towards backward point and looks for one but his partner denies the run.
This is angled into middle and leg, Jospeh stays on the back foot and nudges it onto the leg side.
A short ball now over middle with not much pace behind it. Joseph has ample time to duck under it.
Good length around middle, this is defended back onto the deck.
Tossed up full and on middle, Roston Chase drives it through wide mid on and picks up a single.
Keeps it full and on off stump, Alzarri Joseph pushes it towards mid off.
SIX! Up, up and over! Nicely tossed up on off stump, Alzarri Joseph plays it with the turn and whacks it high and handsome over the man at long on for a maximum.
Flatter delivery around off, Joseph strides forward but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

FOUR! Nicely deflected! A tad shorter and turning in from middle, Alzarri Joseph goes on the back foot and looks to just nudge it down but ends up tickling it towards fine leg. David Warner chases after it but the ball wins the race. The 300 is also up for West Indies!

Shouts of 'catch it,' but there's no one there. Quicker one around off, Alzarri Joseph looks to defend off the front foot but gets na inside edge off the pads towards silly point but the man had already been taken out from there.
Angles a length delivery on off. Chase defends it towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and on the pads. Chase flicks it to fine leg for a couple.

Just short! On a good length and around off. The ball seams away a bit and catches the outside edge of the blade of Chase as he tries to defend it. The ball goes off the thick outside edge and falls just short of widish third slip.
Serves a length delivery and outside off. Chase leaves it alone.
Lands it on a length, on middle. Chase blocks it from his crease.
Serves a fullish delivery on the pads. Chase flicks it through mid-wicket. Cummins runs behind it and he does not look comfortable there but manages to stop it inside the ropes. Three taken.
Tossed up, on off. Chase drives it towards the off side.
Slower through the air, on off. Chase with a solid block off the front foot.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tossed up, around off. Chase leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
On the shorter side, on middle. Chase clips it to square leg for a single.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Joseph blocks it out.
Another solid block! Flatter and on off. Joseph gets right behind it to block it.
On a good length and outside off. Chase leaves it alone.
Serves it on a length again and outside off. Chase with an easy leave.
Goes fuller and down the leg side. Chase tries to clip it but misses.
Shortish and outside off. Chase makes a good leave again.
Serves a fullish delivery on middle. Chase flicks it wide of mid on but the fielder moves swiftly to his right and stops it.
Lands it on a length and Chase is solid in his front foot defence again.
FOUR! Poor delivery and punished! Short and wide outside off. Joseph rocks back and cuts it through point for a boundary.
On the shorter side again, on middle. Joseph defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Alzarri Joseph pushes it to mid off.
Tossd up and around off. Alzarri Joseph goes for a big slog across the line but misses.

Oh, dropped! This is slower through the air again and outside off. Joseph tries to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball catches the outside edge of his blade. Carey though fails to judge the line of the ball and the ball hits his leg and deflects away. Will it cost Australia?

OUT! BOWLED! This time he is gone and finally, Australia manage to break this partnership! What an inspired bowling change by Cummins. This is bowled quicker and flatter on off. Joseph tries to defend it and plays for a turn. However, it is again the natural variation of the off-spinner that does the trick as the ball goes straight and beats the outside edge of Joseph's blade. The ball goes onto knock over the stumps and can Australia wrap this match quickly now?
Howout: b Travis Head

Commentary: On middle, this is swept away hard and along the ground through square leg for a single.
Tossed up on a length and outside off, Jayden Seales leaves it alone.
Floated up full and around off, Seales leans forward and makes the block.
Tossed up, outside off. Seales leaves it alone.
Goes quicker and flatter on off. Seales blocks it out.
Lyon tosses it up and it is outside off. Seales leaves it alone.
A flatter delivery on off. Chase blocks it out.
Tossed up and on off. Chase plays a lofted drive and it is hit towards the long on region. He comes back for the second run as the fielder cuts it off.
Flatter and quicker on off. Chase blocks it off the front foot.
This is pushed fuller and outside off. Chase tries to drive it but misses.
Fuller again and outside off. Chase drives it through covers for a single.
A full toss on the pads. Seales works it to wide of mid on for a single.
On middle and turning away. Seales defends it onto the turf and the ball rolls behind the stumps. Carey picks it and flicks it onto the stumps. No damage done.
Tossed up, on off. Seales blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller delivery and quicker too. Seales defends it solidly again.
This one is pitched, around off and it turns away too. Seales leaves it alone.
Angling on the pads this time. Seales clips it to fine leg and comes back for the second run.
Touch shorter and on off. Seales blocks it from his crease.
Tossed up, on off. Chase drives it to mid off this time.
Slower through the air, on off. Chase blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle and leg. Chase drives it to long on for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off. Seales drives it back to the bowler.
Slidling into middle and leg. Seales defends it towards the leg side.
Fuller delivery on off. Seales pushes it towards the off side.
Tossed up delivery on off. Chase drills it down the ground for a single.
Fires it quicker and angles it into leg. Seales works it with soft hands towards the leg side.
Fuller and on middle at 88.8 kph. Seales defends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air on middle. Seales defends it towards the leg side just away from short leg.
On the shorter side, around off. Seales gets across and covers the line of the ball and allows the ball to hit his pads.
Tossed up delivery on middle.Seales works it towards the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Chase drives it firmly back to the bowler.
Tossed up delivery on off. Chase tries to drive it but the ball goes off the inside half of his blade to the leg side.

Inside edge but that will do for Roston Chase! Gets to his fifty. Superb knock under pressure. This is tossed up on middle. Chase tries to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball catches the inside edge of his blade and goes just wide of short fine leg and two runs are taken.
Flatter and on middle. Chase drives it to long on for a single.
Oh, close! A very full delivery, around off. Seales looks to drive it but gets the inside edge that goes past the stumps for a couple of runs to fine leg.
Wider outside off and touch short. Seales blocks it as he plants his front foot forward towards the ball.
FOUR! Lovely timing from Roston Chase. This is tossed up on the leg stump, Chase stands tall and hoicks it over mid-wicket and picks up another boundary off Lyon.
Nicely bowled! Just pulls back the length a touch and pushes it through quicker around off, Chase looks to block but the ball zips past the outside edge.
On off stump, Chase defends it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Nathan Lyon has the last laugh here and picks up a brilliant five-wicket haul. Lyon gioves it a bit more air and shortens the length ever so slightly on middle and leg. Roston Chase looks to just heave it aerially and in front of mid-wicket but gets undone in flight and ends up playing it off the inner half of the bat and much squarer. Mitchell Starc from deep mid-wicket rushes in and dives forward to take a good low catch. End of a fighting knock from Chase and Australia are onje wicket away from victory.
Howout: c Mitchell Starc b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! That's it, Australia have done it! Lovely bit of bowling once again from Nathan Lyon and he ends the innings with 6 wickets in his bag. This is flighted up on a nagging length and around off. Kemar Roach looks to play for the turn and puts out a dead bat at it but the ball goes straight on with the arm and knocks over the top of off stump. Roach departs for a golden duck and Australia win by 164 runs.
Howout: b Nathan Lyon
